v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

72constexpr MachineType kMaybeSandboxedPointer =
73 V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL ? MachineType::SandboxedPointer()
74 : MachineType::Pointer();
75
76#define FATAL_UNSUPPORTED_OPCODE(opcode) \
77 FATAL("Unsupported opcode 0x%x:%s", (opcode), \
78 wasm::WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode));
79
80MachineType assert_size(int expected_size, MachineType type) {
81 DCHECK_EQ(expected_size, ElementSizeInBytes(type.representation()));
82 return type;
83}
84
85#define WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_SIZE(name) \
86 (WasmTrustedInstanceData::k##name##OffsetEnd - \
87 WasmTrustedInstanceData::k##name##Offset + 1) // NOLINT(whitespace/indent)
88
89#define LOAD_MUTABLE_INSTANCE_FIELD(name, type) \
90 gasm_->LoadFromObject( \
91 assert_size(WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_SIZE(name), type), GetInstanceData(), \
92 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTrustedInstanceData::k##name##Offset))
93
94#define LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(name, type) \
95 gasm_->LoadImmutable( \
96 assert_size(WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_SIZE(name), type), GetInstanceData(), \
97 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTrustedInstanceData::k##name##Offset))
98
99#define LOAD_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(name) \
100 gasm_->LoadProtectedPointerFromObject( \
101 GetInstanceData(), \
102 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged( \
103 WasmTrustedInstanceData::kProtected##name##Offset));
104
105#define LOAD_IMMUTABLE_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(name) \
106 gasm_->LoadImmutableProtectedPointerFromObject( \
107 GetInstanceData(), \
108 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged( \
109 WasmTrustedInstanceData::kProtected##name##Offset));
110
111#define LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD_NO_ELIMINATION(name, type) \
112 gasm_->Load( \
113 assert_size(WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_SIZE(name), type), GetInstanceData(), \
114 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTrustedInstanceData::k##name##Offset))
115
116// Use MachineType::Pointer() over Tagged() to load root pointers because they
117// do not get compressed.
118#define LOAD_ROOT(RootName, factory_name) \
119 (isolate_ ? graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->HeapConstant( \
120 isolate_->factory()->factory_name())) \
121 : gasm_->LoadImmutable( \
122 MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot(), \
123 IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::k##RootName)))
124
125#define LOAD_MUTABLE_ROOT(RootName, factory_name) \
126 (isolate_ ? graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->HeapConstant( \
127 isolate_->factory()->factory_name())) \
128 : gasm_->BitcastWordToTagged(gasm_->Load( \
129 MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot(), \
130 IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::k##RootName))))
131
132template <typename T>
133bool ContainsSimd(const Signature<T>* sig) {
134 for (auto type : sig->all()) {
135 if (type == T::Primitive(wasm::kS128)) return true;
136 }
137 return false;
138}
139
140bool ContainsInt64(const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig) {
141 for (auto type : sig->all()) {
142 if (type == wasm::kCanonicalI64) return true;
143 }
144 return false;
145}

149WasmGraphBuilder::WasmGraphBuilder(
150 wasm::CompilationEnv* env, Zone* zone, MachineGraph* mcgraph,
151 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
152 compiler::SourcePositionTable* source_position_table,
153 ParameterMode parameter_mode, Isolate* isolate,
154 wasm::WasmEnabledFeatures enabled_features,
155 const wasm::CanonicalSig* wrapper_sig)
156 : gasm_(std::make_unique<WasmGraphAssembler>(mcgraph, zone)),
157 zone_(zone),
158 mcgraph_(mcgraph),
159 env_(env),
160 enabled_features_(enabled_features),
161 has_simd_(sig ? ContainsSimd(sig) : ContainsSimd(wrapper_sig)),
162 function_sig_(sig),
163 wrapper_sig_(wrapper_sig),
164 source_position_table_(source_position_table),
165 parameter_mode_(parameter_mode),
166 isolate_(isolate),
167 null_check_strategy_(trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled() &&
168 V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
169 ? NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler
170 : NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit) {
171 // This code is only used
172 // - for compiling certain wrappers (wasm-to-fast API, C-wasm-entry), and
173 // - for inlining js-to-wasm wrappers into Turbofan-compile JS functions.
174 CHECK(parameter_mode != ParameterMode::kInstanceParameterMode);
175
176 // There are two kinds of isolate-specific code: JS-to-JS wrappers (passing
177 // kNoSpecialParameterMode) and JS-to-Wasm wrappers (passing
178 // kJSFunctionAbiMode).
179 DCHECK_IMPLIES(isolate != nullptr,
180 parameter_mode_ == kJSFunctionAbiMode ||
181 parameter_mode_ == kNoSpecialParameterMode);
182 DCHECK_IMPLIES(env && env->module &&
183 std::any_of(env->module->memories.begin(),
184 env->module->memories.end(),
185 [](auto& memory) {
186 return memory.bounds_checks ==
187 wasm::kTrapHandler;
188 }),
189 trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled());
190 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mcgraph_);
191}
192
193// Destructor define here where the definition of {WasmGraphAssembler} is
194// available.
195WasmGraphBuilder::~WasmGraphBuilder() = default;
196
197bool WasmGraphBuilder::TryWasmInlining(int fct_index,
198 wasm::NativeModule* native_module,
199 int inlining_id) {
200#define TRACE(x) \
201 do { \
202 if (v8_flags.trace_turbo_inlining) { \
203 StdoutStream() << x << "\n"; \
204 } \
205 } while (false)
206
207 DCHECK(native_module->HasWireBytes());
208 const wasm::WasmModule* module = native_module->module();
209 const wasm::WasmFunction& inlinee = module->functions[fct_index];
210 // TODO(mliedtke): What would be a proper maximum size?
211 const uint32_t kMaxWasmInlineeSize = 30;
212 if (inlinee.code.length() > kMaxWasmInlineeSize) {
213 TRACE("- not inlining: function body is larger than max inlinee size ("
214 << inlinee.code.length() << " > " << kMaxWasmInlineeSize << ")");
215 return false;
216 }
217 if (inlinee.imported) {
218 TRACE("- not inlining: function is imported");
219 return false;
220 }
221 base::Vector<const uint8_t> bytes(native_module->wire_bytes().SubVector(
222 inlinee.code.offset(), inlinee.code.end_offset()));
223 bool is_shared = module->type(inlinee.sig_index).is_shared;
224 const wasm::FunctionBody inlinee_body(inlinee.sig, inlinee.code.offset(),
225 bytes.begin(), bytes.end(), is_shared);
226 // If the inlinee was not validated before, do that now.
227 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!module->function_was_validated(fct_index))) {
228 wasm::WasmDetectedFeatures unused_detected_features;
229 if (ValidateFunctionBody(graph()->zone(), enabled_features_, module,
230 &unused_detected_features, inlinee_body)
231 .failed()) {
232 // At this point we cannot easily raise a compilation error any more.
233 // Since this situation is highly unlikely though, we just ignore this
234 // inlinee and move on. The same validation error will be triggered
235 // again when actually compiling the invalid function.
236 TRACE("- not inlining: function body is invalid");
237 return false;
238 }
239 module->set_function_validated(fct_index);
240 }
241 bool result = WasmIntoJSInliner::TryInlining(
242 graph()->zone(), module, mcgraph_, inlinee_body, bytes,
243 source_position_table_, inlining_id);
244 TRACE((
245 result
246 ? "- inlining"
247 : "- not inlining: function body contains unsupported instructions"));
248 return result;
249#undef TRACE
250}

252void WasmGraphBuilder::Start(unsigned params) {
253 Node* start = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Start(params));
254 graph()->SetStart(start);
255 SetEffectControl(start);
256 // Initialize parameter nodes.
257 parameters_ = zone_->AllocateArray<Node*>(params);
258 for (unsigned i = 0; i < params; i++) {
259 parameters_[i] = nullptr;
260 }
261 // Initialize instance node.
262 switch (parameter_mode_) {
263 case kInstanceParameterMode: {
264 Node* param = Param(wasm::kWasmInstanceDataParameterIndex);
265 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
266 Assert(gasm_->HasInstanceType(param, WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_TYPE),
267 AbortReason::kUnexpectedInstanceType);
268 }
269 instance_data_node_ = param;
270 break;
271 }
272 case kWasmImportDataMode: {
273 Node* param = Param(0);
274 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
275 Assert(gasm_->HasInstanceType(param, WASM_IMPORT_DATA_TYPE),
276 AbortReason::kUnexpectedInstanceType);
277 }
278 instance_data_node_ = gasm_->LoadProtectedPointerFromObject(
279 param, wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
280 WasmImportData::kProtectedInstanceDataOffset));
281 break;
282 }
283 case kJSFunctionAbiMode: {
284 Node* param = Param(Linkage::kJSCallClosureParamIndex, "%closure");
285 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
286 Assert(gasm_->HasInstanceType(param, JS_FUNCTION_TYPE),
287 AbortReason::kUnexpectedInstanceType);
288 }
289 instance_data_node_ = gasm_->LoadExportedFunctionInstanceData(
290 gasm_->LoadFunctionDataFromJSFunction(param));
291 break;
292 }
293 case kNoSpecialParameterMode:
294 break;
295 }
296 graph()->SetEnd(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->End(0)));
297}
298
299Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Param(int index, const char* debug_name) {
300 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(graph()->start());
301 // Turbofan allows negative parameter indices.
302 DCHECK_GE(index, kMinParameterIndex);
303 int array_index = index - kMinParameterIndex;
304 if (parameters_[array_index] == nullptr) {
305 parameters_[array_index] = graph()->NewNode(
306 mcgraph()->common()->Parameter(index, debug_name), graph()->start());
307 }
308 return parameters_[array_index];
309}
310
311Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Loop(Node* entry) {
312 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Loop(1), entry);
313}
314
315void WasmGraphBuilder::TerminateLoop(Node* effect, Node* control) {
316 Node* terminate =
317 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Terminate(), effect, control);
318 gasm_->MergeControlToEnd(terminate);
319}
320
321Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoopExit(Node* loop_node) {
322 DCHECK(loop_node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kLoop);
323 Node* loop_exit =
324 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->LoopExit(), control(), loop_node);
325 Node* loop_exit_effect = graph()->NewNode(
326 mcgraph()->common()->LoopExitEffect(), effect(), loop_exit);
327 SetEffectControl(loop_exit_effect, loop_exit);
328 return loop_exit;
329}
330
331Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoopExitValue(Node* value,
332 MachineRepresentation representation) {
333 DCHECK_EQ(control()->opcode(), IrOpcode::kLoopExit);
334 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->LoopExitValue(representation),
335 value, control());
336}
337
338void WasmGraphBuilder::TerminateThrow(Node* effect, Node* control) {
339 Node* terminate =
340 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Throw(), effect, control);
341 gasm_->MergeControlToEnd(terminate);
342 gasm_->InitializeEffectControl(nullptr, nullptr);
343}
344
345bool WasmGraphBuilder::IsPhiWithMerge(Node* phi, Node* merge) {
346 return phi && IrOpcode::IsPhiOpcode(phi->opcode()) &&
347 NodeProperties::GetControlInput(phi) == merge;
348}
349
350bool WasmGraphBuilder::ThrowsException(Node* node, Node** if_success,
351 Node** if_exception) {
352 if (node->op()->HasProperty(compiler::Operator::kNoThrow)) {
353 return false;
354 }
355
356 *if_success = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfSuccess(), node);
357 *if_exception =
358 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfException(), node, node);
359
360 return true;
361}
362
363void WasmGraphBuilder::AppendToMerge(Node* merge, Node* from) {
364 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsMergeOpcode(merge->opcode()));
365 merge->AppendInput(mcgraph()->zone(), from);
366 int new_size = merge->InputCount();
367 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
368 merge, mcgraph()->common()->ResizeMergeOrPhi(merge->op(), new_size));
369}
370
371void WasmGraphBuilder::AppendToPhi(Node* phi, Node* from) {
372 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsPhiOpcode(phi->opcode()));
373 int new_size = phi->InputCount();
374 phi->InsertInput(mcgraph()->zone(), phi->InputCount() - 1, from);
375 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
376 phi, mcgraph()->common()->ResizeMergeOrPhi(phi->op(), new_size));
377}

379template <typename... Nodes>
380Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Merge(Node* fst, Nodes*... args) {
381 return graph()->NewNode(this->mcgraph()->common()->Merge(1 + sizeof...(args)),
382 fst, args...);
383}
384
385Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Merge(unsigned count, Node** controls) {
386 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Merge(count), count, controls);
387}
388
389Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Phi(wasm::ValueType type, unsigned count,
390 Node** vals_and_control) {
391 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsMergeOpcode(vals_and_control[count]->opcode()));
392 DCHECK_EQ(vals_and_control[count]->op()->ControlInputCount(), count);
393 return graph()->NewNode(
394 mcgraph()->common()->Phi(type.machine_representation(), count), count + 1,
395 vals_and_control);
396}
397
398Node* WasmGraphBuilder::EffectPhi(unsigned count, Node** effects_and_control) {
399 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsMergeOpcode(effects_and_control[count]->opcode()));
400 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1,
401 effects_and_control);
402}

404Node* WasmGraphBuilder::RefNull(wasm::ValueType type) {
405 // This version is for functions, not wrappers.
406 DCHECK_EQ(parameter_mode_, kInstanceParameterMode);
407 return gasm_->Null(type);
408}
409
410Node* WasmGraphBuilder::RefFunc(uint32_t function_index) {
411 Node* func_refs = LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(FuncRefs, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
412 Node* maybe_function =
413 gasm_->LoadFixedArrayElementPtr(func_refs, function_index);
414 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
415 auto create_funcref = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
416 // We only care to distinguish between zero and funcref, "IsI31" is close
417 // enough.
418 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->IsSmi(maybe_function), &create_funcref);
419 gasm_->Goto(&done, maybe_function);
420
421 gasm_->Bind(&create_funcref);
422 Node* function_from_builtin = gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
423 Builtin::kWasmRefFunc, Operator::kNoThrow,
424 gasm_->Uint32Constant(function_index), gasm_->Int32Constant(0));
425 gasm_->Goto(&done, function_from_builtin);
426
427 gasm_->Bind(&done);
428 return done.PhiAt(0);
429}

460void WasmGraphBuilder::StackCheck(
461 WasmInstanceCacheNodes* shared_memory_instance_cache,
462 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
463 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(env_); // Wrappers don't get stack checks.
464 if (!v8_flags.wasm_stack_checks) return;
465
466 Node* limit =
467 gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), gasm_->LoadRootRegister(),
468 mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(IsolateData::jslimit_offset()));
469
470 Node* check = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
471 mcgraph()->machine()->StackPointerGreaterThan(StackCheckKind::kWasm),
472 limit, effect()));
473
474 auto [if_true, if_false] = BranchExpectTrue(check);
475
476 if (stack_check_call_operator_ == nullptr) {
477 // Build and cache the stack check call operator and the constant
478 // representing the stack check code.
479
480 // A direct call to a wasm runtime stub defined in this module.
481 // Just encode the stub index. This will be patched at relocation.
482 stack_check_code_node_.set(
483 mcgraph()->RelocatableWasmBuiltinCallTarget(Builtin::kWasmStackGuard));
484
485 constexpr Operator::Properties properties =
486 Operator::kNoThrow | Operator::kNoWrite;
487 // If we ever want to mark this call as kNoDeopt, we'll have to make it
488 // non-eliminatable some other way.
489 static_assert((properties & Operator::kEliminatable) !=
490 Operator::kEliminatable);
491 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
492 mcgraph()->zone(), // zone
493 NoContextDescriptor{}, // descriptor
494 0, // stack parameter count
495 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, // flags
496 properties, // properties
497 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub); // stub call mode
498 stack_check_call_operator_ = mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor);
499 }
500
501 Node* call =
502 graph()->NewNode(stack_check_call_operator_.get(),
503 stack_check_code_node_.get(), effect(), if_false);
504 SetSourcePosition(call, position);
505
506 DCHECK_GT(call->op()->EffectOutputCount(), 0);
507 DCHECK_EQ(call->op()->ControlOutputCount(), 0);
508
509 SetEffectControl(call, if_false);
510
511 // We only need to refresh the size of a shared memory, as its start can never
512 // change.
513 // We handle caching of the instance cache nodes manually, and we may reload
514 // them in contexts where load elimination would eliminate the reload.
515 // Therefore, we use plain Load nodes which are not subject to load
516 // elimination.
517 DCHECK_IMPLIES(shared_memory_instance_cache, has_cached_memory());
518 Node* new_memory_size = shared_memory_instance_cache == nullptr
519 ? nullptr
520 : LoadMemSize(cached_memory_index_);
521
522 Node* merge = Merge(if_true, control());
523 Node* ephi_inputs[] = {check, effect(), merge};
524 Node* ephi = EffectPhi(2, ephi_inputs);
525
526 if (shared_memory_instance_cache != nullptr) {
527 shared_memory_instance_cache->mem_size = CreateOrMergeIntoPhi(
528 MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), merge,
529 shared_memory_instance_cache->mem_size, new_memory_size);
530 }
531
532 SetEffectControl(ephi, merge);
533}
534
535void WasmGraphBuilder::PatchInStackCheckIfNeeded() {
536 if (!needs_stack_check_) return;
537
538 Node* start = graph()->start();
539 // Place a stack check which uses a dummy node as control and effect.
540 Node* dummy = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Dead());
541 SetEffectControl(dummy);
542 // The function-prologue stack check is associated with position 0, which
543 // is never a position of any instruction in the function.
544 // We pass the null instance cache, as we are at the beginning of the function
545 // and do not need to update it.
546 StackCheck(nullptr, 0);
547
548 // In testing, no stack checks were emitted. Nothing to rewire then.
549 if (effect() == dummy) return;
550
551 // Now patch all control uses of {start} to use {control} and all effect uses
552 // to use {effect} instead. We exclude Projection nodes: Projections pointing
553 // to start are floating control, and we want it to point directly to start
554 // because of restrictions later in the pipeline (specifically, loop
555 // unrolling).
556 // Then rewire the dummy node to use start instead.
557 NodeProperties::ReplaceUses(start, start, effect(), control());
558 {
559 // We need an intermediate vector because we are not allowed to modify a use
560 // while traversing uses().
561 std::vector<Node*> projections;
562 for (Node* use : control()->uses()) {
563 if (use->opcode() == IrOpcode::kProjection) projections.emplace_back(use);
564 }
565 for (Node* use : projections) {
566 use->ReplaceInput(NodeProperties::FirstControlIndex(use), start);
567 }
568 }
569 NodeProperties::ReplaceUses(dummy, nullptr, start, start);
570}
571
572Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Binop(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode, Node* left, Node* right,
573 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
574 const Operator* op;
575 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
576 switch (opcode) {
577 case wasm::kExprI32Add:
578 op = m->Int32Add();
579 break;
580 case wasm::kExprI32Sub:
581 op = m->Int32Sub();
582 break;
583 case wasm::kExprI32Mul:
584 op = m->Int32Mul();
585 break;
586 case wasm::kExprI32DivS:
587 return BuildI32DivS(left, right, position);
588 case wasm::kExprI32DivU:
589 return BuildI32DivU(left, right, position);
590 case wasm::kExprI32RemS:
591 return BuildI32RemS(left, right, position);
592 case wasm::kExprI32RemU:
593 return BuildI32RemU(left, right, position);
594 case wasm::kExprI32And:
595 op = m->Word32And();
596 break;
597 case wasm::kExprI32Ior:
598 op = m->Word32Or();
599 break;
600 case wasm::kExprI32Xor:
601 op = m->Word32Xor();
602 break;
603 case wasm::kExprI32Shl:
604 op = m->Word32Shl();
605 right = MaskShiftCount32(right);
606 break;
607 case wasm::kExprI32ShrU:
608 op = m->Word32Shr();
609 right = MaskShiftCount32(right);
610 break;
611 case wasm::kExprI32ShrS:
612 op = m->Word32Sar();
613 right = MaskShiftCount32(right);
614 break;
615 case wasm::kExprI32Ror:
616 op = m->Word32Ror();
617 right = MaskShiftCount32(right);
618 break;
619 case wasm::kExprI32Rol:
620 if (m->Word32Rol().IsSupported()) {
621 op = m->Word32Rol().op();
622 right = MaskShiftCount32(right);
623 break;
624 }
625 return BuildI32Rol(left, right);
626 case wasm::kExprI32Eq:
627 op = m->Word32Equal();
628 break;
629 case wasm::kExprI32Ne:
630 return Invert(Binop(wasm::kExprI32Eq, left, right));
631 case wasm::kExprI32LtS:
632 op = m->Int32LessThan();
633 break;
634 case wasm::kExprI32LeS:
635 op = m->Int32LessThanOrEqual();
636 break;
637 case wasm::kExprI32LtU:
638 op = m->Uint32LessThan();
639 break;
640 case wasm::kExprI32LeU:
641 op = m->Uint32LessThanOrEqual();
642 break;
643 case wasm::kExprI32GtS:
644 op = m->Int32LessThan();
645 std::swap(left, right);
646 break;
647 case wasm::kExprI32GeS:
648 op = m->Int32LessThanOrEqual();
649 std::swap(left, right);
650 break;
651 case wasm::kExprI32GtU:
652 op = m->Uint32LessThan();
653 std::swap(left, right);
654 break;
655 case wasm::kExprI32GeU:
656 op = m->Uint32LessThanOrEqual();
657 std::swap(left, right);
658 break;
659 case wasm::kExprI64And:
660 op = m->Word64And();
661 break;
662 case wasm::kExprI64Add:
663 op = m->Int64Add();
664 break;
665 case wasm::kExprI64Sub:
666 op = m->Int64Sub();
667 break;
668 case wasm::kExprI64Mul:
669 op = m->Int64Mul();
670 break;
671 case wasm::kExprI64DivS:
672 return BuildI64DivS(left, right, position);
673 case wasm::kExprI64DivU:
674 return BuildI64DivU(left, right, position);
675 case wasm::kExprI64RemS:
676 return BuildI64RemS(left, right, position);
677 case wasm::kExprI64RemU:
678 return BuildI64RemU(left, right, position);
679 case wasm::kExprI64Ior:
680 op = m->Word64Or();
681 break;
682 case wasm::kExprI64Xor:
683 op = m->Word64Xor();
684 break;
685 case wasm::kExprI64Shl:
686 op = m->Word64Shl();
687 right = MaskShiftCount64(right);
688 break;
689 case wasm::kExprI64ShrU:
690 op = m->Word64Shr();
691 right = MaskShiftCount64(right);
692 break;
693 case wasm::kExprI64ShrS:
694 op = m->Word64Sar();
695 right = MaskShiftCount64(right);
696 break;
697 case wasm::kExprI64Eq:
698 op = m->Word64Equal();
699 break;
700 case wasm::kExprI64Ne:
701 return Invert(Binop(wasm::kExprI64Eq, left, right));
702 case wasm::kExprI64LtS:
703 op = m->Int64LessThan();
704 break;
705 case wasm::kExprI64LeS:
706 op = m->Int64LessThanOrEqual();
707 break;
708 case wasm::kExprI64LtU:
709 op = m->Uint64LessThan();
710 break;
711 case wasm::kExprI64LeU:
712 op = m->Uint64LessThanOrEqual();
713 break;
714 case wasm::kExprI64GtS:
715 op = m->Int64LessThan();
716 std::swap(left, right);
717 break;
718 case wasm::kExprI64GeS:
719 op = m->Int64LessThanOrEqual();
720 std::swap(left, right);
721 break;
722 case wasm::kExprI64GtU:
723 op = m->Uint64LessThan();
724 std::swap(left, right);
725 break;
726 case wasm::kExprI64GeU:
727 op = m->Uint64LessThanOrEqual();
728 std::swap(left, right);
729 break;
730 case wasm::kExprI64Ror:
731 right = MaskShiftCount64(right);
732 return m->Is64() ? graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Ror(), left, right)
733 : graph()->NewNode(m->Word64RorLowerable(), left, right,
734 control());
735 case wasm::kExprI64Rol:
736 if (m->Word64Rol().IsSupported()) {
737 return m->Is64() ? graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Rol().op(), left,
738 MaskShiftCount64(right))
739 : graph()->NewNode(m->Word64RolLowerable().op(), left,
740 MaskShiftCount64(right), control());
741 } else if (m->Word32Rol().IsSupported()) {
742 return graph()->NewNode(m->Word64RolLowerable().placeholder(), left,
743 right, control());
744 }
745 return BuildI64Rol(left, right);
746 case wasm::kExprF32CopySign:
747 return BuildF32CopySign(left, right);
748 case wasm::kExprF64CopySign:
749 return BuildF64CopySign(left, right);
750 case wasm::kExprF32Add:
751 op = m->Float32Add();
752 break;
753 case wasm::kExprF32Sub:
754 op = m->Float32Sub();
755 break;
756 case wasm::kExprF32Mul:
757 op = m->Float32Mul();
758 break;
759 case wasm::kExprF32Div:
760 op = m->Float32Div();
761 break;
762 case wasm::kExprF32Eq:
763 op = m->Float32Equal();
764 break;
765 case wasm::kExprF32Ne:
766 return Invert(Binop(wasm::kExprF32Eq, left, right));
767 case wasm::kExprF32Lt:
768 op = m->Float32LessThan();
769 break;
770 case wasm::kExprF32Ge:
771 op = m->Float32LessThanOrEqual();
772 std::swap(left, right);
773 break;
774 case wasm::kExprF32Gt:
775 op = m->Float32LessThan();
776 std::swap(left, right);
777 break;
778 case wasm::kExprF32Le:
779 op = m->Float32LessThanOrEqual();
780 break;
781 case wasm::kExprF64Add:
782 op = m->Float64Add();
783 break;
784 case wasm::kExprF64Sub:
785 op = m->Float64Sub();
786 break;
787 case wasm::kExprF64Mul:
788 op = m->Float64Mul();
789 break;
790 case wasm::kExprF64Div:
791 op = m->Float64Div();
792 break;
793 case wasm::kExprF64Eq:
794 op = m->Float64Equal();
795 break;
796 case wasm::kExprF64Ne:
797 return Invert(Binop(wasm::kExprF64Eq, left, right));
798 case wasm::kExprF64Lt:
799 op = m->Float64LessThan();
800 break;
801 case wasm::kExprF64Le:
802 op = m->Float64LessThanOrEqual();
803 break;
804 case wasm::kExprF64Gt:
805 op = m->Float64LessThan();
806 std::swap(left, right);
807 break;
808 case wasm::kExprF64Ge:
809 op = m->Float64LessThanOrEqual();
810 std::swap(left, right);
811 break;
812 case wasm::kExprF32Min:
813 op = m->Float32Min();
814 break;
815 case wasm::kExprF64Min:
816 op = m->Float64Min();
817 break;
818 case wasm::kExprF32Max:
819 op = m->Float32Max();
820 break;
821 case wasm::kExprF64Max:
822 op = m->Float64Max();
823 break;
824 case wasm::kExprF64Pow:
825 return BuildF64Pow(left, right);
826 case wasm::kExprF64Atan2:
827 op = m->Float64Atan2();
828 break;
829 case wasm::kExprF64Mod:
830 return BuildF64Mod(left, right);
831 case wasm::kExprRefEq:
832 return gasm_->TaggedEqual(left, right);
833 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsDivS:
834 return BuildI32AsmjsDivS(left, right);
835 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsDivU:
836 return BuildI32AsmjsDivU(left, right);
837 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsRemS:
838 return BuildI32AsmjsRemS(left, right);
839 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsRemU:
840 return BuildI32AsmjsRemU(left, right);
841 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsStoreMem8:
842 return BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType::Int8(), left, right);
843 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsStoreMem16:
844 return BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType::Int16(), left, right);
845 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsStoreMem:
846 return BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType::Int32(), left, right);
847 case wasm::kExprF32AsmjsStoreMem:
848 return BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType::Float32(), left, right);
849 case wasm::kExprF64AsmjsStoreMem:
850 return BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType::Float64(), left, right);
851 default:
852 FATAL_UNSUPPORTED_OPCODE(opcode);
853 }
854 return graph()->NewNode(op, left, right);
855}
856
857Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Unop(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode, Node* input,
858 wasm::ValueType type,
859 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
860 const Operator* op;
861 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
862 switch (opcode) {
863 case wasm::kExprI32Eqz:
864 return gasm_->Word32Equal(input, Int32Constant(0));
865 case wasm::kExprF32Abs:
866 op = m->Float32Abs();
867 break;
868 case wasm::kExprF32Neg: {
869 op = m->Float32Neg();
870 break;
871 }
872 case wasm::kExprF32Sqrt:
873 op = m->Float32Sqrt();
874 break;
875 case wasm::kExprF64Abs:
876 op = m->Float64Abs();
877 break;
878 case wasm::kExprF64Neg: {
879 op = m->Float64Neg();
880 break;
881 }
882 case wasm::kExprF64Sqrt:
883 op = m->Float64Sqrt();
884 break;
885 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF32:
886 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF32:
887 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF64:
888 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF64:
889 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
890 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
891 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
892 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
893 return BuildIntConvertFloat(input, position, opcode);
894 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsSConvertF64:
895 return BuildI32AsmjsSConvertF64(input);
896 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsUConvertF64:
897 return BuildI32AsmjsUConvertF64(input);
898 case wasm::kExprF32ConvertF64:
899 op = m->TruncateFloat64ToFloat32();
900 break;
901 case wasm::kExprF64SConvertI32:
902 op = m->ChangeInt32ToFloat64();
903 break;
904 case wasm::kExprF64UConvertI32:
905 op = m->ChangeUint32ToFloat64();
906 break;
907 case wasm::kExprF32SConvertI32:
908 op = m->RoundInt32ToFloat32();
909 break;
910 case wasm::kExprF32UConvertI32:
911 op = m->RoundUint32ToFloat32();
912 break;
913 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsSConvertF32:
914 return BuildI32AsmjsSConvertF32(input);
915 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsUConvertF32:
916 return BuildI32AsmjsUConvertF32(input);
917 case wasm::kExprF64ConvertF32:
918 op = m->ChangeFloat32ToFloat64();
919 break;
920 case wasm::kExprF32ReinterpretI32:
921 op = m->BitcastInt32ToFloat32();
922 break;
923 case wasm::kExprI32ReinterpretF32:
924 op = m->BitcastFloat32ToInt32();
925 break;
926 case wasm::kExprI32Clz:
927 op = m->Word32Clz();
928 break;
929 case wasm::kExprI32Ctz: {
930 if (m->Word32Ctz().IsSupported()) {
931 op = m->Word32Ctz().op();
932 break;
933 } else if (m->Word32ReverseBits().IsSupported()) {
934 Node* reversed = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32ReverseBits().op(), input);
935 Node* result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Clz(), reversed);
936 return result;
937 } else {
938 return BuildI32Ctz(input);
939 }
940 }
941 case wasm::kExprI32Popcnt: {
942 if (m->Word32Popcnt().IsSupported()) {
943 op = m->Word32Popcnt().op();
944 break;
945 } else {
946 return BuildI32Popcnt(input);
947 }
948 }
949 case wasm::kExprF32Floor: {
950 if (!m->Float32RoundDown().IsSupported()) return BuildF32Floor(input);
951 op = m->Float32RoundDown().op();
952 break;
953 }
954 case wasm::kExprF32Ceil: {
955 if (!m->Float32RoundUp().IsSupported()) return BuildF32Ceil(input);
956 op = m->Float32RoundUp().op();
957 break;
958 }
959 case wasm::kExprF32Trunc: {
960 if (!m->Float32RoundTruncate().IsSupported()) return BuildF32Trunc(input);
961 op = m->Float32RoundTruncate().op();
962 break;
963 }
964 case wasm::kExprF32NearestInt: {
965 if (!m->Float32RoundTiesEven().IsSupported())
966 return BuildF32NearestInt(input);
967 op = m->Float32RoundTiesEven().op();
968 break;
969 }
970 case wasm::kExprF64Floor: {
971 if (!m->Float64RoundDown().IsSupported()) return BuildF64Floor(input);
972 op = m->Float64RoundDown().op();
973 break;
974 }
975 case wasm::kExprF64Ceil: {
976 if (!m->Float64RoundUp().IsSupported()) return BuildF64Ceil(input);
977 op = m->Float64RoundUp().op();
978 break;
979 }
980 case wasm::kExprF64Trunc: {
981 if (!m->Float64RoundTruncate().IsSupported()) return BuildF64Trunc(input);
982 op = m->Float64RoundTruncate().op();
983 break;
984 }
985 case wasm::kExprF64NearestInt: {
986 if (!m->Float64RoundTiesEven().IsSupported())
987 return BuildF64NearestInt(input);
988 op = m->Float64RoundTiesEven().op();
989 break;
990 }
991 case wasm::kExprF64Acos: {
992 return BuildF64Acos(input);
993 }
994 case wasm::kExprF64Asin: {
995 return BuildF64Asin(input);
996 }
997 case wasm::kExprF64Atan:
998 op = m->Float64Atan();
999 break;
1000 case wasm::kExprF64Cos: {
1001 op = m->Float64Cos();
1002 break;
1003 }
1004 case wasm::kExprF64Sin: {
1005 op = m->Float64Sin();
1006 break;
1007 }
1008 case wasm::kExprF64Tan: {
1009 op = m->Float64Tan();
1010 break;
1011 }
1012 case wasm::kExprF64Exp: {
1013 op = m->Float64Exp();
1014 break;
1015 }
1016 case wasm::kExprF64Log:
1017 op = m->Float64Log();
1018 break;
1019 case wasm::kExprI32ConvertI64:
1020 op = m->TruncateInt64ToInt32();
1021 break;
1022 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertI32:
1023 op = m->ChangeInt32ToInt64();
1024 break;
1025 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertI32:
1026 op = m->ChangeUint32ToUint64();
1027 break;
1028 case wasm::kExprF64ReinterpretI64:
1029 op = m->BitcastInt64ToFloat64();
1030 break;
1031 case wasm::kExprI64ReinterpretF64:
1032 op = m->BitcastFloat64ToInt64();
1033 break;
1034 case wasm::kExprI64Clz:
1035 return m->Is64()
1036 ? graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Clz(), input)
1037 : graph()->NewNode(m->Word64ClzLowerable(), input, control());
1038 case wasm::kExprI64Ctz: {
1039 if (m->Word64Ctz().IsSupported()) {
1040 return m->Is64() ? graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Ctz().op(), input)
1041 : graph()->NewNode(m->Word64CtzLowerable().op(), input,
1042 control());
1043 } else if (m->Is32() && m->Word32Ctz().IsSupported()) {
1044 return graph()->NewNode(m->Word64CtzLowerable().placeholder(), input,
1045 control());
1046 } else if (m->Word64ReverseBits().IsSupported()) {
1047 Node* reversed = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64ReverseBits().op(), input);
1048 Node* result = m->Is64() ? graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Clz(), reversed)
1049 : graph()->NewNode(m->Word64ClzLowerable(),
1050 reversed, control());
1051 return result;
1052 } else {
1053 return BuildI64Ctz(input);
1054 }
1055 }
1056 case wasm::kExprI64Popcnt: {
1057 OptionalOperator popcnt64 = m->Word64Popcnt();
1058 if (popcnt64.IsSupported()) {
1059 op = popcnt64.op();
1060 } else if (m->Is32() && m->Word32Popcnt().IsSupported()) {
1061 op = popcnt64.placeholder();
1062 } else {
1063 return BuildI64Popcnt(input);
1064 }
1065 break;
1066 }
1067 case wasm::kExprI64Eqz:
1068 return gasm_->Word64Equal(input, Int64Constant(0));
1069 case wasm::kExprF32SConvertI64:
1070 if (m->Is32()) {
1071 return BuildF32SConvertI64(input);
1072 }
1073 op = m->RoundInt64ToFloat32();
1074 break;
1075 case wasm::kExprF32UConvertI64:
1076 if (m->Is32()) {
1077 return BuildF32UConvertI64(input);
1078 }
1079 op = m->RoundUint64ToFloat32();
1080 break;
1081 case wasm::kExprF64SConvertI64:
1082 if (m->Is32()) {
1083 return BuildF64SConvertI64(input);
1084 }
1085 op = m->RoundInt64ToFloat64();
1086 break;
1087 case wasm::kExprF64UConvertI64:
1088 if (m->Is32()) {
1089 return BuildF64UConvertI64(input);
1090 }
1091 op = m->RoundUint64ToFloat64();
1092 break;
1093 case wasm::kExprI32SExtendI8:
1094 op = m->SignExtendWord8ToInt32();
1095 break;
1096 case wasm::kExprI32SExtendI16:
1097 op = m->SignExtendWord16ToInt32();
1098 break;
1099 case wasm::kExprI64SExtendI8:
1100 op = m->SignExtendWord8ToInt64();
1101 break;
1102 case wasm::kExprI64SExtendI16:
1103 op = m->SignExtendWord16ToInt64();
1104 break;
1105 case wasm::kExprI64SExtendI32:
1106 op = m->SignExtendWord32ToInt64();
1107 break;
1108 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF32:
1109 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF32:
1110 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF64:
1111 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF64:
1112 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
1113 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
1114 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
1115 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
1116 return mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()
1117 ? BuildCcallConvertFloat(input, position, opcode)
1118 : BuildIntConvertFloat(input, position, opcode);
1119 case wasm::kExprRefIsNull:
1120 return IsNull(input, type);
1121 // We abuse ref.as_non_null, which isn't otherwise used in this switch, as
1122 // a sentinel for the negation of ref.is_null.
1123 case wasm::kExprRefAsNonNull:
1124 return gasm_->Word32Equal(gasm_->Int32Constant(0), IsNull(input, type));
1125 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem8S:
1126 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Int8(), input);
1127 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem8U:
1128 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Uint8(), input);
1129 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem16S:
1130 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Int16(), input);
1131 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem16U:
1132 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Uint16(), input);
1133 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem:
1134 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Int32(), input);
1135 case wasm::kExprF32AsmjsLoadMem:
1136 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Float32(), input);
1137 case wasm::kExprF64AsmjsLoadMem:
1138 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Float64(), input);
1139 case wasm::kExprAnyConvertExtern: {
1140 return gasm_->WasmAnyConvertExtern(input);
1141 }
1142 case wasm::kExprExternConvertAny:
1143 return gasm_->WasmExternConvertAny(input);
1144 default:
1145 FATAL_UNSUPPORTED_OPCODE(opcode);
1146 }
1147 return graph()->NewNode(op, input);
1148}
1149
1150Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Float32Constant(float value) {
1151 return mcgraph()->Float32Constant(value);
1152}
1153
1154Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Float64Constant(double value) {
1155 return mcgraph()->Float64Constant(value);
1156}
1157
1158Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Simd128Constant(const uint8_t value[16]) {
1159 has_simd_ = true;
1160 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->S128Const(value));
1161}
1162
1163std::tuple<Node*, Node*> WasmGraphBuilder::BranchNoHint(Node* cond) {
1164 Node* true_node;
1165 Node* false_node;
1166 gasm_->Branch(cond, &true_node, &false_node, BranchHint::kNone);
1167 return {true_node, false_node};
1168}
1169
1170std::tuple<Node*, Node*> WasmGraphBuilder::BranchExpectFalse(Node* cond) {
1171 Node* true_node;
1172 Node* false_node;
1173 gasm_->Branch(cond, &true_node, &false_node, BranchHint::kFalse);
1174 return {true_node, false_node};
1175}
1176
1177std::tuple<Node*, Node*> WasmGraphBuilder::BranchExpectTrue(Node* cond) {
1178 Node* true_node;
1179 Node* false_node;
1180 gasm_->Branch(cond, &true_node, &false_node, BranchHint::kTrue);
1181 return {true_node, false_node};
1182}
1183
1184Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Select(Node *cond, Node* true_node,
1185 Node* false_node, wasm::ValueType type) {
1186 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
1187 wasm::ValueKind kind = type.kind();
1188 // Lower to select if supported.
1189 if (kind == wasm::kF32 && m->Float32Select().IsSupported()) {
1190 return mcgraph()->graph()->NewNode(m->Float32Select().op(), cond,
1191 true_node, false_node);
1192 }
1193 if (kind == wasm::kF64 && m->Float64Select().IsSupported()) {
1194 return mcgraph()->graph()->NewNode(m->Float64Select().op(), cond,
1195 true_node, false_node);
1196 }
1197 if (kind == wasm::kI32 && m->Word32Select().IsSupported()) {
1198 return mcgraph()->graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Select().op(), cond, true_node,
1199 false_node);
1200 }
1201 if (kind == wasm::kI64 && m->Word64Select().IsSupported()) {
1202 return mcgraph()->graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Select().op(), cond, true_node,
1203 false_node);
1204 }
1205 // Default to control-flow.
1206
1207 auto [if_true, if_false] = BranchNoHint(cond);
1208 Node* merge = Merge(if_true, if_false);
1209 SetControl(merge);
1210 Node* inputs[] = {true_node, false_node, merge};
1211 return Phi(type, 2, inputs);
1212}
1213
1214// TODO(ahaas): Merge TrapId with TrapReason.
1215TrapId WasmGraphBuilder::GetTrapIdForTrap(wasm::TrapReason reason) {
1216 switch (reason) {
1217#define TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(name) \
1218 case wasm::k##name: \
1219 static_assert(static_cast<int>(TrapId::k##name) == \
1220 static_cast<int>(Builtin::kThrowWasm##name), \
1221 "trap id mismatch"); \
1222 return TrapId::k##name;
1223 FOREACH_WASM_TRAPREASON(TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID)
1224#undef TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID
1225 default:
1226 UNREACHABLE();
1227 }
1228}
1229
1230void WasmGraphBuilder::TrapIfTrue(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* cond,
1231 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1232 TrapId trap_id = GetTrapIdForTrap(reason);
1233 gasm_->TrapIf(cond, trap_id);
1234 SetSourcePosition(effect(), position);
1235}
1236
1237void WasmGraphBuilder::TrapIfFalse(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* cond,
1238 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1239 TrapId trap_id = GetTrapIdForTrap(reason);
1240 gasm_->TrapUnless(cond, trap_id);
1241 SetSourcePosition(effect(), position);
1242}
1243
1244Node* WasmGraphBuilder::AssertNotNull(Node* object, wasm::ValueType type,
1245 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
1246 wasm::TrapReason reason) {
1247 TrapId trap_id = GetTrapIdForTrap(reason);
1248 Node* result = gasm_->AssertNotNull(object, type, trap_id);
1249 SetSourcePosition(result, position);
1250 return result;
1251}
1252
1253// Add a check that traps if {node} is equal to {val}.
1254void WasmGraphBuilder::TrapIfEq32(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* node,
1255 int32_t val,
1256 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1257 if (val == 0) {
1258 TrapIfFalse(reason, node, position);
1259 } else {
1260 TrapIfTrue(reason, gasm_->Word32Equal(node, Int32Constant(val)), position);
1261 }
1262}
1263
1264// Add a check that traps if {node} is zero.
1265void WasmGraphBuilder::ZeroCheck32(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* node,
1266 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1267 TrapIfEq32(reason, node, 0, position);
1268}
1269
1270// Add a check that traps if {node} is equal to {val}.
1271void WasmGraphBuilder::TrapIfEq64(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* node,
1272 int64_t val,
1273 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1274 TrapIfTrue(reason, gasm_->Word64Equal(node, Int64Constant(val)), position);
1275}
1276
1277// Add a check that traps if {node} is zero.
1278void WasmGraphBuilder::ZeroCheck64(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* node,
1279 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1280 TrapIfEq64(reason, node, 0, position);
1281}
1282
1283Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Switch(unsigned count, Node* key) {
1284 // The instruction selector will use {kArchTableSwitch} for large switches,
1285 // which has limited input count, see {InstructionSelector::EmitTableSwitch}.
1286 DCHECK_LE(count, Instruction::kMaxInputCount - 2); // value_range + 2
1287 DCHECK_LE(count, wasm::kV8MaxWasmFunctionBrTableSize + 1); // plus IfDefault
1288 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Switch(count), key, control());
1289}
1290
1291Node* WasmGraphBuilder::IfValue(int32_t value, Node* sw) {
1292 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kSwitch, sw->opcode());
1293 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfValue(value), sw);
1294}
1295
1296Node* WasmGraphBuilder::IfDefault(Node* sw) {
1297 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kSwitch, sw->opcode());
1298 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfDefault(), sw);
1299}
1300
1301Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Return(base::Vector<Node*> vals) {
1302 unsigned count = static_cast<unsigned>(vals.size());
1303 base::SmallVector<Node*, 8> buf(count + 3);
1304
1305 // TODOC: What is the meaning of the 0-constant?
1306 buf[0] = Int32Constant(0);
1307 if (count > 0) {
1308 memcpy(buf.data() + 1, vals.begin(), sizeof(void*) * count);
1309 }
1310 buf[count + 1] = effect();
1311 buf[count + 2] = control();
1312 Node* ret = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Return(count), count + 3,
1313 buf.data());
1314
1315 gasm_->MergeControlToEnd(ret);
1316 return ret;
1317}
1318
1319void WasmGraphBuilder::Trap(wasm::TrapReason reason,
1320 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1321 TrapIfFalse(reason, Int32Constant(0), position);
1322 // Connect control to end via a Throw() node.
1323 TerminateThrow(effect(), control());
1324}
1325
1326Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MaskShiftCount32(Node* node) {
1327 static const int32_t kMask32 = 0x1F;
1328 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Word32ShiftIsSafe()) {
1329 // Shifts by constants are so common we pattern-match them here.
1330 Int32Matcher match(node);
1331 if (match.HasResolvedValue()) {
1332 int32_t masked = (match.ResolvedValue() & kMask32);
1333 if (match.ResolvedValue() != masked) node = Int32Constant(masked);
1334 } else {
1335 node = gasm_->Word32And(node, Int32Constant(kMask32));
1336 }
1337 }
1338 return node;
1339}
1340
1341Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MaskShiftCount64(Node* node) {
1342 static const int64_t kMask64 = 0x3F;
1343 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Word32ShiftIsSafe()) {
1344 // Shifts by constants are so common we pattern-match them here.
1345 Int64Matcher match(node);
1346 if (match.HasResolvedValue()) {
1347 int64_t masked = (match.ResolvedValue() & kMask64);
1348 if (match.ResolvedValue() != masked) node = Int64Constant(masked);
1349 } else {
1350 node = gasm_->Word64And(node, Int64Constant(kMask64));
1351 }
1352 }
1353 return node;
1354}

1356namespace {
1357
1358bool ReverseBytesSupported(MachineOperatorBuilder* m, size_t size_in_bytes) {
1359 switch (size_in_bytes) {
1360 case 4:
1361 case 16:
1362 return true;
1363 case 8:
1364 return m->Is64();
1365 default:
1366 break;
1367 }
1368 return false;
1369}
1370
1371} // namespace
1372
1373Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildChangeEndiannessStore(
1374 Node* node, MachineRepresentation mem_rep, wasm::ValueType wasmtype) {
1375 Node* result;
1376 Node* value = node;
1377 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
1378 int valueSizeInBytes = wasmtype.value_kind_size();
1379 int valueSizeInBits = 8 * valueSizeInBytes;
1380 bool isFloat = false;
1381
1382 switch (wasmtype.kind()) {
1383 case wasm::kF64:
1384 value = gasm_->BitcastFloat64ToInt64(node);
1385 isFloat = true;
1386 [[fallthrough]];
1387 case wasm::kI64:
1388 result = Int64Constant(0);
1389 break;
1390 case wasm::kF32:
1391 value = gasm_->BitcastFloat32ToInt32(node);
1392 isFloat = true;
1393 [[fallthrough]];
1394 case wasm::kI32:
1395 result = Int32Constant(0);
1396 break;
1397 case wasm::kS128:
1398 DCHECK(ReverseBytesSupported(m, valueSizeInBytes));
1399 break;
1400 default:
1401 UNREACHABLE();
1402 }
1403
1404 if (mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8) {
1405 // No need to change endianness for byte size, return original node
1406 return node;
1407 }
1408 if (wasmtype == wasm::kWasmI64 && mem_rep < MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1409 // In case we store lower part of WasmI64 expression, we can truncate
1410 // upper 32bits
1411 value = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(value);
1412 valueSizeInBytes = wasm::kWasmI32.value_kind_size();
1413 valueSizeInBits = 8 * valueSizeInBytes;
1414 if (mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16) {
1415 value = gasm_->Word32Shl(value, Int32Constant(16));
1416 }
1417 } else if (wasmtype == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
1418 mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16) {
1419 value = gasm_->Word32Shl(value, Int32Constant(16));
1420 }
1421
1422 int i;
1423 uint32_t shiftCount;
1424
1425 if (ReverseBytesSupported(m, valueSizeInBytes)) {
1426 switch (valueSizeInBytes) {
1427 case 4:
1428 result = gasm_->Word32ReverseBytes(value);
1429 break;
1430 case 8:
1431 result = gasm_->Word64ReverseBytes(value);
1432 break;
1433 case 16:
1434 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Simd128ReverseBytes(), value);
1435 break;
1436 default:
1437 UNREACHABLE();
1438 }
1439 } else {
1440 for (i = 0, shiftCount = valueSizeInBits - 8; i < valueSizeInBits / 2;
1441 i += 8, shiftCount -= 16) {
1442 Node* shiftLower;
1443 Node* shiftHigher;
1444 Node* lowerByte;
1445 Node* higherByte;
1446
1447 DCHECK_LT(0, shiftCount);
1448 DCHECK_EQ(0, (shiftCount + 8) % 16);
1449
1450 if (valueSizeInBits > 32) {
1451 shiftLower = gasm_->Word64Shl(value, Int64Constant(shiftCount));
1452 shiftHigher = gasm_->Word64Shr(value, Int64Constant(shiftCount));
1453 lowerByte = gasm_->Word64And(
1454 shiftLower, Int64Constant(static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF)
1455 << (valueSizeInBits - 8 - i)));
1456 higherByte = gasm_->Word64And(
1457 shiftHigher, Int64Constant(static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF) << i));
1458 result = gasm_->Word64Or(result, lowerByte);
1459 result = gasm_->Word64Or(result, higherByte);
1460 } else {
1461 shiftLower = gasm_->Word32Shl(value, Int32Constant(shiftCount));
1462 shiftHigher = gasm_->Word32Shr(value, Int32Constant(shiftCount));
1463 lowerByte = gasm_->Word32And(
1464 shiftLower, Int32Constant(static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF)
1465 << (valueSizeInBits - 8 - i)));
1466 higherByte = gasm_->Word32And(
1467 shiftHigher, Int32Constant(static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF) << i));
1468 result = gasm_->Word32Or(result, lowerByte);
1469 result = gasm_->Word32Or(result, higherByte);
1470 }
1471 }
1472 }
1473
1474 if (isFloat) {
1475 switch (wasmtype.kind()) {
1476 case wasm::kF64:
1477 result = gasm_->BitcastInt64ToFloat64(result);
1478 break;
1479 case wasm::kF32:
1480 result = gasm_->BitcastInt32ToFloat32(result);
1481 break;
1482 default:
1483 UNREACHABLE();
1484 }
1485 }
1486
1487 return result;
1488}
1489
1490Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildChangeEndiannessLoad(Node* node,
1491 MachineType memtype,
1492 wasm::ValueType wasmtype) {
1493 Node* result;
1494 Node* value = node;
1495 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
1496 int valueSizeInBytes = ElementSizeInBytes(memtype.representation());
1497 int valueSizeInBits = 8 * valueSizeInBytes;
1498 bool isFloat = false;
1499
1500 switch (memtype.representation()) {
1501 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1502 value = gasm_->BitcastFloat64ToInt64(node);
1503 isFloat = true;
1504 [[fallthrough]];
1505 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
1506 result = Int64Constant(0);
1507 break;
1508 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1509 value = gasm_->BitcastFloat32ToInt32(node);
1510 isFloat = true;
1511 [[fallthrough]];
1512 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
1513 case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
1514 result = Int32Constant(0);
1515 break;
1516 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
1517 // No need to change endianness for byte size, return original node
1518 return node;
1519 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1520 DCHECK(ReverseBytesSupported(m, valueSizeInBytes));
1521 break;
1522 default:
1523 UNREACHABLE();
1524 }
1525
1526 int i;
1527 uint32_t shiftCount;
1528
1529 if (ReverseBytesSupported(m, valueSizeInBytes < 4 ? 4 : valueSizeInBytes)) {
1530 switch (valueSizeInBytes) {
1531 case 2:
1532 result = gasm_->Word32ReverseBytes(
1533 gasm_->Word32Shl(value, Int32Constant(16)));
1534 break;
1535 case 4:
1536 result = gasm_->Word32ReverseBytes(value);
1537 break;
1538 case 8:
1539 result = gasm_->Word64ReverseBytes(value);
1540 break;
1541 case 16:
1542 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Simd128ReverseBytes(), value);
1543 break;
1544 default:
1545 UNREACHABLE();
1546 }
1547 } else {
1548 for (i = 0, shiftCount = valueSizeInBits - 8; i < valueSizeInBits / 2;
1549 i += 8, shiftCount -= 16) {
1550 Node* shiftLower;
1551 Node* shiftHigher;
1552 Node* lowerByte;
1553 Node* higherByte;
1554
1555 DCHECK_LT(0, shiftCount);
1556 DCHECK_EQ(0, (shiftCount + 8) % 16);
1557
1558 if (valueSizeInBits > 32) {
1559 shiftLower = gasm_->Word64Shl(value, Int64Constant(shiftCount));
1560 shiftHigher = gasm_->Word64Shr(value, Int64Constant(shiftCount));
1561 lowerByte = gasm_->Word64And(
1562 shiftLower, Int64Constant(static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF)
1563 << (valueSizeInBits - 8 - i)));
1564 higherByte = gasm_->Word64And(
1565 shiftHigher, Int64Constant(static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF) << i));
1566 result = gasm_->Word64Or(result, lowerByte);
1567 result = gasm_->Word64Or(result, higherByte);
1568 } else {
1569 shiftLower = gasm_->Word32Shl(value, Int32Constant(shiftCount));
1570 shiftHigher = gasm_->Word32Shr(value, Int32Constant(shiftCount));
1571 lowerByte = gasm_->Word32And(
1572 shiftLower, Int32Constant(static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF)
1573 << (valueSizeInBits - 8 - i)));
1574 higherByte = gasm_->Word32And(
1575 shiftHigher, Int32Constant(static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF) << i));
1576 result = gasm_->Word32Or(result, lowerByte);
1577 result = gasm_->Word32Or(result, higherByte);
1578 }
1579 }
1580 }
1581
1582 if (isFloat) {
1583 switch (memtype.representation()) {
1584 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1585 result = gasm_->BitcastInt64ToFloat64(result);
1586 break;
1587 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1588 result = gasm_->BitcastInt32ToFloat32(result);
1589 break;
1590 default:
1591 UNREACHABLE();
1592 }
1593 }
1594
1595 // We need to sign or zero extend the value
1596 if (memtype.IsSigned()) {
1597 DCHECK(!isFloat);
1598 if (valueSizeInBits < 32) {
1599 Node* shiftBitCount;
1600 // Perform sign extension using following trick
1601 // result = (x << machine_width - type_width) >> (machine_width -
1602 // type_width)
1603 if (wasmtype == wasm::kWasmI64) {
1604 shiftBitCount = Int32Constant(64 - valueSizeInBits);
1605 result = gasm_->Word64Sar(
1606 gasm_->Word64Shl(gasm_->ChangeInt32ToInt64(result), shiftBitCount),
1607 shiftBitCount);
1608 } else if (wasmtype == wasm::kWasmI32) {
1609 shiftBitCount = Int32Constant(32 - valueSizeInBits);
1610 result = gasm_->Word32Sar(gasm_->Word32Shl(result, shiftBitCount),
1611 shiftBitCount);
1612 }
1613 }
1614 } else if (wasmtype == wasm::kWasmI64 && valueSizeInBits < 64) {
1615 result = gasm_->ChangeUint32ToUint64(result);
1616 }
1617
1618 return result;
1619}
1620
1621Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildF32CopySign(Node* left, Node* right) {
1622 Node* result = Unop(
1623 wasm::kExprF32ReinterpretI32,
1624 Binop(wasm::kExprI32Ior,
1625 Binop(wasm::kExprI32And, Unop(wasm::kExprI32ReinterpretF32, left),
1626 Int32Constant(0x7FFFFFFF)),
1627 Binop(wasm::kExprI32And, Unop(wasm::kExprI32ReinterpretF32, right),
1628 Int32Constant(0x80000000))));
1629
1630 return result;
1631}
1632
1633Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildF64CopySign(Node* left, Node* right) {
1634 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is64()) {
1635 return gasm_->BitcastInt64ToFloat64(
1636 gasm_->Word64Or(gasm_->Word64And(gasm_->BitcastFloat64ToInt64(left),
1637 Int64Constant(0x7FFFFFFFFFFFFFFF)),
1638 gasm_->Word64And(gasm_->BitcastFloat64ToInt64(right),
1639 Int64Constant(0x8000000000000000))));
1640 }
1641
1642 DCHECK(mcgraph()->machine()->Is32());
1643
1644 Node* high_word_left = gasm_->Float64ExtractHighWord32(left);
1645 Node* high_word_right = gasm_->Float64ExtractHighWord32(right);
1646
1647 Node* new_high_word = gasm_->Word32Or(
1648 gasm_->Word32And(high_word_left, Int32Constant(0x7FFFFFFF)),
1649 gasm_->Word32And(high_word_right, Int32Constant(0x80000000)));
1650
1651 return gasm_->Float64InsertHighWord32(left, new_high_word);
1652}

1656MachineType IntConvertType(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
1657 switch (opcode) {
1658 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF32:
1659 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF64:
1660 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
1661 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
1662 return MachineType::Int32();
1663 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF32:
1664 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF64:
1665 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
1666 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
1667 return MachineType::Uint32();
1668 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF32:
1669 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF64:
1670 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
1671 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
1672 return MachineType::Int64();
1673 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF32:
1674 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF64:
1675 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
1676 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
1677 return MachineType::Uint64();
1678 default:
1679 UNREACHABLE();
1680 }

1686 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF32:

1688 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF32:

1708const Operator* ConvertOp(WasmGraphBuilder* builder, wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
1709 switch (opcode) {
1710 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF32:
1711 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateFloat32ToInt32(
1712 TruncateKind::kSetOverflowToMin);
1713 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
1714 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateFloat32ToInt32(
1715 TruncateKind::kArchitectureDefault);
1716 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF32:
1717 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateFloat32ToUint32(
1718 TruncateKind::kSetOverflowToMin);
1719 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
1720 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateFloat32ToUint32(
1721 TruncateKind::kArchitectureDefault);
1722 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF64:
1723 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
1724 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->ChangeFloat64ToInt32();
1725 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF64:
1726 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
1727 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateFloat64ToUint32();
1728 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF32:
1729 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
1730 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TryTruncateFloat32ToInt64();
1731 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF32:
1732 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
1733 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TryTruncateFloat32ToUint64();
1734 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF64:
1735 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
1736 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TryTruncateFloat64ToInt64();
1737 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF64:
1738 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
1739 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TryTruncateFloat64ToUint64();
1740 default:
1741 UNREACHABLE();
1742 }
1743}

1789Node* Zero(WasmGraphBuilder* builder, const MachineType& ty) {
1790 switch (ty.representation()) {
1791 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
1792 return builder->Int32Constant(0);
1793 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
1794 return builder->Int64Constant(0);
1795 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1796 return builder->Float32Constant(0.0);
1797 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1798 return builder->Float64Constant(0.0);
1799 default:
1800 UNREACHABLE();
1801 }
1802}

1806 case MachineSemantic::kInt32:
1807 return builder->Int32Constant(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min());
1808 case MachineSemantic::kUint32:
1809 return builder->Int32Constant(std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::min());
1810 case MachineSemantic::kInt64:
1811 return builder->Int64Constant(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min());
1812 case MachineSemantic::kUint64:
1813 return builder->Int64Constant(std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::min());
1814 default:
1815 UNREACHABLE();
1816 }
1817}

1823 case MachineSemantic::kUint32:
1824 return builder->Int32Constant(std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
1825 case MachineSemantic::kInt64:
1826 return builder->Int64Constant(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max());
1827 case MachineSemantic::kUint64:

1844
1845wasm::WasmOpcode NeOp(const MachineType& ty) {
1846 switch (ty.representation()) {
1847 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1848 return wasm::kExprF32Ne;
1849 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1850 return wasm::kExprF64Ne;
1851 default:
1852 UNREACHABLE();
1853 }
1854}
1855
1856wasm::WasmOpcode LtOp(const MachineType& ty) {
1857 switch (ty.representation()) {
1858 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1859 return wasm::kExprF32Lt;
1860 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1861 return wasm::kExprF64Lt;
1862 default:
1863 UNREACHABLE();
1864 }
1865}
1866
1867Node* ConvertTrapTest(WasmGraphBuilder* builder, wasm::WasmOpcode opcode,
1868 const MachineType& int_ty, const MachineType& float_ty,
1869 Node* trunc, Node* converted_value) {
1870 if (int_ty.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
1871 Node* check = builder->Unop(ConvertBackOp(opcode), converted_value);
1872 return builder->Binop(NeOp(float_ty), trunc, check);
1873 }
1874 return builder->graph()->NewNode(builder->mcgraph()->common()->Projection(1),
1875 trunc, builder->graph()->start());
1876}
1877
1878Node* ConvertSaturateTest(WasmGraphBuilder* builder, wasm::WasmOpcode opcode,
1879 const MachineType& int_ty,
1880 const MachineType& float_ty, Node* trunc,
1881 Node* converted_value) {
1882 Node* test = ConvertTrapTest(builder, opcode, int_ty, float_ty, trunc,
1883 converted_value);
1884 if (int_ty.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1885 test = builder->Binop(wasm::kExprI64Eq, test, builder->Int64Constant(0));
1886 }
1887 return test;
1888}
1889
1890} // namespace
1891
1892Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildIntConvertFloat(Node* input,
1893 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
1894 wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
1895 const MachineType int_ty = IntConvertType(opcode);
1896 const MachineType float_ty = FloatConvertType(opcode);
1897 const Operator* conv_op = ConvertOp(this, opcode);
1898 Node* trunc = nullptr;
1899 Node* converted_value = nullptr;
1900 const bool is_int32 =
1901 int_ty.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord32;
1902 if (is_int32) {
1903 trunc = Unop(TruncOp(float_ty), input);
1904 converted_value = graph()->NewNode(conv_op, trunc);
1905 } else {
1906 trunc = graph()->NewNode(conv_op, input);
1907 converted_value = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Projection(0),
1908 trunc, graph()->start());
1909 }
1910 if (IsTrappingConvertOp(opcode)) {
1911 Node* test =
1912 ConvertTrapTest(this, opcode, int_ty, float_ty, trunc, converted_value);
1913 if (is_int32) {
1914 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapFloatUnrepresentable, test, position);
1915 } else {
1916 ZeroCheck64(wasm::kTrapFloatUnrepresentable, test, position);
1917 }
1918 return converted_value;
1919 }
1920 if (mcgraph()->machine()->SatConversionIsSafe()) {
1921 return converted_value;
1922 }
1923 Node* test = ConvertSaturateTest(this, opcode, int_ty, float_ty, trunc,
1924 converted_value);
1925 Diamond tl_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), test, BranchHint::kFalse);
1926 tl_d.Chain(control());
1927 Node* nan_test = Binop(NeOp(float_ty), input, input);
1928 Diamond nan_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), nan_test, BranchHint::kFalse);
1929 nan_d.Nest(tl_d, true);
1930 Node* neg_test = Binop(LtOp(float_ty), input, Zero(this, float_ty));
1931 Diamond sat_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), neg_test, BranchHint::kNone);
1932 sat_d.Nest(nan_d, false);
1933 Node* sat_val =
1934 sat_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), Min(this, int_ty), Max(this, int_ty));
1935 Node* nan_val =
1936 nan_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), Zero(this, int_ty), sat_val);
1937 SetControl(tl_d.merge);
1938 return tl_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), nan_val, converted_value);
1939}

1961Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildBitCountingCall(Node* input, ExternalReference ref,
1962 MachineRepresentation input_type) {
1963 auto sig = FixedSizeSignature<MachineType>::Returns(MachineType::Int32())
1964 .Params(MachineType::TypeForRepresentation(input_type, false));
1965 return BuildCCall(&sig, gasm_->ExternalConstant(ref), input);
1966}
1967
1968Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32Ctz(Node* input) {
1969 return BuildBitCountingCall(input, ExternalReference::wasm_word32_ctz(),
1970 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1971}
1972
1973Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64Ctz(Node* input) {
1974 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()) {
1975 Node* upper_word = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(
1976 Binop(wasm::kExprI64ShrU, input, Int64Constant(32)));
1977 Node* lower_word = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(input);
1978 // return lower_word == 0 ? 32 + CTZ32(upper_word) : CTZ32(lower_word);
1979 // Build control flow because Word32Select is not always available.
1980 Diamond d{graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
1981 gasm_->Word32Equal(lower_word, gasm_->Uint32Constant(0))};
1982 d.Chain(control());
1983 Node* original_effect = gasm_->effect();
1984 // Build the path that uses the upper word.
1985 SetControl(d.if_true);
1986 Node* result_from_upper = gasm_->Int32Add(
1987 BuildBitCountingCall(upper_word, ExternalReference::wasm_word32_ctz(),
1988 MachineRepresentation::kWord32),
1989 gasm_->Int32Constant(32));
1990 Node* effect_after_upper = gasm_->effect();
1991 // Build the path that uses the lower word.
1992 SetEffectControl(original_effect, d.if_false);
1993 Node* result_from_lower =
1994 BuildBitCountingCall(lower_word, ExternalReference::wasm_word32_ctz(),
1995 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1996 Node* effect_after_lower = gasm_->effect();
1997 // Merge the two paths.
1998 Node* ephi = d.EffectPhi(effect_after_upper, effect_after_lower);
1999 SetEffectControl(ephi, d.merge);
2000 Node* result_32 = d.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, result_from_upper,
2001 result_from_lower);
2002 return gasm_->ChangeUint32ToUint64(result_32);
2003 }
2004 return gasm_->ChangeUint32ToUint64(
2005 BuildBitCountingCall(input, ExternalReference::wasm_word64_ctz(),
2006 MachineRepresentation::kWord64));
2007}
2008
2009Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32Popcnt(Node* input) {
2010 return BuildBitCountingCall(input, ExternalReference::wasm_word32_popcnt(),
2011 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2012}
2013
2014Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64Popcnt(Node* input) {
2015 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()) {
2016 // Emit two calls to wasm_word32_popcnt.
2017 Node* upper_word = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(
2018 Binop(wasm::kExprI64ShrU, input, Int64Constant(32)));
2019 Node* lower_word = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(input);
2020 return gasm_->ChangeUint32ToUint64(gasm_->Int32Add(
2021 BuildBitCountingCall(lower_word,
2022 ExternalReference::wasm_word32_popcnt(),
2023 MachineRepresentation::kWord32),
2024 BuildBitCountingCall(upper_word,
2025 ExternalReference::wasm_word32_popcnt(),
2026 MachineRepresentation::kWord32)));
2027 }
2028 return gasm_->ChangeUint32ToUint64(
2029 BuildBitCountingCall(input, ExternalReference::wasm_word64_popcnt(),
2030 MachineRepresentation::kWord64));
2031}

2105
2106Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCFuncInstruction(ExternalReference ref,
2107 MachineType type, Node* input0,
2108 Node* input1) {
2109 // We do truncation by calling a C function which calculates the result.
2110 // The input is passed to the C function as a byte buffer holding the two
2111 // input doubles. We reserve this byte buffer as a stack slot, store the
2112 // parameters in this buffer slots, pass a pointer to the buffer to the C
2113 // function, and after calling the C function we collect the return value from
2114 // the buffer.
2115 Node* stack_slot;
2116 if (input1) {
2117 stack_slot = StoreArgsInStackSlot(
2118 {{type.representation(), input0}, {type.representation(), input1}});
2119 } else {
2120 stack_slot = StoreArgsInStackSlot({{type.representation(), input0}});
2121 }
2122
2123 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Pointer()};
2124 MachineSignature sig(0, 1, sig_types);
2125 Node* function = gasm_->ExternalConstant(ref);
2126 BuildCCall(&sig, function, stack_slot);
2127
2128 return gasm_->LoadFromObject(type, stack_slot, 0);
2129}
2130
2131Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildF32SConvertI64(Node* input) {
2132 // TODO(titzer/bradnelson): Check handlng of asm.js case.
2133 return BuildIntToFloatConversionInstruction(
2134 input, ExternalReference::wasm_int64_to_float32(),
2135 MachineRepresentation::kWord64, MachineType::Float32());
2136}
2137Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildF32UConvertI64(Node* input) {

2139 return BuildIntToFloatConversionInstruction(
2140 input, ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_to_float32(),
2141 MachineRepresentation::kWord64, MachineType::Float32());
2142}

2152}
2153
2154Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildIntToFloatConversionInstruction(
2155 Node* input, ExternalReference ref,
2156 MachineRepresentation parameter_representation,
2157 const MachineType result_type) {
2158 int stack_slot_size =
2159 std::max(ElementSizeInBytes(parameter_representation),
2160 ElementSizeInBytes(result_type.representation()));
2161 Node* stack_slot =
2162 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->StackSlot(stack_slot_size));
2163 auto store_rep =
2164 StoreRepresentation(parameter_representation, kNoWriteBarrier);
2165 gasm_->Store(store_rep, stack_slot, 0, input);
2166 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Pointer()};
2167 MachineSignature sig(0, 1, sig_types);
2168 Node* function = gasm_->ExternalConstant(ref);
2169 BuildCCall(&sig, function, stack_slot);
2170 return gasm_->LoadFromObject(result_type, stack_slot, 0);
2171}

2173namespace {
2174
2175ExternalReference convert_ccall_ref(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
2176 switch (opcode) {
2177 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF32:
2178 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
2179 return ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_int64();
2180 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF32:
2181 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
2182 return ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_uint64();
2183 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF64:
2184 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
2185 return ExternalReference::wasm_float64_to_int64();
2186 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF64:
2187 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
2188 return ExternalReference::wasm_float64_to_uint64();
2189 default:
2190 UNREACHABLE();
2191 }
2192}
2193
2194} // namespace
2195
2196Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCcallConvertFloat(Node* input,
2197 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2198 wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
2199 const MachineType int_ty = IntConvertType(opcode);
2200 const MachineType float_ty = FloatConvertType(opcode);
2201 ExternalReference call_ref = convert_ccall_ref(opcode);
2202 int stack_slot_size = std::max(ElementSizeInBytes(int_ty.representation()),
2203 ElementSizeInBytes(float_ty.representation()));
2204 Node* stack_slot =
2205 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->StackSlot(stack_slot_size));
2206 auto store_rep =
2207 StoreRepresentation(float_ty.representation(), kNoWriteBarrier);
2208 gasm_->Store(store_rep, stack_slot, 0, input);
2209 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Int32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
2210 MachineSignature sig(1, 1, sig_types);
2211 Node* function = gasm_->ExternalConstant(call_ref);
2212 Node* overflow = BuildCCall(&sig, function, stack_slot);
2213 if (IsTrappingConvertOp(opcode)) {
2214 ZeroCheck32(wasm::kTrapFloatUnrepresentable, overflow, position);
2215 return gasm_->LoadFromObject(int_ty, stack_slot, 0);
2216 }
2217 Node* test = Binop(wasm::kExprI32Eq, overflow, Int32Constant(0), position);
2218 Diamond tl_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), test, BranchHint::kFalse);
2219 tl_d.Chain(control());
2220 Node* nan_test = Binop(NeOp(float_ty), input, input);
2221 Diamond nan_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), nan_test, BranchHint::kFalse);
2222 nan_d.Nest(tl_d, true);
2223 Node* neg_test = Binop(LtOp(float_ty), input, Zero(this, float_ty));
2224 Diamond sat_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), neg_test, BranchHint::kNone);
2225 sat_d.Nest(nan_d, false);
2226 Node* sat_val =
2227 sat_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), Min(this, int_ty), Max(this, int_ty));
2228 Node* load = gasm_->LoadFromObject(int_ty, stack_slot, 0);
2229 Node* nan_val =
2230 nan_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), Zero(this, int_ty), sat_val);
2231 return tl_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), nan_val, load);
2232}
2233
2234Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MemoryGrow(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory,
2235 Node* input) {
2236 needs_stack_check_ = true;
2237 if (!memory->is_memory64()) {
2238 // For 32-bit memories, just call the builtin.
2239 return gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
2240 Builtin::kWasmMemoryGrow, Operator::kNoThrow,
2241 gasm_->Int32Constant(memory->index), input);
2242 }
2243
2244 // If the input is not a positive int32, growing will always fail
2245 // (growing negative or requesting >= 256 TB).
2246 Node* old_effect = effect();
2247 Diamond is_32_bit(graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2248 gasm_->Uint64LessThanOrEqual(input, Int64Constant(kMaxInt)),
2249 BranchHint::kTrue);
2250 is_32_bit.Chain(control());
2251
2252 SetControl(is_32_bit.if_true);
2253
2254 Node* grow_result =
2255 gasm_->ChangeInt32ToInt64(gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
2256 Builtin::kWasmMemoryGrow, Operator::kNoThrow,
2257 gasm_->Int32Constant(memory->index),
2258 gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(input)));
2259
2260 Node* diamond_result = is_32_bit.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord64,
2261 grow_result, gasm_->Int64Constant(-1));
2262 SetEffectControl(is_32_bit.EffectPhi(effect(), old_effect), is_32_bit.merge);
2263 return diamond_result;
2264}
2265
2266Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Throw(uint32_t tag_index, const wasm::WasmTag* tag,
2267 const base::Vector<Node*> values,
2268 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2269 needs_stack_check_ = true;
2270 uint32_t encoded_size = WasmExceptionPackage::GetEncodedSize(tag);
2271
2272 Node* values_array = gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
2273 Builtin::kWasmAllocateFixedArray, Operator::kNoThrow,
2274 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(encoded_size));
2275 SetSourcePosition(values_array, position);
2276
2277 uint32_t index = 0;
2278 const wasm::WasmTagSig* sig = tag->sig;
2279 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2280 for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); ++i) {
2281 Node* value = values[i];
2282 switch (sig->GetParam(i).kind()) {
2283 case wasm::kF32:
2284 value = gasm_->BitcastFloat32ToInt32(value);
2285 [[fallthrough]];
2286 case wasm::kI32:
2287 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index, value);
2288 break;
2289 case wasm::kF64:
2290 value = gasm_->BitcastFloat64ToInt64(value);
2291 [[fallthrough]];
2292 case wasm::kI64: {
2293 Node* upper32 = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(
2294 Binop(wasm::kExprI64ShrU, value, Int64Constant(32)));
2295 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index, upper32);
2296 Node* lower32 = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(value);
2297 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index, lower32);
2298 break;
2299 }
2300 case wasm::kS128:
2301 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(
2302 values_array, &index,
2303 graph()->NewNode(m->I32x4ExtractLane(0), value));
2304 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(
2305 values_array, &index,
2306 graph()->NewNode(m->I32x4ExtractLane(1), value));
2307 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(
2308 values_array, &index,
2309 graph()->NewNode(m->I32x4ExtractLane(2), value));
2310 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(
2311 values_array, &index,
2312 graph()->NewNode(m->I32x4ExtractLane(3), value));
2313 break;
2314 case wasm::kRef:
2315 case wasm::kRefNull:
2316 case wasm::kRtt:
2317 gasm_->StoreFixedArrayElementAny(values_array, index, value);
2318 ++index;
2319 break;
2320 case wasm::kI8:
2321 case wasm::kI16:
2322 case wasm::kF16:
2323 case wasm::kVoid:
2324 case wasm::kTop:
2325 case wasm::kBottom:
2326 UNREACHABLE();
2327 }
2328 }
2329 DCHECK_EQ(encoded_size, index);
2330
2331 Node* exception_tag = LoadTagFromTable(tag_index);
2332
2333 Node* throw_call = gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
2334 Builtin::kWasmThrow, Operator::kNoProperties, exception_tag,
2335 values_array);
2336 SetSourcePosition(throw_call, position);
2337 return throw_call;
2338}
2339
2340void WasmGraphBuilder::BuildEncodeException32BitValue(Node* values_array,
2341 uint32_t* index,
2342 Node* value) {
2343 Node* upper_halfword_as_smi =
2344 gasm_->BuildChangeUint31ToSmi(gasm_->Word32Shr(value, Int32Constant(16)));
2345 gasm_->StoreFixedArrayElementSmi(values_array, *index, upper_halfword_as_smi);
2346 ++(*index);
2347 Node* lower_halfword_as_smi = gasm_->BuildChangeUint31ToSmi(
2348 gasm_->Word32And(value, Int32Constant(0xFFFFu)));
2349 gasm_->StoreFixedArrayElementSmi(values_array, *index, lower_halfword_as_smi);
2350 ++(*index);
2351}
2352
2353Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildDecodeException32BitValue(Node* values_array,
2354 uint32_t* index) {
2355 Node* upper = gasm_->BuildChangeSmiToInt32(
2356 gasm_->LoadFixedArrayElementSmi(values_array, *index));
2357 (*index)++;
2358 upper = gasm_->Word32Shl(upper, Int32Constant(16));
2359 Node* lower = gasm_->BuildChangeSmiToInt32(
2360 gasm_->LoadFixedArrayElementSmi(values_array, *index));
2361 (*index)++;
2362 Node* value = gasm_->Word32Or(upper, lower);
2363 return value;
2364}
2365
2366Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildDecodeException64BitValue(Node* values_array,
2367 uint32_t* index) {
2368 Node* upper = Binop(wasm::kExprI64Shl,
2369 Unop(wasm::kExprI64UConvertI32,
2370 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, index)),
2371 Int64Constant(32));
2372 Node* lower = Unop(wasm::kExprI64UConvertI32,
2373 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, index));
2374 return Binop(wasm::kExprI64Ior, upper, lower);
2375}
