2393Node* WasmGraphBuilder::IsExceptionTagUndefined(Node* tag) {
2394 return gasm_->TaggedEqual(tag, UndefinedValue());
2395}
2396
2397Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoadJSTag() {
2398 Node* context =
2399 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
2400 Node* tag_obj =
2401 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), context,
2402 NativeContext::SlotOffset(Context::WASM_JS_TAG_INDEX));
2403 return gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), tag_obj,
2404 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTagObject::kTagOffset));
2405}
2406
2407Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ExceptionTagEqual(Node* caught_tag,
2408 Node* expected_tag) {
2409 return gasm_->WordEqual(caught_tag, expected_tag);
2410}
2411
2412Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoadTagFromTable(uint32_t tag_index) {
2413 Node* tags_table =
2414 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(TagsTable, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
2415 Node* tag = gasm_->LoadFixedArrayElementPtr(tags_table, tag_index);
2416 return tag;
2417}
2418
2419Node* WasmGraphBuilder::GetExceptionTag(Node* except_obj) {
2420 return gasm_->CallBuiltin(
2421 Builtin::kWasmGetOwnProperty, Operator::kEliminatable, except_obj,
2422 LOAD_ROOT(wasm_exception_tag_symbol, wasm_exception_tag_symbol),
2423 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
2424}
2425
2426Node* WasmGraphBuilder::GetExceptionValues(Node* except_obj,
2427 const wasm::WasmTag* tag,
2428 base::Vector<Node*> values) {
2429 Node* values_array = gasm_->CallBuiltin(
2430 Builtin::kWasmGetOwnProperty, Operator::kEliminatable, except_obj,
2431 LOAD_ROOT(wasm_exception_values_symbol, wasm_exception_values_symbol),
2432 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
2433 uint32_t index = 0;
2434 const wasm::WasmTagSig* sig = tag->sig;
2435 DCHECK_EQ(sig->parameter_count(), values.size());
2436 for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); ++i) {
2437 Node* value;
2438 switch (sig->GetParam(i).kind()) {
2439 case wasm::kI32:
2440 value = BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index);
2441 break;
2442 case wasm::kI64:
2443 value = BuildDecodeException64BitValue(values_array, &index);
2444 break;
2445 case wasm::kF32: {
2446 value = Unop(wasm::kExprF32ReinterpretI32,
2447 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index));
2448 break;
2449 }
2450 case wasm::kF64: {
2451 value = Unop(wasm::kExprF64ReinterpretI64,
2452 BuildDecodeException64BitValue(values_array, &index));
2453 break;
2454 }
2455 case wasm::kS128:
2456 value = graph()->NewNode(
2457 mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4Splat(),
2458 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index));
2459 value = graph()->NewNode(
2460 mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4ReplaceLane(1), value,
2461 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index));
2462 value = graph()->NewNode(
2463 mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4ReplaceLane(2), value,
2464 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index));
2465 value = graph()->NewNode(
2466 mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4ReplaceLane(3), value,
2467 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index));
2468 break;
2469 case wasm::kRef:
2470 case wasm::kRefNull:
2471 case wasm::kRtt:
2472 value = gasm_->LoadFixedArrayElementAny(values_array, index);
2473 ++index;
2474 break;
2475 case wasm::kI8:
2476 case wasm::kI16:
2477 case wasm::kF16:
2478 case wasm::kVoid:
2479 case wasm::kTop:
2480 case wasm::kBottom:
2481 UNREACHABLE();
2482 }
2483 values[i] = value;
2484 }
2485 DCHECK_EQ(index, WasmExceptionPackage::GetEncodedSize(tag));
2486 return values_array;
2487}
2488
2489Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32DivS(Node* left, Node* right,
2490 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2491 ZeroCheck32(wasm::kTrapDivByZero, right, position);
2492 Node* previous_effect = effect();
2493 auto [denom_is_m1, denom_is_not_m1] =
2494 BranchExpectFalse(gasm_->Word32Equal(right, Int32Constant(-1)));
2495 SetControl(denom_is_m1);
2496 TrapIfEq32(wasm::kTrapDivUnrepresentable, left, kMinInt, position);
2497 Node* merge = Merge(control(), denom_is_not_m1);
2498 SetEffectControl(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->EffectPhi(2), effect(),
2499 previous_effect, merge),
2500 merge);
2501 return gasm_->Int32Div(left, right);
2502}
2503
2504Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32RemS(Node* left, Node* right,
2505 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2506 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2507
2508 ZeroCheck32(wasm::kTrapRemByZero, right, position);
2509
2510 Diamond d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2511 gasm_->Word32Equal(right, Int32Constant(-1)), BranchHint::kFalse);
2512 d.Chain(control());
2513
2514 return d.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Int32Constant(0),
2515 graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Mod(), left, right, d.if_false));
2516}
2517
2518Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32DivU(Node* left, Node* right,
2519 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2520 ZeroCheck32(wasm::kTrapDivByZero, right, position);
2521 return gasm_->Uint32Div(left, right);
2522}
2523
2524Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32RemU(Node* left, Node* right,
2525 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2526 ZeroCheck32(wasm::kTrapRemByZero, right, position);
2527 return gasm_->Uint32Mod(left, right);
2528}
2529
2530Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32AsmjsDivS(Node* left, Node* right) {
2531 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2532
2533 Int32Matcher mr(right);
2534 if (mr.HasResolvedValue()) {
2535 if (mr.ResolvedValue() == 0) {
2536 return Int32Constant(0);
2537 } else if (mr.ResolvedValue() == -1) {
2538 // The result is the negation of the left input.
2539 return gasm_->Int32Sub(Int32Constant(0), left);
2540 }
2541 return gasm_->Int32Div(left, right);
2542 }
2543
2544 // asm.js semantics return 0 on divide or mod by zero.
2545 if (m->Int32DivIsSafe()) {
2546 // The hardware instruction does the right thing (e.g. arm).
2547 return gasm_->Int32Div(left, right);
2548 }
2549
2550 // Check denominator for zero.
2551 Diamond z(graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2552 gasm_->Word32Equal(right, Int32Constant(0)), BranchHint::kFalse);
2553 z.Chain(control());
2554
2555 // Check denominator for -1. (avoid minint / -1 case).
2556 Diamond n(graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2557 gasm_->Word32Equal(right, Int32Constant(-1)), BranchHint::kFalse);
2558 n.Chain(z.if_false);
2559
2560 Node* div = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Div(), left, right, n.if_false);
2561
2562 Node* neg = gasm_->Int32Sub(Int32Constant(0), left);
2563
2564 return z.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Int32Constant(0),
2565 n.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, neg, div));
2566}
2567
2568Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32AsmjsRemS(Node* left, Node* right) {
2569 CommonOperatorBuilder* c = mcgraph()->common();
2570 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2571 Node* const zero = Int32Constant(0);
2572
2573 Int32Matcher mr(right);
2574 if (mr.HasResolvedValue()) {
2575 if (mr.ResolvedValue() == 0 || mr.ResolvedValue() == -1) {
2576 return zero;
2577 }
2578 return gasm_->Int32Mod(left, right);
2579 }
2580
2581 // General case for signed integer modulus, with optimization for (unknown)
2582 // power of 2 right hand side.
2583 //
2584 // if 0 < right then
2585 // msk = right - 1
2586 // if right & msk != 0 then
2587 // left % right
2588 // else
2589 // if left < 0 then
2590 // -(-left & msk)
2591 // else
2592 // left & msk
2593 // else
2594 // if right < -1 then
2595 // left % right
2596 // else
2597 // zero
2598 //
2599 // Note: We do not use the Diamond helper class here, because it really hurts
2600 // readability with nested diamonds.
2601 Node* const minus_one = Int32Constant(-1);
2602
2603 const Operator* const merge_op = c->Merge(2);
2604 const Operator* const phi_op = c->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2);
2605
2606 Node* check0 = gasm_->Int32LessThan(zero, right);
2607 Node* branch0 =
2608 graph()->NewNode(c->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check0, control());
2609
2610 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfTrue(), branch0);
2611 Node* true0;
2612 {
2613 Node* msk = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Add(), right, minus_one);
2614
2615 Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32And(), right, msk);
2616 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(c->Branch(), check1, if_true0);
2617
2618 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfTrue(), branch1);
2619 Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Mod(), left, right, if_true1);
2620
2621 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfFalse(), branch1);
2622 Node* false1;
2623 {
2624 Node* check2 = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32LessThan(), left, zero);
2625 Node* branch2 =
2626 graph()->NewNode(c->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check2, if_false1);
2627
2628 Node* if_true2 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfTrue(), branch2);
2629 Node* true2 = graph()->NewNode(
2630 m->Int32Sub(), zero,
2631 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32And(),
2632 graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Sub(), zero, left), msk));
2633
2634 Node* if_false2 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfFalse(), branch2);
2635 Node* false2 = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32And(), left, msk);
2636
2637 if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true2, if_false2);
2638 false1 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true2, false2, if_false1);
2639 }
2640
2641 if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
2642 true0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_true0);
2643 }
2644
2645 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfFalse(), branch0);
2646 Node* false0;
2647 {
2648 Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32LessThan(), right, minus_one);
2649 Node* branch1 =
2650 graph()->NewNode(c->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check1, if_false0);
2651
2652 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfTrue(), branch1);
2653 Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Mod(), left, right, if_true1);
2654
2655 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfFalse(), branch1);
2656 Node* false1 = zero;
2657
2658 if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
2659 false0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_false0);
2660 }
2661
2662 Node* merge0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true0, if_false0);
2663 return graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true0, false0, merge0);
2664}
2665
2666Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32AsmjsDivU(Node* left, Node* right) {
2667 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2668 // asm.js semantics return 0 on divide or mod by zero.
2669 if (m->Uint32DivIsSafe()) {
2670 // The hardware instruction does the right thing (e.g. arm).
2671 return gasm_->Uint32Div(left, right);
2672 }
2673
2674 // Explicit check for x / 0.
2675 Diamond z(graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2676 gasm_->Word32Equal(right, Int32Constant(0)), BranchHint::kFalse);
2677 z.Chain(control());
2678
2679 return z.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Int32Constant(0),
2680 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Uint32Div(), left, right,
2681 z.if_false));
2682}
2683
2684Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32AsmjsRemU(Node* left, Node* right) {
2685 // asm.js semantics return 0 on divide or mod by zero.
2686 // Explicit check for x % 0.
2687 Diamond z(graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2688 gasm_->Word32Equal(right, Int32Constant(0)), BranchHint::kFalse);
2689 z.Chain(control());
2690
2691 Node* rem = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Uint32Mod(), left, right,
2692 z.if_false);
2693 return z.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Int32Constant(0), rem);
2694}
2695
2696Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64DivS(Node* left, Node* right,
2697 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2698 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()) {
2699 return BuildDiv64Call(left, right, ExternalReference::wasm_int64_div(),
2700 MachineType::Int64(), wasm::kTrapDivByZero, position);
2701 }
2702 ZeroCheck64(wasm::kTrapDivByZero, right, position);
2703 Node* previous_effect = effect();
2704 auto [denom_is_m1, denom_is_not_m1] =
2705 BranchExpectFalse(gasm_->Word64Equal(right, Int64Constant(-1)));
2706 SetControl(denom_is_m1);
2707 TrapIfEq64(wasm::kTrapDivUnrepresentable, left,
2708 std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min(), position);
2709 Node* merge = Merge(control(), denom_is_not_m1);
2710 SetEffectControl(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->EffectPhi(2), effect(),
2711 previous_effect, merge),
2712 merge);
2713 return gasm_->Int64Div(left, right);
2714}
2715
2716Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64RemS(Node* left, Node* right,
2717 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2718 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()) {
2719 return BuildDiv64Call(left, right, ExternalReference::wasm_int64_mod(),
2720 MachineType::Int64(), wasm::kTrapRemByZero, position);
2721 }
2722 ZeroCheck64(wasm::kTrapRemByZero, right, position);
2723 Diamond d(mcgraph()->graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2724 gasm_->Word64Equal(right, Int64Constant(-1)));
2725
2726 d.Chain(control());
2727
2728 Node* rem = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Int64Mod(), left, right,
2729 d.if_false);
2730
2731 return d.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord64, Int64Constant(0), rem);
2732}
2733
2734Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64DivU(Node* left, Node* right,
2735 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2736 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()) {
2737 return BuildDiv64Call(left, right, ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_div(),
2738 MachineType::Int64(), wasm::kTrapDivByZero, position);
2739 }
2740 ZeroCheck64(wasm::kTrapDivByZero, right, position);
2741 return gasm_->Uint64Div(left, right);
2742}
2743Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64RemU(Node* left, Node* right,
2744 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2745 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()) {
2746 return BuildDiv64Call(left, right, ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_mod(),
2747 MachineType::Int64(), wasm::kTrapRemByZero, position);
2748 }
2749 ZeroCheck64(wasm::kTrapRemByZero, right, position);
2750 return gasm_->Uint64Mod(left, right);
2751}
2752
2753Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildDiv64Call(Node* left, Node* right,
2754 ExternalReference ref,
2755 MachineType result_type,
2756 wasm::TrapReason trap_zero,
2757 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2758 Node* stack_slot =
2759 StoreArgsInStackSlot({{MachineRepresentation::kWord64, left},
2760 {MachineRepresentation::kWord64, right}});
2761
2762 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Int32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
2763 MachineSignature sig(1, 1, sig_types);
2764
2765 Node* function = gasm_->ExternalConstant(ref);
2766 Node* call = BuildCCall(&sig, function, stack_slot);
2767
2768 ZeroCheck32(trap_zero, call, position);
2769 TrapIfEq32(wasm::kTrapDivUnrepresentable, call, -1, position);
2770 return gasm_->Load(result_type, stack_slot, 0);
2771}
2772
2773Node* WasmGraphBuilder::IsNull(Node* object, wasm::ValueType type) {
2774 // This version is for Wasm functions (i.e. not wrappers):
2775 // - they use module-specific types
2776 // - they go through a lowering phase later
2777 // Both points are different in wrappers, see
2778 // WasmWrapperGraphBuilder::IsNull().
2779 DCHECK_EQ(parameter_mode_, kInstanceParameterMode);
2780 return gasm_->IsNull(object, type);
2781}
2782
2783template <typename... Args>
2784Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCCall(MachineSignature* sig, Node* function,
2785 Args... args) {
2786 DCHECK_LE(sig->return_count(), 1);
2787 DCHECK_EQ(sizeof...(args), sig->parameter_count());
2788 Node* call_args[] = {function, args..., effect(), control()};
2789
2790 auto call_descriptor =
2791 Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(mcgraph()->zone(), sig);
2792
2793 return gasm_->Call(call_descriptor, arraysize(call_args), call_args);
2794}
2795
2796Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCallNode(size_t param_count,
2797 base::Vector<Node*> args,
2798 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2799 Node* implicit_first_arg,
2800 const Operator* op, Node* frame_state) {
2801 needs_stack_check_ = true;
2802 const size_t has_frame_state = frame_state != nullptr ? 1 : 0;
2803 const size_t extra = 3; // instance_node, effect, and control.
2804 const size_t count = 1 + param_count + extra + has_frame_state;
2805
2806 // Reallocate the buffer to make space for extra inputs.
2807 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16 + extra> inputs(count);
2808 DCHECK_EQ(1 + param_count, args.size());
2809
2810 // Make room for the first argument at index 1, just after code.
2811 inputs[0] = args[0]; // code
2812 inputs[1] = implicit_first_arg;
2813 if (param_count > 0) {
2814 memcpy(&inputs[2], &args[1], param_count * sizeof(Node*));
2815 }
2816
2817 // Add effect and control inputs.
2818 if (has_frame_state != 0) inputs[param_count + 2] = frame_state;
2819 inputs[param_count + has_frame_state + 2] = effect();
2820 inputs[param_count + has_frame_state + 3] = control();
2821
2822 Node* call = graph()->NewNode(op, static_cast<int>(count), inputs.begin());
2823 // Return calls have no effect output. Other calls are the new effect node.
2824 if (op->EffectOutputCount() > 0) SetEffect(call);
2825 DCHECK(position == wasm::kNoCodePosition || position > 0);
2826 if (position > 0) SetSourcePosition(call, position);
2827
2828 return call;
2829}
2830
2831template <typename T>
2832Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildWasmCall(const Signature<T>* sig,
2833 base::Vector<Node*> args,
2834 base::Vector<Node*> rets,
2835 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2836 Node* implicit_first_arg, bool indirect,
2837 Node* frame_state) {
2838 WasmCallKind call_kind = indirect ? kWasmIndirectFunction : kWasmFunction;
2839 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = GetWasmCallDescriptor(
2840 mcgraph()->zone(), sig, call_kind, frame_state != nullptr);
2841 const Operator* op = mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor);
2842 Node* call = BuildCallNode(sig->parameter_count(), args, position,
2843 implicit_first_arg, op, frame_state);
2844 // TODO(manoskouk): These assume the call has control and effect outputs.
2845 DCHECK_GT(op->ControlOutputCount(), 0);
2846 DCHECK_GT(op->EffectOutputCount(), 0);
2847 SetEffectControl(call);
2848
2849 size_t ret_count = sig->return_count();
2850 if (ret_count == 0) return call; // No return value.
2851
2852 DCHECK_EQ(ret_count, rets.size());
2853 if (ret_count == 1) {
2854 // Only a single return value.
2855 rets[0] = call;
2856 } else {
2857 // Create projections for all return values.
2858 for (size_t i = 0; i < ret_count; i++) {
2859 rets[i] = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Projection(i), call,
2860 graph()->start());
2861 }
2862 }
2863 return call;
2864}
2865
2866Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildWasmReturnCall(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
2867 base::Vector<Node*> args,
2868 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2869 Node* implicit_first_arg,
2870 bool indirect) {
2871 WasmCallKind call_kind = indirect ? kWasmIndirectFunction : kWasmFunction;
2872 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
2873 GetWasmCallDescriptor(mcgraph()->zone(), sig, call_kind);
2874 const Operator* op = mcgraph()->common()->TailCall(call_descriptor);
2875 Node* call = BuildCallNode(sig->parameter_count(), args, position,
2876 implicit_first_arg, op);
2877
2878 // TODO(manoskouk): If we have kNoThrow calls, do not merge them to end.
2879 DCHECK_GT(call->op()->ControlOutputCount(), 0);
2880 gasm_->MergeControlToEnd(call);
2881
2882 return call;
2883}
2884
2885Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildImportCall(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
2886 base::Vector<Node*> args,
2887 base::Vector<Node*> rets,
2888 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2889 int func_index,
2890 IsReturnCall continuation) {
2891 return BuildImportCall(sig, args, rets, position,
2892 gasm_->Uint32Constant(func_index), continuation);
2893}
2894
2895Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildImportCall(
2896 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig, base::Vector<Node*> args,
2897 base::Vector<Node*> rets, wasm::WasmCodePosition position, Node* func_index,
2898 IsReturnCall continuation, Node* frame_state) {
2899 // Load the imported function refs array from the instance.
2900 Node* dispatch_table =
2901 LOAD_IMMUTABLE_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(DispatchTableForImports);
2902 // Access fixed array at {header_size - tag + func_index * kTaggedSize}.
2903 Node* func_index_intptr = gasm_->BuildChangeUint32ToUintPtr(func_index);
2904 Node* dispatch_table_entry_offset = gasm_->IntMul(
2905 func_index_intptr, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(WasmDispatchTable::kEntrySize));
2906 Node* implicit_arg = gasm_->LoadProtectedPointerFromObject(
2907 dispatch_table,
2908 gasm_->IntAdd(dispatch_table_entry_offset,
2909 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
2910 WasmDispatchTable::kEntriesOffset +
2911 WasmDispatchTable::kImplicitArgBias))));
2912
2913 Node* target = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
2914 MachineType::Uint32(), dispatch_table,
2915 gasm_->IntAdd(dispatch_table_entry_offset,
2916 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
2917 WasmDispatchTable::kEntriesOffset +
2918 WasmDispatchTable::kTargetBias))));
2919
2920 args[0] = target;
2921
2922 switch (continuation) {
2923 case kCallContinues:
2924 return BuildWasmCall(sig, args, rets, position, implicit_arg, true,
2925 frame_state);
2926 case kReturnCall:
2927 DCHECK(rets.empty());
2928 return BuildWasmReturnCall(sig, args, position, implicit_arg, true);
2929 }
2930}
2931
2932Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CallDirect(uint32_t index, base::Vector<Node*> args,
2933 base::Vector<Node*> rets,
2934 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2935 DCHECK_NULL(args[0]);
2936 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig = env_->module->functions[index].sig;
2937
2938 if (env_ && index < env_->module->num_imported_functions) {
2939 // Call to an imported function.
2940 return BuildImportCall(sig, args, rets, position, index, kCallContinues);
2941 }
2942
2943 // A direct call to a wasm function defined in this module.
2944 // Just encode the function index. This will be patched at instantiation.
2945 Address code = static_cast<Address>(index);
2946 args[0] = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(code, RelocInfo::WASM_CALL);
2947
2948 return BuildWasmCall(sig, args, rets, position, GetInstanceData(), false);
2949}
2950
2951Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CallIndirect(uint32_t table_index,
2952 wasm::ModuleTypeIndex sig_index,
2953 base::Vector<Node*> args,
2954 base::Vector<Node*> rets,
2955 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2956 return BuildIndirectCall(table_index, sig_index, args, rets, position,
2957 kCallContinues);
2958}
2959
2960Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildIndirectCall(uint32_t table_index,
2961 wasm::ModuleTypeIndex sig_index,
2962 base::Vector<Node*> args,
2963 base::Vector<Node*> rets,
2964 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2965 IsReturnCall continuation) {
2966 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(args[0]);
2967 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(env_);
2968
2969 // Load the dispatch table.
2970 Node* dispatch_table;
2971 if (table_index == 0) {
2972 dispatch_table = LOAD_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(DispatchTable0);
2973 } else {
2974 Node* dispatch_tables =
2975 LOAD_IMMUTABLE_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(DispatchTables);
2976 dispatch_table = gasm_->LoadProtectedPointerFromObject(
2977 dispatch_tables,
2978 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
2979 ProtectedFixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(table_index)));
2980 }
2981
2982 // Bounds check the index.
2983 Node* index = args[0];
2984 const wasm::WasmTable& table = env_->module->tables[table_index];
2985 TableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(table.address_type, {&index}, position);
2986 const bool needs_dynamic_size =
2987 !table.has_maximum_size || table.maximum_size != table.initial_size;
2988 Node* table_size =
2989 needs_dynamic_size
2990 ? gasm_->LoadFromObject(
2991 MachineType::Int32(), dispatch_table,
2992 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmDispatchTable::kLengthOffset))
2993 : Int32Constant(table.initial_size);
2994 Node* in_bounds = Is64() ? gasm_->Uint64LessThan(
2995 index, gasm_->ChangeUint32ToUint64(table_size))
2996 : gasm_->Uint32LessThan(index, table_size);
2997 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapTableOutOfBounds, in_bounds, position);
2998
2999 wasm::ValueType table_type = env_->module->tables[table_index].type;
3000 bool needs_type_check = !wasm::EquivalentTypes(
3001 table_type.AsNonNull(), wasm::ValueType::Ref(sig_index), env_->module,
3002 env_->module);
3003 bool needs_null_check = table_type.is_nullable();
3004
3005 Node* dispatch_table_entry_offset = gasm_->IntAdd(
3006 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(
3007 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmDispatchTable::kEntriesOffset)),
3008 gasm_->IntMul(index,
3009 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(WasmDispatchTable::kEntrySize)));
3010
3011 // Skip check if table type matches declared signature.
3012 if (needs_type_check) {
3013 // Embed the expected signature ID as a relocatable constant.
3014 wasm::CanonicalTypeIndex canonical_sig_id =
3015 env_->module->canonical_sig_id(sig_index);
3016 Node* expected_sig_id = mcgraph()->RelocatableInt32Constant(
3017 canonical_sig_id.index, RelocInfo::WASM_CANONICAL_SIG_ID);
3018
3019 Node* loaded_sig = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
3020 MachineType::Int32(), dispatch_table,
3021 gasm_->IntAdd(dispatch_table_entry_offset,
3022 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(WasmDispatchTable::kSigBias)));
3023 Node* sig_match = gasm_->Word32Equal(loaded_sig, expected_sig_id);
3024
3025 if (!env_->module->type(sig_index).is_final) {
3026 // Do a full subtyping check.
3027 auto end_label = gasm_->MakeLabel();
3028 gasm_->GotoIf(sig_match, &end_label);
3029
3030 // Trap on null element.
3031 if (needs_null_check) {
3032 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapFuncSigMismatch,
3033 gasm_->Word32Equal(loaded_sig, Int32Constant(-1)), position);
3034 }
3035
3036 Node* formal_rtt = RttCanon(sig_index);
3037 int rtt_depth = wasm::GetSubtypingDepth(env_->module, sig_index);
3038 DCHECK_GE(rtt_depth, 0);
3039
3040 // Since we have the canonical index of the real rtt, we have to load it
3041 // from the isolate rtt-array (which is canonically indexed). Since this
3042 // reference is weak, we have to promote it to a strong reference.
3043 // Note: The reference cannot have been cleared: Since the loaded_sig
3044 // corresponds to a function of the same canonical type, that function
3045 // will have kept the type alive.
3046 Node* rtts = LOAD_MUTABLE_ROOT(WasmCanonicalRtts, wasm_canonical_rtts);
3047 Node* real_rtt =
3048 gasm_->WordAnd(gasm_->LoadWeakFixedArrayElement(rtts, loaded_sig),
3049 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
3050 Node* type_info = gasm_->LoadWasmTypeInfo(real_rtt);
3051
3052 // If the depth of the rtt is known to be less than the minimum supertype
3053 // array length, we can access the supertype without bounds-checking the
3054 // supertype array.
3055 if (static_cast<uint32_t>(rtt_depth) >=
3056 wasm::kMinimumSupertypeArraySize) {
3057 Node* supertypes_length =
3058 gasm_->BuildChangeSmiToIntPtr(gasm_->LoadImmutableFromObject(
3059 MachineType::TaggedSigned(), type_info,
3060 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
3061 WasmTypeInfo::kSupertypesLengthOffset)));
3062 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapFuncSigMismatch,
3063 gasm_->UintLessThan(gasm_->IntPtrConstant(rtt_depth),
3064 supertypes_length),
3065 position);
3066 }
3067
3068 Node* maybe_match = gasm_->LoadImmutableFromObject(
3069 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), type_info,
3070 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTypeInfo::kSupertypesOffset +
3071 kTaggedSize * rtt_depth));
3072 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapFuncSigMismatch,
3073 gasm_->TaggedEqual(maybe_match, formal_rtt), position);
3074 gasm_->Goto(&end_label);
3075
3076 gasm_->Bind(&end_label);
3077 } else {
3078 // In absence of subtyping, we just need to check for type equality.
3079 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapFuncSigMismatch, sig_match, position);
3080 }
3081 } else if (needs_null_check) {
3082 Node* loaded_sig = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
3083 MachineType::Int32(), dispatch_table,
3084 gasm_->IntAdd(dispatch_table_entry_offset,
3085 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(WasmDispatchTable::kSigBias)));
3086 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapFuncSigMismatch,
3087 gasm_->Word32Equal(loaded_sig, Int32Constant(-1)), position);
3088 }
3089
3090 Node* implicit_arg = gasm_->LoadProtectedPointerFromObject(
3091 dispatch_table, gasm_->IntAdd(dispatch_table_entry_offset,
3092 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(
3093 WasmDispatchTable::kImplicitArgBias)));
3094
3095 Node* target = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
3096 MachineType::Uint32(), dispatch_table,
3097 gasm_->IntAdd(dispatch_table_entry_offset,
3098 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(WasmDispatchTable::kTargetBias)));
3099 args[0] = target;
3100
3101 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig = env_->module->signature(sig_index);
3102
3103 switch (continuation) {
3104 case kCallContinues:
3105 return BuildWasmCall(sig, args, rets, position, implicit_arg, true);
3106 case kReturnCall:
3107 return BuildWasmReturnCall(sig, args, position, implicit_arg, true);
3108 }
3109}
3110
3111Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildLoadCallTargetFromExportedFunctionData(
3112 Node* function_data) {
3113 // TODO(sroettger): this code should do a signature check, but it's only used
3114 // for CAPI.
3115 Node* internal = gasm_->LoadProtectedPointerFromObject(
3116 function_data, wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
3117 WasmExportedFunctionData::kProtectedInternalOffset));
3118 Node* code_pointer = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
3119 MachineType::Uint32(), internal,
3120 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmInternalFunction::kRawCallTargetOffset));
3121 return gasm_->LoadWasmCodePointer(code_pointer);
3122}
3123
3124// TODO(9495): Support CAPI function refs.
3125Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCallRef(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
3126 base::Vector<Node*> args,
3127 base::Vector<Node*> rets,
3128 CheckForNull null_check,
3129 IsReturnCall continuation,
3130 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3131 Node* func_ref = args[0];
3132 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck &&
3133 null_check_strategy_ == NullCheckStrategy::kExplicit) {
3134 func_ref =
3135 AssertNotNull(func_ref, wasm::kWasmFuncRef /* good enough */, position);
3136 }
3137
3138 Node* internal_function;
3139 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck &&
3140 null_check_strategy_ == NullCheckStrategy::kTrapHandler) {
3141 // TODO(14564): Move WasmInternalFunction to trusted space and make
3142 // this a load of a trusted (immutable) pointer.
3143 Node* load;
3144 std::tie(load, internal_function) =
3145 gasm_->LoadTrustedPointerFromObjectTrapOnNull(
3146 func_ref,
3147 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmFuncRef::kTrustedInternalOffset),
3148 kWasmInternalFunctionIndirectPointerTag);
3149 SetSourcePosition(load, position);
3150 } else {
3151 internal_function = gasm_->LoadTrustedPointerFromObject(
3152 func_ref,
3153 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmFuncRef::kTrustedInternalOffset),
3154 kWasmInternalFunctionIndirectPointerTag);
3155 }
3156
3157 Node* implicit_arg = gasm_->LoadImmutableProtectedPointerFromObject(
3158 internal_function,
3159 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
3160 WasmInternalFunction::kProtectedImplicitArgOffset));
3161 Node* target = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
3162 MachineType::Uint32(), internal_function,
3163 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmInternalFunction::kRawCallTargetOffset));
3164
3165 args[0] = target;
3166
3167 Node* call =
3168 continuation == kCallContinues
3169 ? BuildWasmCall(sig, args, rets, position, implicit_arg, true)
3170 : BuildWasmReturnCall(sig, args, position, implicit_arg, true);
3171 return call;
3172}
3173
3174void WasmGraphBuilder::CompareToFuncRefAtIndex(Node* func_ref,
3175 uint32_t function_index,
3176 Node** success_control,
3177 Node** failure_control,
3178 bool is_last_case) {
3179 // Since we are comparing to a function reference, it is guaranteed that
3180 // instance->wasm_internal_functions() has been initialized.
3181 Node* func_refs = gasm_->LoadImmutable(
3182 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), GetInstanceData(),
3183 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTrustedInstanceData::kFuncRefsOffset));
3184 // We cannot use an immutable load here, since function references are
3185 // initialized lazily: Calling {RefFunc()} between two invocations of this
3186 // function may initialize the function, i.e. mutate the object we are
3187 // loading.
3188 Node* function_ref_at_index = gasm_->LoadFixedArrayElement(
3189 func_refs, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(function_index),
3190 MachineType::AnyTagged());
3191 BranchHint hint = is_last_case ? BranchHint::kTrue : BranchHint::kNone;
3192 gasm_->Branch(gasm_->TaggedEqual(function_ref_at_index, func_ref),
3193 success_control, failure_control, hint);
3194}

3196Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CallRef(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
3197 base::Vector<Node*> args,
3198 base::Vector<Node*> rets,
3199 CheckForNull null_check,
3200 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3201 return BuildCallRef(sig, args, rets, null_check, IsReturnCall::kCallContinues,
3202 position);
3203}

3205Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ReturnCallRef(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
3206 base::Vector<Node*> args,
3207 CheckForNull null_check,
3208 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3209 return BuildCallRef(sig, args, {}, null_check, IsReturnCall::kReturnCall,
3210 position);
3211}
3212
3213Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ReturnCall(uint32_t index, base::Vector<Node*> args,
3214 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3215 DCHECK_NULL(args[0]);
3216 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig = env_->module->functions[index].sig;
3217
3218 if (env_ && index < env_->module->num_imported_functions) {
3219 // Return Call to an imported function.
3220 return BuildImportCall(sig, args, {}, position, index, kReturnCall);
3221 }
3222
3223 // A direct tail call to a wasm function defined in this module.
3224 // Just encode the function index. This will be patched during code
3225 // generation.
3226 Address code = static_cast<Address>(index);
3227 args[0] = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(code, RelocInfo::WASM_CALL);
3228
3229 return BuildWasmReturnCall(sig, args, position, GetInstanceData());
3230}

3232Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ReturnCallIndirect(uint32_t table_index,
3233 wasm::ModuleTypeIndex sig_index,
3234 base::Vector<Node*> args,
3235 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3236 return BuildIndirectCall(table_index, sig_index, args, {}, position,
3237 kReturnCall);
3238}
3239
3240std::tuple<Node*, Node*> WasmGraphBuilder::BrOnNull(Node* ref_object,
3241 wasm::ValueType type) {
3242 return BranchExpectFalse(IsNull(ref_object, type));
3243}
3244
3245Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32Rol(Node* left, Node* right) {
3246 // Implement Rol by Ror since TurboFan does not have Rol opcode.
3247 // TODO(weiliang): support Word32Rol opcode in TurboFan.
3248 Int32Matcher m(right);
3249 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
3250 return Binop(wasm::kExprI32Ror, left,
3251 Int32Constant(32 - (m.ResolvedValue() & 0x1F)));
3252 } else {
3253 return Binop(wasm::kExprI32Ror, left,
3254 Binop(wasm::kExprI32Sub, Int32Constant(32), right));
3255 }
3256}
3257
3258Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64Rol(Node* left, Node* right) {
3259 // Implement Rol by Ror since TurboFan does not have Rol opcode.
3260 // TODO(weiliang): support Word64Rol opcode in TurboFan.
3261 Int64Matcher m(right);
3262 Node* inv_right = m.HasResolvedValue()
3263 ? Int64Constant(64 - (m.ResolvedValue() & 0x3F))
3264 : Binop(wasm::kExprI64Sub, Int64Constant(64), right);
3265 return Binop(wasm::kExprI64Ror, left, inv_right);
3266}
3267
3268Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Invert(Node* node) {
3269 return Unop(wasm::kExprI32Eqz, node);
3270}
3271
3272void WasmGraphBuilder::InitInstanceCache(
3273 WasmInstanceCacheNodes* instance_cache) {
3274 // We handle caching of the instance cache nodes manually, and we may reload
3275 // them in contexts where load elimination would eliminate the reload.
3276 // Therefore, we use plain Load nodes which are not subject to load
3277 // elimination.
3278
3279 // Only cache memory start and size if there is a memory (the nodes would be
3280 // dead otherwise, but we can avoid creating them in the first place).
3281 if (!has_cached_memory()) return;
3282
3283 instance_cache->mem_start = LoadMemStart(cached_memory_index_);
3284
3285 // TODO(13957): Clamp the loaded memory size to a safe value.
3286 instance_cache->mem_size = LoadMemSize(cached_memory_index_);
3287}
3288
3289void WasmGraphBuilder::PrepareInstanceCacheForLoop(
3290 WasmInstanceCacheNodes* instance_cache, Node* control) {
3291 if (!has_cached_memory()) return;
3292 for (auto field : WasmInstanceCacheNodes::kFields) {
3293 instance_cache->*field = graph()->NewNode(
3294 mcgraph()->common()->Phi(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), 1),
3295 instance_cache->*field, control);
3296 }
3297}
3298
3299void WasmGraphBuilder::NewInstanceCacheMerge(WasmInstanceCacheNodes* to,
3300 WasmInstanceCacheNodes* from,
3301 Node* merge) {
3302 for (auto field : WasmInstanceCacheNodes::kFields) {
3303 if (to->*field == from->*field) continue;
3304 Node* vals[] = {to->*field, from->*field, merge};
3305 to->*field = graph()->NewNode(
3306 mcgraph()->common()->Phi(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), 2), 3,
3307 vals);
3308 }
3309}
3310
3311void WasmGraphBuilder::MergeInstanceCacheInto(WasmInstanceCacheNodes* to,
3312 WasmInstanceCacheNodes* from,
3313 Node* merge) {
3314 if (!has_cached_memory()) {
3315 // Instance cache nodes should be nullptr then.
3316 DCHECK(to->mem_start == nullptr && to->mem_size == nullptr &&
3317 from->mem_start == nullptr && from->mem_size == nullptr);
3318 return;
3319 }
3320
3321 for (auto field : WasmInstanceCacheNodes::kFields) {
3322 to->*field = CreateOrMergeIntoPhi(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
3323 merge, to->*field, from->*field);
3324 }
3325}
3326
3327Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CreateOrMergeIntoPhi(MachineRepresentation rep,
3328 Node* merge, Node* tnode,
3329 Node* fnode) {
3330 if (IsPhiWithMerge(tnode, merge)) {
3331 AppendToPhi(tnode, fnode);
3332 } else if (tnode != fnode) {
3333 // Note that it is not safe to use {Buffer} here since this method is used
3334 // via {CheckForException} while the {Buffer} is in use by another method.
3335 uint32_t count = merge->InputCount();
3336 // + 1 for the merge node.
3337 base::SmallVector<Node*, 9> inputs(count + 1);
3338 for (uint32_t j = 0; j < count - 1; j++) inputs[j] = tnode;
3339 inputs[count - 1] = fnode;
3340 inputs[count] = merge;
3341 tnode = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Phi(rep, count), count + 1,
3342 inputs.begin());
3343 }
3344 return tnode;
3345}
3346
3347Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CreateOrMergeIntoEffectPhi(Node* merge, Node* tnode,
3348 Node* fnode) {
3349 if (IsPhiWithMerge(tnode, merge)) {
3350 AppendToPhi(tnode, fnode);
3351 } else if (tnode != fnode) {
3352 // Note that it is not safe to use {Buffer} here since this method is used
3353 // via {CheckForException} while the {Buffer} is in use by another method.
3354 uint32_t count = merge->InputCount();
3355 // + 1 for the merge node.
3356 base::SmallVector<Node*, 9> inputs(count + 1);
3357 for (uint32_t j = 0; j < count - 1; j++) {
3358 inputs[j] = tnode;
3359 }
3360 inputs[count - 1] = fnode;
3361 inputs[count] = merge;
3362 tnode = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1,
3363 inputs.begin());
3364 }
3365 return tnode;
3366}

3373 SetEffectControl(node, control());

3385
3386Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MemStart(uint32_t mem_index) {
3387 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instance_cache_);
3388 V8_ASSUME(cached_memory_index_ == kNoCachedMemoryIndex ||
3389 cached_memory_index_ >= 0);
3390 if (mem_index == static_cast<uint32_t>(cached_memory_index_)) {
3391 return instance_cache_->mem_start;
3392 }
3393 return LoadMemStart(mem_index);
3394}
3395
3396Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MemSize(uint32_t mem_index) {
3397 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instance_cache_);
3398 V8_ASSUME(cached_memory_index_ == kNoCachedMemoryIndex ||
3399 cached_memory_index_ >= 0);
3400 if (mem_index == static_cast<uint32_t>(cached_memory_index_)) {
3401 return instance_cache_->mem_size;
3402 }
3403
3404 return LoadMemSize(mem_index);
3405}
3406
3407Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoadMemStart(uint32_t mem_index) {
3408 if (mem_index == 0) {
3409 return LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD_NO_ELIMINATION(Memory0Start,
3410 MachineType::Pointer());
3411 }
3412 Node* memory_bases_and_sizes =
3413 LOAD_IMMUTABLE_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(MemoryBasesAndSizes);
3414 // Use {LoadByteArrayElement} even though it's a trusted array; their layout
3415 // is the same.
3416 static_assert(FixedAddressArray::OffsetOfElementAt(0) ==
3417 TrustedFixedAddressArray::OffsetOfElementAt(0));
3418 return gasm_->LoadByteArrayElement(memory_bases_and_sizes,
3419 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(2 * mem_index),
3420 MachineType::Pointer());
3421}
3422
3423Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoadMemSize(uint32_t mem_index) {
3424 wasm::ValueType mem_type = env_->module->memories[mem_index].is_memory64()
3425 ? wasm::kWasmI64
3426 : wasm::kWasmI32;
3427 if (mem_index == 0) {
3428 return SetType(
3429 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD_NO_ELIMINATION(Memory0Size, MachineType::UintPtr()),
3430 mem_type);
3431 }
3432 Node* memory_bases_and_sizes =
3433 LOAD_IMMUTABLE_PROTECTED_INSTANCE_FIELD(MemoryBasesAndSizes);
3434 // Use {LoadByteArrayElement} even though it's a trusted array; their layout
3435 // is the same.
3436 static_assert(FixedAddressArray::OffsetOfElementAt(0) ==
3437 TrustedFixedAddressArray::OffsetOfElementAt(0));
3438 return SetType(
3439 gasm_->LoadByteArrayElement(memory_bases_and_sizes,
3440 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(2 * mem_index + 1),
3441 MachineType::UintPtr()),
3442 mem_type);
3443}
3444
3445Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MemBuffer(uint32_t mem_index, uintptr_t offset) {
3446 Node* mem_start = MemStart(mem_index);
3447 if (offset == 0) return mem_start;
3448 return gasm_->IntAdd(mem_start, gasm_->UintPtrConstant(offset));
3449}
3450
3451Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CurrentMemoryPages(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory) {
3452 // CurrentMemoryPages can not be called from asm.js.
3453 DCHECK_EQ(wasm::kWasmOrigin, env_->module->origin);
3454
3455 Node* mem_size = MemSize(memory->index);
3456 Node* result =
3457 gasm_->WordShr(mem_size, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(wasm::kWasmPageSizeLog2));
3458 result = memory->is_memory64() ? gasm_->BuildChangeIntPtrToInt64(result)
3459 : gasm_->BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(result);
3460 return result;
3461}
3462
3463// Only call this function for code which is not reused across instantiations,
3464// as we do not patch the embedded js_context.
3465Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::FunctionId f,
3466 Node* js_context,
3467 Node** parameters,
3468 int parameter_count) {
3469 const Runtime::Function* fun = Runtime::FunctionForId(f);
3470 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetRuntimeCallDescriptor(
3471 mcgraph()->zone(), f, fun->nargs, Operator::kNoProperties,
3472 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
3473 // The CEntryStub is loaded from the IsolateRoot so that generated code is
3474 // Isolate independent. At the moment this is only done for CEntryStub(1).
3475 Node* isolate_root = BuildLoadIsolateRoot();
3476 DCHECK_EQ(1, fun->result_size);
3477 auto centry_id = Builtin::kWasmCEntry;
3478 int builtin_slot_offset = IsolateData::BuiltinSlotOffset(centry_id);
3479 Node* centry_stub =
3480 gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), isolate_root, builtin_slot_offset);
3481 // TODO(titzer): allow arbitrary number of runtime arguments
3482 // At the moment we only allow 5 parameters. If more parameters are needed,
3483 // increase this constant accordingly.
3484 static const int kMaxParams = 5;
3485 DCHECK_GE(kMaxParams, parameter_count);
3486 Node* inputs[kMaxParams + 6];
3487 int count = 0;
3488 inputs[count++] = centry_stub;
3489 for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count; i++) {
3490 inputs[count++] = parameters[i];
3491 }
3492 inputs[count++] =
3493 mcgraph()->ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(f)); // ref
3494 inputs[count++] = Int32Constant(fun->nargs); // arity
3495 inputs[count++] = js_context; // js_context
3496 inputs[count++] = effect();
3497 inputs[count++] = control();
3498
3499 return gasm_->Call(call_descriptor, count, inputs);
3500}
3501
3502Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCallToRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId f,
3503 Node** parameters,
3504 int parameter_count) {
3505 return BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(f, NoContextConstant(), parameters,
3506 parameter_count);
3507}
3508
3509void WasmGraphBuilder::GetGlobalBaseAndOffset(const wasm::WasmGlobal& global,
3510 Node** base, Node** offset) {
3511 if (global.mutability && global.imported) {
3512 Node* imported_mutable_globals = LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(
3513 ImportedMutableGlobals, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
3514 Node* field_offset = Int32Constant(
3515 wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedAddressArray(
3516 global.index));
3517 if (global.type.is_reference()) {
3518 // Load the base from the ImportedMutableGlobalsBuffer of the instance.
3519 Node* buffers = LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(ImportedMutableGlobalsBuffers,
3520 MachineType::TaggedPointer());
3521 *base = gasm_->LoadFixedArrayElementAny(buffers, global.index);
3522
3523 Node* index = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
3524 MachineType::Int32(), imported_mutable_globals, field_offset);
3525 // For this case, {index} gives the index of the global in the buffer.
3526 // From the index, calculate the actual offset in the FixedArray. This is
3527 // kHeaderSize + (index * kTaggedSize).
3528 *offset = gasm_->IntAdd(
3529 gasm_->IntMul(index, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(kTaggedSize)),
3530 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(
3531 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(0))));
3532 } else {
3533 *base = gasm_->LoadFromObject(kMaybeSandboxedPointer,
3534 imported_mutable_globals, field_offset);
3535 *offset = gasm_->IntPtrConstant(0);
3536 }
3537 } else if (global.type.is_reference()) {
3538 *base =
3539 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(TaggedGlobalsBuffer, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
3540 *offset = gasm_->IntPtrConstant(
3541 wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(global.offset));
3542 } else {
3543 *base = LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(GlobalsStart, MachineType::Pointer());
3544 *offset = gasm_->IntPtrConstant(global.offset);
3545 }
3546}
3547
3548Node* WasmGraphBuilder::GlobalGet(uint32_t index) {
3549 const wasm::WasmGlobal& global = env_->module->globals[index];
3550 if (global.type == wasm::kWasmS128) has_simd_ = true;
3551 Node* base = nullptr;
3552 Node* offset = nullptr;
3553 GetGlobalBaseAndOffset(global, &base, &offset);
3554 MachineType mem_type = global.type.machine_type();
3555 return global.mutability ? gasm_->LoadFromObject(mem_type, base, offset)
3556 : gasm_->LoadImmutable(mem_type, base, offset);
3557}
3558
3559void WasmGraphBuilder::GlobalSet(uint32_t index, Node* val) {
3560 const wasm::WasmGlobal& global = env_->module->globals[index];
3561 if (global.type == wasm::kWasmS128) has_simd_ = true;
3562 Node* base = nullptr;
3563 Node* offset = nullptr;
3564 GetGlobalBaseAndOffset(global, &base, &offset);
3565 ObjectAccess access(global.type.machine_type(), global.type.is_reference()
3566 ? kFullWriteBarrier
3567 : kNoWriteBarrier);
3568 gasm_->StoreToObject(access, base, offset, val);
3569}
3570
3571Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TableGet(uint32_t table_index, Node* index,
3572 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3573 const wasm::WasmTable& table = env_->module->tables[table_index];
3574 bool is_funcref = IsSubtypeOf(table.type, wasm::kWasmFuncRef, env_->module);
3575 auto stub =
3576 is_funcref ? Builtin::kWasmTableGetFuncRef : Builtin::kWasmTableGet;
3577
3578 TableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(table.address_type, {&index}, position);
3579 return gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
3580 stub, Operator::kNoThrow, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(table_index), index);
3581}
3582
3583void WasmGraphBuilder::TableSet(uint32_t table_index, Node* index, Node* val,
3584 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3585 const wasm::WasmTable& table = env_->module->tables[table_index];
3586 bool is_funcref = IsSubtypeOf(table.type, wasm::kWasmFuncRef, env_->module);
3587 auto stub =
3588 is_funcref ? Builtin::kWasmTableSetFuncRef : Builtin::kWasmTableSet;
3589 TableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(table.address_type, {&index}, position);
3590 gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(stub, Operator::kNoThrow,
3591 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(table_index),
3592 gasm_->Int32Constant(0), index, val);
3593}
3594
3595// Insert code to bounds check a memory access if necessary. Return the
3596// bounds-checked index, which is guaranteed to have (the equivalent of)
3597// {uintptr_t} representation.
3598std::pair<Node*, BoundsCheckResult> WasmGraphBuilder::BoundsCheckMem(
3599 const wasm::WasmMemory* memory, uint8_t access_size, Node* index,
3600 uintptr_t offset, wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
3601 EnforceBoundsCheck enforce_check, AlignmentCheck alignment_check) {
3602 DCHECK_LE(1, access_size);
3603
3604 wasm::BoundsCheckStrategy bounds_checks = memory->bounds_checks;
3605
3606 // The function body decoder already validated that the access is not
3607 // statically OOB.
3608 DCHECK(base::IsInBounds<uintptr_t>(offset, access_size,
3609 memory->max_memory_size));
3610
3611 // Convert the index to uintptr.
3612 Node* converted_index = index;
3613 if (!memory->is_memory64()) {
3614 converted_index = gasm_->BuildChangeUint32ToUintPtr(index);
3615 } else if (kSystemPointerSize == kInt32Size) {
3616 // Only use the low word for the following bounds check.
3617 converted_index = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(index);
3618 }
3619
3620 UintPtrMatcher constant_index(converted_index);
3621 // Do alignment checks only for > 1 byte accesses (otherwise they trivially
3622 // pass).
3623 const uintptr_t align_mask = access_size - 1;
3624 if (static_cast<bool>(alignment_check) && align_mask != 0) {
3625 // Don't emit an alignment check if the index is a constant.
3626 // TODO(wasm): a constant match is also done above in {BoundsCheckMem}.
3627 if (constant_index.HasResolvedValue()) {
3628 uintptr_t effective_offset = constant_index.ResolvedValue() + offset;
3629 if ((effective_offset & align_mask) != 0) {
3630 // statically known to be unaligned; trap.
3631 TrapIfEq32(wasm::kTrapUnalignedAccess, Int32Constant(0), 0, position);
3632 }
3633 } else {
3634 // Unlike regular memory accesses, atomic memory accesses should trap if
3635 // the effective offset is misaligned.
3636 // TODO(wasm): this addition is redundant with one inserted by
3637 // {MemBuffer}.
3638 Node* effective_offset =
3639 gasm_->IntAdd(MemBuffer(memory->index, offset), converted_index);
3640
3641 Node* cond =
3642 gasm_->WordAnd(effective_offset, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(align_mask));
3643 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapUnalignedAccess,
3644 gasm_->Word32Equal(cond, Int32Constant(0)), position);
3645 }
3646 }
3647
3648 // If no bounds checks should be performed (for testing), just return the
3649 // converted index and assume it to be in-bounds.
3650 if (bounds_checks == wasm::kNoBoundsChecks) {
3651 return {converted_index, BoundsCheckResult::kInBounds};
3652 }
3653
3654 if (memory->is_memory64() && kSystemPointerSize == kInt32Size) {
3655 // In memory64 mode on 32-bit systems, the upper 32 bits need to be zero to
3656 // succeed the bounds check.
3657 DCHECK_EQ(wasm::kExplicitBoundsChecks, bounds_checks);
3658 Node* high_word =
3659 gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(gasm_->Word64Shr(index, Int32Constant(32)));
3660 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, high_word, position);
3661 }
3662
3663 // The accessed memory is [index + offset, index + end_offset].
3664 // Check that the last read byte (at {index + end_offset}) is in bounds.
3665 // 1) Check that {end_offset < mem_size}. This also ensures that we can safely
3666 // compute {effective_size} as {mem_size - end_offset)}.
3667 // {effective_size} is >= 1 if condition 1) holds.
3668 // 2) Check that {index + end_offset < mem_size} by
3669 // - computing {effective_size} as {mem_size - end_offset} and
3670 // - checking that {index < effective_size}.
3671
3672 uintptr_t end_offset = offset + access_size - 1u;
3673 DCHECK_LT(end_offset, memory->max_memory_size);
3674
3675 if (constant_index.HasResolvedValue() &&
3676 end_offset <= memory->min_memory_size &&
3677 constant_index.ResolvedValue() < memory->min_memory_size - end_offset) {
3678 // The input index is a constant and everything is statically within
3679 // bounds of the smallest possible memory.
3680 return {converted_index, BoundsCheckResult::kInBounds};
3681 }
3682
3683 if (bounds_checks == wasm::kTrapHandler &&
3684 enforce_check == EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck) {
3685 if (memory->is_memory64()) {
3686 // Bounds check `index` against `max_mem_size - end_offset`, such that
3687 // at runtime `index + end_offset` will be within `max_mem_size`, where
3688 // the trap handler can handle out-of-bound accesses.
3689 Node* cond = gasm_->Uint64LessThan(
3690 converted_index, Int64Constant(memory->max_memory_size - end_offset));
3691 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, cond, position);
3692 }
3693 return {converted_index, BoundsCheckResult::kTrapHandler};
3694 }
3695
3696 Node* mem_size = MemSize(memory->index);
3697
3698 Node* end_offset_node = mcgraph_->UintPtrConstant(end_offset);
3699 if (end_offset > memory->min_memory_size) {
3700 // The end offset is larger than the smallest memory.
3701 // Dynamically check the end offset against the dynamic memory size.
3702 Node* cond = gasm_->UintLessThan(end_offset_node, mem_size);
3703 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, cond, position);
3704 }
3705
3706 // This produces a positive number since {end_offset <= min_size <= mem_size}.
3707 Node* effective_size = gasm_->IntSub(mem_size, end_offset_node);
3708
3709 // Introduce the actual bounds check.
3710 Node* cond = gasm_->UintLessThan(converted_index, effective_size);
3711 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, cond, position);
3712 return {converted_index, BoundsCheckResult::kDynamicallyChecked};
3713}
3714
3715const Operator* WasmGraphBuilder::GetSafeLoadOperator(
3716 int offset, wasm::ValueTypeBase type) {
3717 int alignment = offset % type.value_kind_size();
3718 MachineType mach_type = type.machine_type();
3719 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL && mach_type.IsTagged()) {
3720 // We are loading tagged value from off-heap location, so we need to load
3721 // it as a full word otherwise we will not be able to decompress it.
3722 mach_type = MachineType::Pointer();
3723 }
3724 if (alignment == 0 || mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedLoadSupported(
3725 type.machine_representation())) {
3726 return mcgraph()->machine()->Load(mach_type);
3727 }
3728 return mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedLoad(mach_type);
3729}
3730
3731const Operator* WasmGraphBuilder::GetSafeStoreOperator(
3732 int offset, wasm::ValueTypeBase type) {
3733 int alignment = offset % type.value_kind_size();
3734 MachineRepresentation rep = type.machine_representation();
3735 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL && IsAnyTagged(rep)) {
3736 // We are storing tagged value to off-heap location, so we need to store
3737 // it as a full word otherwise we will not be able to decompress it.
3738 rep = MachineType::PointerRepresentation();
3739 }
3740 if (alignment == 0 || mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedStoreSupported(rep)) {
3741 StoreRepresentation store_rep(rep, WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier);
3742 return mcgraph()->machine()->Store(store_rep);
3743 }
3744 UnalignedStoreRepresentation store_rep(rep);
3745 return mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedStore(store_rep);
3746}
3747
3748void WasmGraphBuilder::TraceFunctionEntry(wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3749 Node* call = BuildCallToRuntime(Runtime::kWasmTraceEnter, nullptr, 0);
3750 SetSourcePosition(call, position);
3751}
3752
3753void WasmGraphBuilder::TraceFunctionExit(base::Vector<Node*> vals,
3754 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3755 Node* info = gasm_->IntPtrConstant(0);
3756 size_t num_returns = vals.size();
3757 if (num_returns == 1) {
3758 wasm::ValueType return_type = function_sig_->GetReturn(0);
3759 MachineRepresentation rep = return_type.machine_representation();
3760 int size = ElementSizeInBytes(rep);
3761 info = gasm_->StackSlot(size, size);
3762
3763 gasm_->Store(StoreRepresentation(rep, kNoWriteBarrier), info,
3764 Int32Constant(0), vals[0]);
3765 }
3766
3767 Node* call = BuildCallToRuntime(Runtime::kWasmTraceExit, &info, 1);
3768 SetSourcePosition(call, position);
3769}
3770
3771void WasmGraphBuilder::TraceMemoryOperation(bool is_store,
3772 MachineRepresentation rep,
3773 Node* index, uintptr_t offset,
3774 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3775 int kAlign = 4; // Ensure that the LSB is 0, such that this looks like a Smi.
3776 TNode<RawPtrT> info =
3777 gasm_->StackSlot(sizeof(wasm::MemoryTracingInfo), kAlign);
3778
3779 Node* effective_offset = gasm_->IntAdd(gasm_->UintPtrConstant(offset), index);
3780 auto store = [&](int field_offset, MachineRepresentation rep, Node* data) {
3781 gasm_->Store(StoreRepresentation(rep, kNoWriteBarrier), info,
3782 Int32Constant(field_offset), data);
3783 };
3784 // Store effective_offset, is_store, and mem_rep.
3785 store(offsetof(wasm::MemoryTracingInfo, offset),
3786 MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), effective_offset);
3787 store(offsetof(wasm::MemoryTracingInfo, is_store),
3788 MachineRepresentation::kWord8, Int32Constant(is_store ? 1 : 0));
3789 store(offsetof(wasm::MemoryTracingInfo, mem_rep),
3790 MachineRepresentation::kWord8, Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(rep)));
3791
3792 Node* args[] = {info};
3793 Node* call =
3794 BuildCallToRuntime(Runtime::kWasmTraceMemory, args, arraysize(args));
3795 SetSourcePosition(call, position);
3796}
3797
3798namespace {
3799LoadTransformation GetLoadTransformation(
3800 MachineType memtype, wasm::LoadTransformationKind transform) {
3801 switch (transform) {
3802 case wasm::LoadTransformationKind::kSplat: {
3803 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
3804 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load8Splat;
3805 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
3806 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load16Splat;
3807 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
3808 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load32Splat;
3809 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
3810 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load64Splat;
3811 }
3812 break;
3813 }
3814 case wasm::LoadTransformationKind::kExtend: {
3815 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
3816 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load8x8S;
3817 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint8()) {
3818 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load8x8U;
3819 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
3820 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load16x4S;
3821 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint16()) {
3822 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load16x4U;
3823 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
3824 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load32x2S;
3825 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint32()) {
3826 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load32x2U;
3827 }
3828 break;
3829 }
3830 case wasm::LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend: {
3831 if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
3832 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load32Zero;
3833 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
3834 return LoadTransformation::kS128Load64Zero;
3835 }
3836 break;
3837 }
3838 }
3839 UNREACHABLE();
3840}
3841
3842MemoryAccessKind GetMemoryAccessKind(MachineGraph* mcgraph,
3843 MachineRepresentation memrep,
3844 BoundsCheckResult bounds_check_result) {
3845 if (bounds_check_result == BoundsCheckResult::kTrapHandler) {
3846 // Protected instructions do not come in an 'unaligned' flavor, so the trap
3847 // handler can currently only be used on systems where all memory accesses
3848 // are allowed to be unaligned.
3849 DCHECK(memrep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8 ||
3850 mcgraph->machine()->UnalignedLoadSupported(memrep));
3851 return MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler;
3852 }
3853 if (memrep != MachineRepresentation::kWord8 &&
3854 !mcgraph->machine()->UnalignedLoadSupported(memrep)) {
3855 return MemoryAccessKind::kUnaligned;
3856 }
3857 return MemoryAccessKind::kNormal;
3858}
3859} // namespace
3860
3861Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoadLane(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory,
3862 wasm::ValueType type, MachineType memtype,
3863 Node* value, Node* index, uintptr_t offset,
3864 uint32_t alignment, uint8_t laneidx,
3865 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3866 has_simd_ = true;
3867 Node* load;
3868 uint8_t access_size = memtype.MemSize();
3869 BoundsCheckResult bounds_check_result;
3870 std::tie(index, bounds_check_result) = BoundsCheckMem(
3871 memory, access_size, index, offset, position,
3872 EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck, AlignmentCheck::kNo);
3873
3874 MemoryAccessKind load_kind = GetMemoryAccessKind(
3875 mcgraph_, memtype.representation(), bounds_check_result);
3876
3877 load = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
3878 mcgraph()->machine()->LoadLane(load_kind, memtype, laneidx),
3879 MemBuffer(memory->index, offset), index, value, effect(), control()));
3880
3881 if (load_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
3882 SetSourcePosition(load, position);
3883 }
3884 if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory) {
3885 // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
3886 CHECK_EQ(0, memory->index);
3887 TraceMemoryOperation(false, memtype.representation(), index, offset,
3888 position);
3889 }
3890
3891 return load;
3892}
3893
3894Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoadTransform(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory,
3895 wasm::ValueType type, MachineType memtype,
3896 wasm::LoadTransformationKind transform,
3897 Node* index, uintptr_t offset,
3898 uint32_t alignment,
3899 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3900 has_simd_ = true;
3901
3902 // Wasm semantics throw on OOB. Introduce explicit bounds check and
3903 // conditioning when not using the trap handler.
3904
3905 // Load extends always load 8 bytes.
3906 uint8_t access_size = transform == wasm::LoadTransformationKind::kExtend
3907 ? 8
3908 : memtype.MemSize();
3909 BoundsCheckResult bounds_check_result;
3910 std::tie(index, bounds_check_result) = BoundsCheckMem(
3911 memory, access_size, index, offset, position,
3912 EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck, AlignmentCheck::kNo);
3913
3914 LoadTransformation transformation = GetLoadTransformation(memtype, transform);
3915 MemoryAccessKind load_kind = GetMemoryAccessKind(
3916 mcgraph_, memtype.representation(), bounds_check_result);
3917
3918 Node* load = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
3919 mcgraph()->machine()->LoadTransform(load_kind, transformation),
3920 MemBuffer(memory->index, offset), index, effect(), control()));
3921
3922 if (load_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
3923 SetSourcePosition(load, position);
3924 }
3925
3926 if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory) {
3927 // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
3928 CHECK_EQ(0, memory->index);
3929 TraceMemoryOperation(false, memtype.representation(), index, offset,
3930 position);
3931 }
3932 return load;
3933}
3934
3935Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoadMem(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory,
3936 wasm::ValueType type, MachineType memtype,
3937 Node* index, uintptr_t offset,
3938 uint32_t alignment,
3939 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3940 if (memtype.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
3941 has_simd_ = true;
3942 }
3943
3944 // Wasm semantics throw on OOB. Introduce explicit bounds check and
3945 // conditioning when not using the trap handler.
3946 BoundsCheckResult bounds_check_result;
3947 std::tie(index, bounds_check_result) = BoundsCheckMem(
3948 memory, memtype.MemSize(), index, offset, position,
3949 EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck, AlignmentCheck::kNo);
3950
3951 Node* mem_start = MemBuffer(memory->index, offset);
3952 Node* load;
3953 switch (GetMemoryAccessKind(mcgraph_, memtype.representation(),
3954 bounds_check_result)) {
3955 case MemoryAccessKind::kUnaligned:
3956 load = gasm_->LoadUnaligned(memtype, mem_start, index);
3957 break;
3958 case MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler:
3959 load = gasm_->ProtectedLoad(memtype, mem_start, index);
3960 SetSourcePosition(load, position);
3961 break;
3962 case MemoryAccessKind::kNormal:
3963 load = gasm_->Load(memtype, mem_start, index);
3964 break;
3965 }
3966
3967#if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
3968 load = BuildChangeEndiannessLoad(load, memtype, type);
3969#endif
3970
3971 if (type == wasm::kWasmI64 &&
3972 ElementSizeInBytes(memtype.representation()) < 8) {
3973 // TODO(titzer): TF zeroes the upper bits of 64-bit loads for subword sizes.
3974 load = memtype.IsSigned()
3975 ? gasm_->ChangeInt32ToInt64(load) // sign extend
3976 : gasm_->ChangeUint32ToUint64(load); // zero extend
3977 }
3978
3979 if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory) {
3980 // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
3981 CHECK_EQ(0, memory->index);
3982 TraceMemoryOperation(false, memtype.representation(), index, offset,
3983 position);
3984 }
3985
3986 return load;
3987}
3988
3989void WasmGraphBuilder::StoreLane(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory,
3990 MachineRepresentation mem_rep, Node* index,
3991 uintptr_t offset, uint32_t alignment,
3992 Node* val, uint8_t laneidx,
3993 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
3994 wasm::ValueType type) {
3995 has_simd_ = true;
3996 BoundsCheckResult bounds_check_result;
3997 std::tie(index, bounds_check_result) = BoundsCheckMem(
3998 memory, i::ElementSizeInBytes(mem_rep), index, offset, position,
3999 wasm::kPartialOOBWritesAreNoops ? EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck
4000 : EnforceBoundsCheck::kNeedsBoundsCheck,
4001 AlignmentCheck::kNo);
4002 MemoryAccessKind load_kind =
4003 GetMemoryAccessKind(mcgraph_, mem_rep, bounds_check_result);
4004
4005 Node* store = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
4006 mcgraph()->machine()->StoreLane(load_kind, mem_rep, laneidx),
4007 MemBuffer(memory->index, offset), index, val, effect(), control()));
4008
4009 if (load_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
4010 SetSourcePosition(store, position);
4011 }
4012 if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory) {
4013 // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
4014 CHECK_EQ(0, memory->index);
4015 TraceMemoryOperation(true, mem_rep, index, offset, position);
4016 }
4017}
4018
4019void WasmGraphBuilder::StoreMem(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory,
4020 MachineRepresentation mem_rep, Node* index,
4021 uintptr_t offset, uint32_t alignment, Node* val,
4022 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
4023 wasm::ValueType type) {
4024 if (mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4025 has_simd_ = true;
4026 }
4027
4028 BoundsCheckResult bounds_check_result;
4029 std::tie(index, bounds_check_result) = BoundsCheckMem(
4030 memory, i::ElementSizeInBytes(mem_rep), index, offset, position,
4031 wasm::kPartialOOBWritesAreNoops ? EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck
4032 : EnforceBoundsCheck::kNeedsBoundsCheck,
4033 AlignmentCheck::kNo);
4034
4035#if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
4036 val = BuildChangeEndiannessStore(val, mem_rep, type);
4037#endif
4038
4039 Node* mem_start = MemBuffer(memory->index, offset);
4040 switch (GetMemoryAccessKind(mcgraph_, mem_rep, bounds_check_result)) {
4041 case MemoryAccessKind::kUnaligned:
4042 gasm_->StoreUnaligned(UnalignedStoreRepresentation{mem_rep}, mem_start,
4043 index, val);
4044 break;
4045 case MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler: {
4046 Node* store = gasm_->ProtectedStore(mem_rep, mem_start, index, val);
4047 SetSourcePosition(store, position);
4048 if (mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4049 graph()->RecordSimdStore(store);
4050 }
4051 break;
4052 }
4053 case MemoryAccessKind::kNormal: {
4054 Node* store = gasm_->Store(StoreRepresentation{mem_rep, kNoWriteBarrier},
4055 mem_start, index, val);
4056 if (mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4057 graph()->RecordSimdStore(store);
4058 }
4059 break;
4060 }
4061 }
4062
4063 if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_memory) {
4064 // TODO(14259): Implement memory tracing for multiple memories.
4065 CHECK_EQ(0, memory->index);
4066 TraceMemoryOperation(true, mem_rep, index, offset, position);
4067 }
4068}
4069
4070Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType type, Node* index) {
4071 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instance_cache_);
4072 DCHECK_EQ(1, env_->module->memories.size());
4073 Node* mem_start = MemStart(0);
4074 Node* mem_size = MemSize(0);
4075
4076 // Asm.js semantics are defined in terms of typed arrays, hence OOB
4077 // reads return {undefined} coerced to the result type (0 for integers, NaN
4078 // for float and double).
4079 // Note that we check against the memory size ignoring the size of the
4080 // stored value, which is conservative if misaligned. Technically, asm.js
4081 // should never have misaligned accesses.
4082 // Technically, we should do a signed 32-to-ptr extension here. However,
4083 // that is an explicit instruction, whereas unsigned extension is implicit.
4084 // Since the difference is only observable for memories larger than 2 GiB,
4085 // and since we disallow such memories, we can use unsigned extension.
4086 index = gasm_->BuildChangeUint32ToUintPtr(index);
4087 Diamond bounds_check(graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
4088 gasm_->UintLessThan(index, mem_size), BranchHint::kTrue);
4089 bounds_check.Chain(control());
4090
4091 Node* load = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Load(type), mem_start,
4092 index, effect(), bounds_check.if_true);
4093 SetEffectControl(bounds_check.EffectPhi(load, effect()), bounds_check.merge);
4094
4095 Node* oob_value;
4096 switch (type.representation()) {
4097 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
4098 case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
4099 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
4100 oob_value = Int32Constant(0);
4101 break;
4102 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
4103 oob_value = Int64Constant(0);
4104 break;
4105 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
4106 oob_value = Float32Constant(std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN());
4107 break;
4108 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
4109 oob_value = Float64Constant(std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN());
4110 break;
4111 default:
4112 UNREACHABLE();
4113 }
4114
4115 return bounds_check.Phi(type.representation(), load, oob_value);
4116}
4117
4118Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType type, Node* index,
4119 Node* val) {
4120 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instance_cache_);
4121 DCHECK_EQ(1, env_->module->memories.size());
4122 Node* mem_start = MemStart(0);
4123 Node* mem_size = MemSize(0);
4124
4125 // Asm.js semantics are to ignore OOB writes.
4126 // Note that we check against the memory size ignoring the size of the
4127 // stored value, which is conservative if misaligned. Technically, asm.js
4128 // should never have misaligned accesses.
4129 // See {BuildAsmJsLoadMem} for background on using an unsigned extension
4130 // here.
4131 index = gasm_->BuildChangeUint32ToUintPtr(index);
4132 Diamond bounds_check(graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
4133 gasm_->UintLessThan(index, mem_size), BranchHint::kTrue);
4134 bounds_check.Chain(control());
4135
4136 const Operator* store_op = mcgraph()->machine()->Store(StoreRepresentation(
4137 type.representation(), WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier));
4138 Node* store = graph()->NewNode(store_op, mem_start, index, val, effect(),
4139 bounds_check.if_true);
4140 SetEffectControl(bounds_check.EffectPhi(store, effect()), bounds_check.merge);
4141 return val;
4142}

4199
4200template <typename T>
4201Signature<MachineRepresentation>* CreateMachineSignature(
4202 Zone* zone, const Signature<T>* sig, wasm::CallOrigin origin) {
4203 Signature<MachineRepresentation>::Builder builder(zone, sig->return_count(),
4204 sig->parameter_count());
4205 for (auto ret : sig->returns()) {
4206 if (origin == wasm::kCalledFromJS) {
4207 builder.AddReturn(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4208 } else {
4209 builder.AddReturn(ret.machine_representation());
4210 }
4211 }
4212
4213 for (auto param : sig->parameters()) {
4214 if (origin == wasm::kCalledFromJS) {
4215 // Parameters coming from JavaScript are always tagged values. Especially
4216 // when the signature says that it's an I64 value, then a BigInt object is
4217 // provided by JavaScript, and not two 32-bit parameters.
4218 builder.AddParam(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4219 } else {
4220 builder.AddParam(param.machine_representation());
4221 }
4222 }
4223 return builder.Get();
4224}
4225
4226template Signature<MachineRepresentation>* CreateMachineSignature(
4227 Zone*, const Signature<wasm::ValueType>*, wasm::CallOrigin);
4228template Signature<MachineRepresentation>* CreateMachineSignature(
4229 Zone*, const Signature<wasm::CanonicalValueType>*, wasm::CallOrigin);
4230
4231void WasmGraphBuilder::LowerInt64(Signature<MachineRepresentation>* sig) {
4232 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is64()) return;
4233 Int64Lowering r(mcgraph()->graph(), mcgraph()->machine(), mcgraph()->common(),
4234 gasm_->simplified(), mcgraph()->zone(), sig);
4235 r.LowerGraph();
4236}
4237
4238void WasmGraphBuilder::LowerInt64(wasm::CallOrigin origin) {
4239 Signature<MachineRepresentation>* machine_sig =
4240 function_sig_ != nullptr
4241 ? CreateMachineSignature(mcgraph()->zone(), function_sig_, origin)
4242 : CreateMachineSignature(mcgraph()->zone(), wrapper_sig_, origin);
4243 LowerInt64(machine_sig);
4244}
4245
4246Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildChangeInt64ToBigInt(Node* input,
4247 StubCallMode stub_mode) {
4248 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is64()) {
4249 return gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kI64ToBigInt, Operator::kEliminatable,
4250 input);
4251 } else {
4252 Node* low_word = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(input);
4253 Node* high_word = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(
4254 gasm_->Word64Shr(input, gasm_->Int32Constant(32)));
4255 return gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kI32PairToBigInt,
4256 Operator::kEliminatable, low_word, high_word);
4257 }
4258}
4259
4260void WasmGraphBuilder::SetSourcePosition(Node* node,
4261 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
4262 DCHECK_NE(position, wasm::kNoCodePosition);
4263 if (source_position_table_) {
4264 source_position_table_->SetSourcePosition(
4265 node, SourcePosition(position, inlining_id_));
4266 }
4267}

4275 has_simd_ = true;
4276 switch (opcode) {
4277 case wasm::kExprF64x2Splat:
4278 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Splat(), inputs[0]);
4279 case wasm::kExprF64x2Abs:
4280 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Abs(), inputs[0]);
4281 case wasm::kExprF64x2Neg:
4282 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Neg(), inputs[0]);

4285 case wasm::kExprF64x2Add:

4294 case wasm::kExprF64x2Div:

4296 inputs[1]);
4297 case wasm::kExprF64x2Min:

4299 inputs[1]);
4300 case wasm::kExprF64x2Max:
4301 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Max(), inputs[0],
4302 inputs[1]);
4303 case wasm::kExprF64x2Eq:
4304 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Eq(), inputs[0],
4305 inputs[1]);
4306 case wasm::kExprF64x2Ne:
4307 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Ne(), inputs[0],
4308 inputs[1]);

4311 inputs[1]);
