4927
4928Node* WasmGraphBuilder::SimdLaneOp(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode, uint8_t lane,
4929 Node* const* inputs) {
4930 has_simd_ = true;
4931 switch (opcode) {
4932 case wasm::kExprF64x2ExtractLane:
4933 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2ExtractLane(lane),
4934 inputs[0]);
4935 case wasm::kExprF64x2ReplaceLane:
4936 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2ReplaceLane(lane),
4937 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
4938 case wasm::kExprF32x4ExtractLane:
4939 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4ExtractLane(lane),
4940 inputs[0]);
4941 case wasm::kExprF32x4ReplaceLane:
4942 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4ReplaceLane(lane),
4943 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
4944 case wasm::kExprI64x2ExtractLane:
4945 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I64x2ExtractLane(lane),
4946 inputs[0]);
4947 case wasm::kExprI64x2ReplaceLane:
4948 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I64x2ReplaceLane(lane),
4949 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
4950 case wasm::kExprI32x4ExtractLane:
4951 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4ExtractLane(lane),
4952 inputs[0]);
4953 case wasm::kExprI32x4ReplaceLane:
4954 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4ReplaceLane(lane),
4955 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
4956 case wasm::kExprI16x8ExtractLaneS:
4957 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I16x8ExtractLaneS(lane),
4958 inputs[0]);
4959 case wasm::kExprI16x8ExtractLaneU:
4960 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I16x8ExtractLaneU(lane),
4961 inputs[0]);
4962 case wasm::kExprI16x8ReplaceLane:
4963 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I16x8ReplaceLane(lane),
4964 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
4965 case wasm::kExprI8x16ExtractLaneS:
4966 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I8x16ExtractLaneS(lane),
4967 inputs[0]);
4968 case wasm::kExprI8x16ExtractLaneU:
4969 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I8x16ExtractLaneU(lane),
4970 inputs[0]);
4971 case wasm::kExprI8x16ReplaceLane:
4972 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I8x16ReplaceLane(lane),
4973 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
4974 default:
4975 FATAL_UNSUPPORTED_OPCODE(opcode);
4976 }
4977}
4978
4979Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Simd8x16ShuffleOp(const uint8_t shuffle[16],
4980 Node* const* inputs) {
4981 has_simd_ = true;
4982 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I8x16Shuffle(shuffle),
4983 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
4984}
4985
4986Node* WasmGraphBuilder::AtomicOp(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory,
4987 wasm::WasmOpcode opcode, Node* const* inputs,
4988 uint32_t alignment, uintptr_t offset,
4989 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
4990 struct AtomicOpInfo {
4991 enum Type : int8_t {
4992 kNoInput = 0,
4993 kOneInput = 1,
4994 kTwoInputs = 2,
4995 kSpecial
4996 };
4997
4998 using OperatorByAtomicOpParams =
4999 const Operator* (MachineOperatorBuilder::*)(AtomicOpParameters);
5000 using OperatorByAtomicLoadRep =
5001 const Operator* (MachineOperatorBuilder::*)(AtomicLoadParameters);
5002 using OperatorByAtomicStoreRep =
5003 const Operator* (MachineOperatorBuilder::*)(AtomicStoreParameters);
5004
5005 const Type type;
5006 const MachineType machine_type;
5007 const OperatorByAtomicOpParams operator_by_type = nullptr;
5008 const OperatorByAtomicLoadRep operator_by_atomic_load_params = nullptr;
5009 const OperatorByAtomicStoreRep operator_by_atomic_store_rep = nullptr;
5010 const wasm::ValueType wasm_type;
5011
5012 constexpr AtomicOpInfo(Type t, MachineType m, OperatorByAtomicOpParams o)
5013 : type(t), machine_type(m), operator_by_type(o) {}
5014 constexpr AtomicOpInfo(Type t, MachineType m, OperatorByAtomicLoadRep o,
5015 wasm::ValueType v)
5016 : type(t),
5017 machine_type(m),
5018 operator_by_atomic_load_params(o),
5019 wasm_type(v) {}
5020 constexpr AtomicOpInfo(Type t, MachineType m, OperatorByAtomicStoreRep o,
5021 wasm::ValueType v)
5022 : type(t),
5023 machine_type(m),
5024 operator_by_atomic_store_rep(o),
5025 wasm_type(v) {}
5026
5027 // Constexpr, hence just a table lookup in most compilers.
5028 static constexpr AtomicOpInfo Get(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
5029 switch (opcode) {
5030#define CASE(Name, Type, MachType, Op) \
5031 case wasm::kExpr##Name: \
5032 return {Type, MachineType::MachType(), &MachineOperatorBuilder::Op};
5033#define CASE_LOAD_STORE(Name, Type, MachType, Op, WasmType) \
5034 case wasm::kExpr##Name: \
5035 return {Type, MachineType::MachType(), &MachineOperatorBuilder::Op, \
5036 WasmType};
5037
5038 // Binops.
5039 CASE(I32AtomicAdd, kOneInput, Uint32, Word32AtomicAdd)
5040 CASE(I64AtomicAdd, kOneInput, Uint64, Word64AtomicAdd)
5041 CASE(I32AtomicAdd8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word32AtomicAdd)
5042 CASE(I32AtomicAdd16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word32AtomicAdd)
5043 CASE(I64AtomicAdd8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word64AtomicAdd)
5044 CASE(I64AtomicAdd16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word64AtomicAdd)
5045 CASE(I64AtomicAdd32U, kOneInput, Uint32, Word64AtomicAdd)
5046 CASE(I32AtomicSub, kOneInput, Uint32, Word32AtomicSub)
5047 CASE(I64AtomicSub, kOneInput, Uint64, Word64AtomicSub)
5048 CASE(I32AtomicSub8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word32AtomicSub)
5049 CASE(I32AtomicSub16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word32AtomicSub)
5050 CASE(I64AtomicSub8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word64AtomicSub)
5051 CASE(I64AtomicSub16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word64AtomicSub)
5052 CASE(I64AtomicSub32U, kOneInput, Uint32, Word64AtomicSub)
5053 CASE(I32AtomicAnd, kOneInput, Uint32, Word32AtomicAnd)
5054 CASE(I64AtomicAnd, kOneInput, Uint64, Word64AtomicAnd)
5055 CASE(I32AtomicAnd8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word32AtomicAnd)
5056 CASE(I32AtomicAnd16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word32AtomicAnd)
5057 CASE(I64AtomicAnd8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word64AtomicAnd)
5058 CASE(I64AtomicAnd16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word64AtomicAnd)
5059 CASE(I64AtomicAnd32U, kOneInput, Uint32, Word64AtomicAnd)
5060 CASE(I32AtomicOr, kOneInput, Uint32, Word32AtomicOr)
5061 CASE(I64AtomicOr, kOneInput, Uint64, Word64AtomicOr)
5062 CASE(I32AtomicOr8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word32AtomicOr)
5063 CASE(I32AtomicOr16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word32AtomicOr)
5064 CASE(I64AtomicOr8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word64AtomicOr)
5065 CASE(I64AtomicOr16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word64AtomicOr)
5066 CASE(I64AtomicOr32U, kOneInput, Uint32, Word64AtomicOr)
5067 CASE(I32AtomicXor, kOneInput, Uint32, Word32AtomicXor)
5068 CASE(I64AtomicXor, kOneInput, Uint64, Word64AtomicXor)
5069 CASE(I32AtomicXor8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word32AtomicXor)
5070 CASE(I32AtomicXor16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word32AtomicXor)
5071 CASE(I64AtomicXor8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word64AtomicXor)
5072 CASE(I64AtomicXor16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word64AtomicXor)
5073 CASE(I64AtomicXor32U, kOneInput, Uint32, Word64AtomicXor)
5074 CASE(I32AtomicExchange, kOneInput, Uint32, Word32AtomicExchange)
5075 CASE(I64AtomicExchange, kOneInput, Uint64, Word64AtomicExchange)
5076 CASE(I32AtomicExchange8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word32AtomicExchange)
5077 CASE(I32AtomicExchange16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word32AtomicExchange)
5078 CASE(I64AtomicExchange8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word64AtomicExchange)
5079 CASE(I64AtomicExchange16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word64AtomicExchange)
5080 CASE(I64AtomicExchange32U, kOneInput, Uint32, Word64AtomicExchange)
5081
5082 // Compare-exchange.
5083 CASE(I32AtomicCompareExchange, kTwoInputs, Uint32,
5084 Word32AtomicCompareExchange)
5085 CASE(I64AtomicCompareExchange, kTwoInputs, Uint64,
5086 Word64AtomicCompareExchange)
5087 CASE(I32AtomicCompareExchange8U, kTwoInputs, Uint8,
5088 Word32AtomicCompareExchange)
5089 CASE(I32AtomicCompareExchange16U, kTwoInputs, Uint16,
5090 Word32AtomicCompareExchange)
5091 CASE(I64AtomicCompareExchange8U, kTwoInputs, Uint8,
5092 Word64AtomicCompareExchange)
5093 CASE(I64AtomicCompareExchange16U, kTwoInputs, Uint16,
5094 Word64AtomicCompareExchange)
5095 CASE(I64AtomicCompareExchange32U, kTwoInputs, Uint32,
5096 Word64AtomicCompareExchange)
5097
5098 // Load.
5099 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I32AtomicLoad, kNoInput, Uint32, Word32AtomicLoad,
5100 wasm::kWasmI32)
5101 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I64AtomicLoad, kNoInput, Uint64, Word64AtomicLoad,
5102 wasm::kWasmI64)
5103 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I32AtomicLoad8U, kNoInput, Uint8, Word32AtomicLoad,
5104 wasm::kWasmI32)
5105 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I32AtomicLoad16U, kNoInput, Uint16, Word32AtomicLoad,
5106 wasm::kWasmI32)
5107 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I64AtomicLoad8U, kNoInput, Uint8, Word64AtomicLoad,
5108 wasm::kWasmI64)
5109 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I64AtomicLoad16U, kNoInput, Uint16, Word64AtomicLoad,
5110 wasm::kWasmI64)
5111 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I64AtomicLoad32U, kNoInput, Uint32, Word64AtomicLoad,
5112 wasm::kWasmI64)
5113
5114 // Store.
5115 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I32AtomicStore, kOneInput, Uint32, Word32AtomicStore,
5116 wasm::kWasmI32)
5117 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I64AtomicStore, kOneInput, Uint64, Word64AtomicStore,
5118 wasm::kWasmI64)
5119 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I32AtomicStore8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word32AtomicStore,
5120 wasm::kWasmI32)
5121 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I32AtomicStore16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word32AtomicStore,
5122 wasm::kWasmI32)
5123 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I64AtomicStore8U, kOneInput, Uint8, Word64AtomicStore,
5124 wasm::kWasmI64)
5125 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I64AtomicStore16U, kOneInput, Uint16, Word64AtomicStore,
5126 wasm::kWasmI64)
5127 CASE_LOAD_STORE(I64AtomicStore32U, kOneInput, Uint32, Word64AtomicStore,
5128 wasm::kWasmI64)
5129
5130#undef CASE
5131#undef CASE_LOAD_STORE
5132
5133 case wasm::kExprAtomicNotify:
5134 return {kSpecial, MachineType::Int32(),
5135 OperatorByAtomicOpParams{nullptr}};
5136 case wasm::kExprI32AtomicWait:
5137 return {kSpecial, MachineType::Int32(),
5138 OperatorByAtomicOpParams{nullptr}};
5139 case wasm::kExprI64AtomicWait:
5140 return {kSpecial, MachineType::Int64(),
5141 OperatorByAtomicOpParams{nullptr}};
5142 default:
5143 UNREACHABLE();
5144 }
5145 }
5146 };
5147
5148 AtomicOpInfo info = AtomicOpInfo::Get(opcode);
5149
5150 const auto enforce_bounds_check = info.type != AtomicOpInfo::kSpecial
5151 ? EnforceBoundsCheck::kCanOmitBoundsCheck
5152 : EnforceBoundsCheck::kNeedsBoundsCheck;
5153 Node* index;
5154 BoundsCheckResult bounds_check_result;
5155 // Atomic operations need bounds checks until the backend can emit protected
5156 // loads. Independently, an alignemnt check is needed as well.
5157 std::tie(index, bounds_check_result) =
5158 BoundsCheckMem(memory, info.machine_type.MemSize(), inputs[0], offset,
5159 position, enforce_bounds_check, AlignmentCheck::kYes);
5160 // MemoryAccessKind::kUnaligned is impossible due to explicit aligment check.
5161 MemoryAccessKind access_kind =
5162 bounds_check_result == BoundsCheckResult::kTrapHandler
5163 ? MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler
5164 : MemoryAccessKind::kNormal;
5165
5166 if (info.type != AtomicOpInfo::kSpecial) {
5167 const Operator* op;
5168 if (info.operator_by_type) {
5169 op = (mcgraph()->machine()->*info.operator_by_type)(
5170 AtomicOpParameters(info.machine_type,
5171 access_kind));
5172 } else if (info.operator_by_atomic_load_params) {
5173 op = (mcgraph()->machine()->*info.operator_by_atomic_load_params)(
5174 AtomicLoadParameters(info.machine_type, AtomicMemoryOrder::kSeqCst,
5175 access_kind));
5176 } else {
5177 op = (mcgraph()->machine()->*info.operator_by_atomic_store_rep)(
5178 AtomicStoreParameters(info.machine_type.representation(),
5179 WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier,
5180 AtomicMemoryOrder::kSeqCst,
5181 access_kind));
5182 }
5183
5184 Node* input_nodes[6] = {MemBuffer(memory->index, offset), index};
5185 int num_actual_inputs = info.type;
5186 std::copy_n(inputs + 1, num_actual_inputs, input_nodes + 2);
5187 input_nodes[num_actual_inputs + 2] = effect();
5188 input_nodes[num_actual_inputs + 3] = control();
5189
5190#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
5191 // Reverse the value bytes before storing.
5192 if (info.operator_by_atomic_store_rep) {
5193 input_nodes[num_actual_inputs + 1] = BuildChangeEndiannessStore(
5194 input_nodes[num_actual_inputs + 1],
5195 info.machine_type.representation(), info.wasm_type);
5196 }
5197#endif
5198
5199 Node* result = gasm_->AddNode(
5200 graph()->NewNode(op, num_actual_inputs + 4, input_nodes));
5201
5202 if (access_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
5203 SetSourcePosition(result, position);
5204 }
5205
5206#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
5207 // Reverse the value bytes after load.
5208 if (info.operator_by_atomic_load_params) {
5209 result =
5210 BuildChangeEndiannessLoad(result, info.machine_type, info.wasm_type);
5211 }
5212#endif
5213
5214 return result;
5215 }
5216
5217 Node* memory_index = gasm_->Int32Constant(memory->index);
5218 Node* effective_offset = gasm_->IntAdd(gasm_->UintPtrConstant(offset), index);
5219
5220 switch (opcode) {
5221 case wasm::kExprAtomicNotify: {
5222 Node* function =
5223 gasm_->ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::wasm_atomic_notify());
5224 auto sig = FixedSizeSignature<MachineType>::Returns(MachineType::Int32())
5225 .Params(MachineType::Pointer(), MachineType::Uint32());
5226
5227 Node* addr = gasm_->IntAdd(MemStart(memory->index), effective_offset);
5228 Node* num_waiters_to_wake = inputs[1];
5229
5230 return BuildCCall(&sig, function, addr, num_waiters_to_wake);
5231 }
5232
5233 case wasm::kExprI32AtomicWait: {
5234 constexpr StubCallMode kStubMode = StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub;
5235 auto* call_descriptor = GetBuiltinCallDescriptor(
5236 Builtin::kWasmI32AtomicWait, zone_, kStubMode);
5237
5238 Builtin target = Builtin::kWasmI32AtomicWait;
5239 Node* call_target = mcgraph()->RelocatableWasmBuiltinCallTarget(target);
5240
5241 return gasm_->Call(call_descriptor, call_target, memory_index,
5242 effective_offset, inputs[1],
5243 BuildChangeInt64ToBigInt(inputs[2], kStubMode));
5244 }
5245
5246 case wasm::kExprI64AtomicWait: {
5247 constexpr StubCallMode kStubMode = StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub;
5248 auto* call_descriptor = GetBuiltinCallDescriptor(
5249 Builtin::kWasmI64AtomicWait, zone_, kStubMode);
5250
5251 Builtin target = Builtin::kWasmI64AtomicWait;
5252 Node* call_target = mcgraph()->RelocatableWasmBuiltinCallTarget(target);
5253
5254 return gasm_->Call(call_descriptor, call_target, memory_index,
5255 effective_offset,
5256 BuildChangeInt64ToBigInt(inputs[1], kStubMode),
5257 BuildChangeInt64ToBigInt(inputs[2], kStubMode));
5258 }
5259
5260 default:
5261 FATAL_UNSUPPORTED_OPCODE(opcode);
5262 }
5263}
5264
5265void WasmGraphBuilder::AtomicFence() {
5266 SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
5267 mcgraph()->machine()->MemoryBarrier(AtomicMemoryOrder::kSeqCst), effect(),
5268 control()));
5269}
5270
5271void WasmGraphBuilder::MemoryInit(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory,
5272 uint32_t data_segment_index, Node* dst,
5273 Node* src, Node* size,
5274 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5275 // The data segment index must be in bounds since it is required by
5276 // validation.
5277 DCHECK_LT(data_segment_index, env_->module->num_declared_data_segments);
5278
5279 Node* function =
5280 gasm_->ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::wasm_memory_init());
5281
5282 MemTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(memory->address_type, {&dst}, position);
5283
5284 auto sig = FixedSizeSignature<MachineType>::Returns(MachineType::Int32())
5285 .Params(MachineType::Pointer(), MachineType::Uint32(),
5286 MachineType::UintPtr(), MachineType::Uint32(),
5287 MachineType::Uint32(), MachineType::Uint32());
5288 Node* call = BuildCCall(&sig, function, GetInstanceData(),
5289 gasm_->Int32Constant(memory->index), dst, src,
5290 gasm_->Uint32Constant(data_segment_index), size);
5291
5292 // TODO(manoskouk): Also throw kDataSegmentOutOfBounds.
5293 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, call, position);
5294}
5295
5296void WasmGraphBuilder::DataDrop(uint32_t data_segment_index,
5297 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5298 DCHECK_LT(data_segment_index, env_->module->num_declared_data_segments);
5299
5300 Node* seg_size_array =
5301 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(DataSegmentSizes, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
5302 static_assert(wasm::kV8MaxWasmDataSegments <= kMaxUInt32 >> 2);
5303 auto access = ObjectAccess(MachineType::Int32(), kNoWriteBarrier);
5304 gasm_->StoreToObject(
5305 access, seg_size_array,
5306 wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedUInt32Array(
5307 data_segment_index),
5308 Int32Constant(0));
5309}
5310
5311Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StoreArgsInStackSlot(
5312 std::initializer_list<std::pair<MachineRepresentation, Node*>> args) {
5313 int slot_size = 0;
5314 for (auto arg : args) {
5315 slot_size += ElementSizeInBytes(arg.first);
5316 }
5317 DCHECK_LT(0, slot_size);
5318 Node* stack_slot =
5319 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->StackSlot(slot_size));
5320
5321 int offset = 0;
5322 for (auto arg : args) {
5323 MachineRepresentation type = arg.first;
5324 Node* value = arg.second;
5325 gasm_->StoreUnaligned(type, stack_slot, Int32Constant(offset), value);
5326 offset += ElementSizeInBytes(type);
5327 }
5328 return stack_slot;
5329}
5330
5331void WasmGraphBuilder::MemTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(
5332 wasm::AddressType address_type, std::initializer_list<Node**> nodes,
5333 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5334 MemOrTableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(address_type, nodes, position,
5335 wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
5336}
5337
5338void WasmGraphBuilder::TableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(
5339 wasm::AddressType address_type, std::initializer_list<Node**> nodes,
5340 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5341 MemOrTableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(address_type, nodes, position,
5342 wasm::kTrapTableOutOfBounds);
5343}
5344
5345void WasmGraphBuilder::MemOrTableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(
5346 wasm::AddressType address_type, std::initializer_list<Node**> nodes,
5347 wasm::WasmCodePosition position, wasm::TrapReason trap_reason) {
5348 if (address_type == wasm::AddressType::kI32) {
5349 for (Node** node : nodes) {
5350 *node = gasm_->BuildChangeUint32ToUintPtr(*node);
5351 }
5352 return;
5353 }
5354 if constexpr (Is64()) return;
5355 Node* any_high_word = nullptr;
5356 for (Node** node : nodes) {
5357 Node* high_word =
5358 gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(gasm_->Word64Shr(*node, Int32Constant(32)));
5359 any_high_word =
5360 any_high_word ? gasm_->Word32Or(any_high_word, high_word) : high_word;
5361 // Only keep the low word as uintptr_t.
5362 *node = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(*node);
5363 }
5364 TrapIfTrue(trap_reason, any_high_word, position);
5365}
5366
5367void WasmGraphBuilder::MemoryCopy(const wasm::WasmMemory* dst_memory,
5368 const wasm::WasmMemory* src_memory, Node* dst,
5369 Node* src, Node* size,
5370 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5371 Node* function =
5372 gasm_->ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::wasm_memory_copy());
5373
5374 if (dst_memory->address_type == src_memory->address_type) {
5375 MemTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(dst_memory->address_type, {&dst, &src, &size},
5376 position);
5377 } else {
5378 MemTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(dst_memory->address_type, {&dst}, position);
5379 MemTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(src_memory->address_type, {&src}, position);
5380 wasm::AddressType min_address_type =
5381 dst_memory->is_memory64() && src_memory->is_memory64()
5382 ? wasm::AddressType::kI64
5383 : wasm::AddressType::kI32;
5384 MemTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(min_address_type, {&size}, position);
5385 }
5386
5387 auto sig = FixedSizeSignature<MachineType>::Returns(MachineType::Int32())
5388 .Params(MachineType::Pointer(), MachineType::Uint32(),
5389 MachineType::Uint32(), MachineType::UintPtr(),
5390 MachineType::UintPtr(), MachineType::UintPtr());
5391
5392 Node* call =
5393 BuildCCall(&sig, function, GetInstanceData(),
5394 gasm_->Int32Constant(dst_memory->index),
5395 gasm_->Int32Constant(src_memory->index), dst, src, size);
5396 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, call, position);
5397}
5398
5399void WasmGraphBuilder::MemoryFill(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory, Node* dst,
5400 Node* value, Node* size,
5401 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5402 Node* function =
5403 gasm_->ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::wasm_memory_fill());
5404
5405 MemTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(memory->address_type, {&dst, &size}, position);
5406
5407 auto sig = FixedSizeSignature<MachineType>::Returns(MachineType::Int32())
5408 .Params(MachineType::Pointer(), MachineType::Uint32(),
5409 MachineType::UintPtr(), MachineType::Uint8(),
5410 MachineType::UintPtr());
5411 Node* call =
5412 BuildCCall(&sig, function, GetInstanceData(),
5413 gasm_->Int32Constant(memory->index), dst, value, size);
5414 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, call, position);
5415}
5416
5417void WasmGraphBuilder::TableInit(uint32_t table_index,
5418 uint32_t elem_segment_index, Node* dst,
5419 Node* src, Node* size,
5420 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5421 const wasm::WasmTable& table = env_->module->tables[table_index];
5422 TableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(table.address_type, {&dst}, position);
5423 gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
5424 Builtin::kWasmTableInit, Operator::kNoThrow, dst, src, size,
5425 gasm_->NumberConstant(table_index),
5426 gasm_->NumberConstant(elem_segment_index), gasm_->Int32Constant(0));
5427}
5428
5429void WasmGraphBuilder::ElemDrop(uint32_t elem_segment_index,
5430 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5431 // The elem segment index must be in bounds since it is required by
5432 // validation.
5433 DCHECK_LT(elem_segment_index, env_->module->elem_segments.size());
5434
5435 Node* elem_segments =
5436 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(ElementSegments, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
5437 gasm_->StoreFixedArrayElement(
5438 elem_segments, elem_segment_index,
5439 LOAD_ROOT(EmptyFixedArray, empty_fixed_array),
5440 ObjectAccess(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), kFullWriteBarrier));
5441}
5442
5443void WasmGraphBuilder::TableCopy(uint32_t table_dst_index,
5444 uint32_t table_src_index, Node* dst, Node* src,
5445 Node* size, wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5446 const wasm::WasmTable& table_dst = env_->module->tables[table_dst_index];
5447 const wasm::WasmTable& table_src = env_->module->tables[table_src_index];
5448 // TODO(crbug.com/338024338): Merge the `TableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap` calls
5449 // into one. This would result in smaller graphs because we would have a
5450 // single `TrapIf` node that uses the combined high words of `dst`, `src`, and
5451 // `size`.
5452 TableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(table_dst.address_type, {&dst}, position);
5453 TableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(table_src.address_type, {&src}, position);
5454 wasm::AddressType min_address_type =
5455 table_src.is_table64() && table_dst.is_table64()
5456 ? wasm::AddressType::kI64
5457 : wasm::AddressType::kI32;
5458 TableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(min_address_type, {&size}, position);
5459 gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
5460 Builtin::kWasmTableCopy, Operator::kNoThrow, dst, src, size,
5461 gasm_->NumberConstant(table_dst_index),
5462 gasm_->NumberConstant(table_src_index), gasm_->NumberConstant(0));
5463}
5464
5465Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TableGrow(uint32_t table_index, Node* value,
5466 Node* delta,
5467 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5468 const wasm::WasmTable& table = env_->module->tables[table_index];
5469 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
5470
5471 // If `delta` is OOB, return -1.
5472 if (!table.is_table64()) {
5473 delta = gasm_->BuildChangeUint32ToUintPtr(delta);
5474 } else if constexpr (!Is64()) {
5475 Node* high_word =
5476 gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(gasm_->Word64Shr(delta, Int32Constant(32)));
5477 gasm_->GotoIf(high_word, &done, Int32Constant(-1));
5478 delta = gasm_->TruncateInt64ToInt32(delta);
5479 }
5480
5481 Node* result =
5482 gasm_->BuildChangeSmiToInt32(gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
5483 Builtin::kWasmTableGrow, Operator::kNoThrow,
5484 gasm_->NumberConstant(table_index), delta, gasm_->Int32Constant(0),
5485 value));
5486 gasm_->Goto(&done, result);
5487
5488 gasm_->Bind(&done);
5489 result = done.PhiAt(0);
5490
5491 return table.is_table64() ? gasm_->ChangeInt32ToInt64(result) : result;
5492}
5493
5494Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TableSize(uint32_t table_index) {
5495 Node* tables = LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(Tables, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
5496 Node* table = gasm_->LoadFixedArrayElementAny(tables, table_index);
5497
5498 int length_field_size = WasmTableObject::kCurrentLengthOffsetEnd -
5499 WasmTableObject::kCurrentLengthOffset + 1;
5500 Node* length_smi = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
5501 assert_size(length_field_size, MachineType::TaggedSigned()), table,
5502 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTableObject::kCurrentLengthOffset));
5503 Node* length32 = gasm_->BuildChangeSmiToInt32(length_smi);
5504 return env_->module->tables[table_index].is_table64()
5505 ? gasm_->ChangeInt32ToInt64(length32)
5506 : length32;
5507}
5508
5509void WasmGraphBuilder::TableFill(uint32_t table_index, Node* start, Node* value,
5510 Node* count, wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5511 const wasm::WasmTable& table = env_->module->tables[table_index];
5512 TableTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(table.address_type, {&start, &count}, position);
5513 gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
5514 Builtin::kWasmTableFill, Operator::kNoThrow, start, count,
5515 gasm_->Int32Constant(false), gasm_->NumberConstant(table_index), value);
5516}
5517
5518Node* WasmGraphBuilder::DefaultValue(wasm::ValueType type) {
5519 DCHECK(type.is_defaultable());
5520 switch (type.kind()) {
5521 case wasm::kI8:
5522 case wasm::kI16:
5523 case wasm::kI32:
5524 return Int32Constant(0);
5525 case wasm::kI64:
5526 return Int64Constant(0);
5527 case wasm::kF16:
5528 case wasm::kF32:
5529 return Float32Constant(0);
5530 case wasm::kF64:
5531 return Float64Constant(0);
5532 case wasm::kS128:
5533 return S128Zero();
5534 case wasm::kRefNull:
5535 return RefNull(type);
5536 case wasm::kRtt:
5537 case wasm::kVoid:
5538 case wasm::kTop:
5539 case wasm::kBottom:
5540 case wasm::kRef:
5541 UNREACHABLE();
5542 }
5543}
5544
5545Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StructNew(wasm::ModuleTypeIndex struct_index,
5546 const wasm::StructType* type, Node* rtt,
5547 base::Vector<Node*> fields) {
5548 int size = WasmStruct::Size(type);
5549 Node* s = gasm_->Allocate(size);
5550 gasm_->StoreMap(s, rtt);
5551 gasm_->InitializeImmutableInObject(
5552 ObjectAccess(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), kNoWriteBarrier), s,
5553 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(JSReceiver::kPropertiesOrHashOffset),
5554 LOAD_ROOT(EmptyFixedArray, empty_fixed_array));
5555 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < type->field_count(); i++) {
5556 gasm_->StructSet(s, fields[i], type, i, kWithoutNullCheck);
5557 }
5558 // If this assert fails then initialization of padding field might be
5559 // necessary.
5560 static_assert(Heap::kMinObjectSizeInTaggedWords == 2 &&
5561 WasmStruct::kHeaderSize == 2 * kTaggedSize,
5562 "empty struct might require initialization of padding field");
5563 return s;
5564}
5565
5566Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayNew(wasm::ModuleTypeIndex array_index,
5567 const wasm::ArrayType* type, Node* length,
5568 Node* initial_value, Node* rtt,
5569 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5570 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapArrayTooLarge,
5571 gasm_->Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
5572 length, gasm_->Uint32Constant(WasmArray::MaxLength(type))),
5573 position);
5574 wasm::ValueType element_type = type->element_type();
5575
5576 // RoundUp(length * value_size, kObjectAlignment) =
5577 // RoundDown(length * value_size + kObjectAlignment - 1,
5578 // kObjectAlignment);
5579 Node* padded_length = gasm_->Word32And(
5580 gasm_->Int32Add(
5581 gasm_->Int32Mul(length,
5582 Int32Constant(element_type.value_kind_size())),
5583 Int32Constant(kObjectAlignment - 1)),
5584 Int32Constant(-kObjectAlignment));
5585 Node* a = gasm_->Allocate(
5586 gasm_->Int32Add(padded_length, Int32Constant(WasmArray::kHeaderSize)));
5587
5588 // Initialize the array header.
5589 gasm_->StoreMap(a, rtt);
5590 gasm_->InitializeImmutableInObject(
5591 ObjectAccess(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), kNoWriteBarrier), a,
5592 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(JSReceiver::kPropertiesOrHashOffset),
5593 LOAD_ROOT(EmptyFixedArray, empty_fixed_array));
5594 gasm_->ArrayInitializeLength(a, length);
5595
5596 ArrayFillImpl(a, gasm_->Int32Constant(0),
5597 initial_value != nullptr
5598 ? initial_value
5599 : SetType(DefaultValue(element_type),
5600 type->element_type().Unpacked()),
5601 length, type, false);
5602
5603 return a;
5604}
5605
5606Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayNewFixed(const wasm::ArrayType* type, Node* rtt,
5607 base::Vector<Node*> elements) {
5608 wasm::ValueType element_type = type->element_type();
5609 Node* array = gasm_->Allocate(RoundUp(element_type.value_kind_size() *
5610 static_cast<int>(elements.size()),
5611 kObjectAlignment) +
5612 WasmArray::kHeaderSize);
5613 gasm_->StoreMap(array, rtt);
5614 gasm_->InitializeImmutableInObject(
5615 ObjectAccess(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), kNoWriteBarrier), array,
5616 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(JSReceiver::kPropertiesOrHashOffset),
5617 LOAD_ROOT(EmptyFixedArray, empty_fixed_array));
5618 gasm_->ArrayInitializeLength(
5619 array, SetType(Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(elements.size())),
5620 wasm::kWasmI32));
5621 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(elements.size()); i++) {
5622 gasm_->ArraySet(array, gasm_->Int32Constant(i), elements[i], type);
5623 }
5624 return array;
5625}
5626
5627Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayNewSegment(uint32_t segment_index, Node* offset,
5628 Node* length, Node* rtt,
5629 bool is_element,
5630 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5631 // This call cannot be marked as eliminatable because it performs an array
5632 // maximum size check.
5633 Node* array = gasm_->CallBuiltin(
5634 Builtin::kWasmArrayNewSegment, Operator::kNoProperties,
5635 gasm_->Uint32Constant(segment_index), offset, length,
5636 gasm_->SmiConstant(is_element ? 1 : 0), gasm_->SmiConstant(0), rtt);
5637 SetSourcePosition(array, position);
5638 return array;
5639}
5640
5641// TODO(jkummerow): This check would be more elegant if we made
5642// {ArrayNewSegment} a high-level node that's lowered later.
5643bool IsArrayNewSegment(Node* node) {
5644 if (node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kCall) return false;
5645 Node* callee = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
5646 if (callee->opcode() != IrOpcode::kNumberConstant) return false;
5647 double target = OpParameter<double>(callee->op());
5648 return target == static_cast<double>(Builtin::kWasmArrayNewSegment);
5649}
5650
5651void WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayInitSegment(uint32_t segment_index, Node* array,
5652 Node* array_index, Node* segment_offset,
5653 Node* length, bool is_element,
5654 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5655 gasm_->CallBuiltin(
5656 Builtin::kWasmArrayInitSegment, Operator::kNoProperties, array_index,
5657 segment_offset, length, gasm_->SmiConstant(segment_index),
5658 gasm_->SmiConstant(is_element ? 1 : 0), gasm_->SmiConstant(0), array);
5659 SetSourcePosition(control(), position);
5660}

5662Node* WasmGraphBuilder::RttCanon(wasm::ModuleTypeIndex type_index) {
5663 Node* rtt = graph()->NewNode(gasm_->simplified()->RttCanon(type_index),
5664 GetInstanceData());
5665 return SetType(rtt, wasm::ValueType::Rtt(type_index));
5666}
5667
5668WasmGraphBuilder::Callbacks WasmGraphBuilder::TestCallbacks(
5669 GraphAssemblerLabel<1>* label) {
5670 return {// succeed_if
5671 [this, label](Node* condition, BranchHint hint) -> void {
5672 gasm_->GotoIf(condition, label, hint, Int32Constant(1));
5673 },
5674 // fail_if
5675 [this, label](Node* condition, BranchHint hint) -> void {
5676 gasm_->GotoIf(condition, label, hint, Int32Constant(0));
5677 },
5678 // fail_if_not
5679 [this, label](Node* condition, BranchHint hint) -> void {
5680 gasm_->GotoIfNot(condition, label, hint, Int32Constant(0));
5681 }};
5682}
5683
5684WasmGraphBuilder::Callbacks WasmGraphBuilder::CastCallbacks(
5685 GraphAssemblerLabel<0>* label, wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5686 return {// succeed_if
5687 [this, label](Node* condition, BranchHint hint) -> void {
5688 gasm_->GotoIf(condition, label, hint);
5689 },
5690 // fail_if
5691 [this, position](Node* condition, BranchHint hint) -> void {
5692 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapIllegalCast, condition, position);
5693 },
5694 // fail_if_not
5695 [this, position](Node* condition, BranchHint hint) -> void {
5696 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapIllegalCast, condition, position);
5697 }};
5698}
5699
5700WasmGraphBuilder::Callbacks WasmGraphBuilder::BranchCallbacks(
5701 SmallNodeVector& no_match_controls, SmallNodeVector& no_match_effects,
5702 SmallNodeVector& match_controls, SmallNodeVector& match_effects) {
5703 return {
5704 // succeed_if
5705 [&](Node* condition, BranchHint hint) -> void {
5706 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Branch(hint),
5707 condition, control());
5708 match_controls.emplace_back(
5709 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfTrue(), branch));
5710 match_effects.emplace_back(effect());
5711 SetControl(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfFalse(), branch));
5712 },
5713 // fail_if
5714 [&](Node* condition, BranchHint hint) -> void {
5715 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Branch(hint),
5716 condition, control());
5717 no_match_controls.emplace_back(
5718 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfTrue(), branch));
5719 no_match_effects.emplace_back(effect());
5720 SetControl(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfFalse(), branch));
5721 },
5722 // fail_if_not
5723 [&](Node* condition, BranchHint hint) -> void {
5724 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Branch(hint),
5725 condition, control());
5726 no_match_controls.emplace_back(
5727 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfFalse(), branch));
5728 no_match_effects.emplace_back(effect());
5729 SetControl(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfTrue(), branch));
5730 }};
5731}
5732
5733void WasmGraphBuilder::EqCheck(Node* object, bool object_can_be_null,
5734 Callbacks callbacks, bool null_succeeds) {
5735 if (object_can_be_null) {
5736 if (null_succeeds) {
5737 callbacks.succeed_if(IsNull(object, wasm::kWasmAnyRef),
5738 BranchHint::kFalse);
5739 } else {
5740 // The {IsDataRefMap} check below will fail for {null} anyway.
5741 }
5742 }
5743 callbacks.succeed_if(gasm_->IsSmi(object), BranchHint::kFalse);
5744 Node* map = gasm_->LoadMap(object);
5745 callbacks.fail_if_not(gasm_->IsDataRefMap(map), BranchHint::kTrue);
5746}
5747
5748void WasmGraphBuilder::ManagedObjectInstanceCheck(Node* object,
5749 bool object_can_be_null,
5750 InstanceType instance_type,
5751 Callbacks callbacks,
5752 bool null_succeeds) {
5753 if (object_can_be_null) {
5754 if (null_succeeds) {
5755 callbacks.succeed_if(IsNull(object, wasm::kWasmAnyRef),
5756 BranchHint::kFalse);
5757 } else {
5758 // The {IsDataRefMap} check below will fail for {null} anyway.
5759 }
5760 }
5761 callbacks.fail_if(gasm_->IsSmi(object), BranchHint::kFalse);
5762 callbacks.fail_if_not(gasm_->HasInstanceType(object, instance_type),
5763 BranchHint::kTrue);
5764}
5765
5766void WasmGraphBuilder::StringCheck(Node* object, bool object_can_be_null,
5767 Callbacks callbacks, bool null_succeeds) {
5768 if (object_can_be_null) {
5769 if (null_succeeds) {
5770 callbacks.succeed_if(IsNull(object, wasm::kWasmAnyRef),
5771 BranchHint::kFalse);
5772 } else {
5773 // The {IsDataRefMap} check below will fail for {null} anyway.
5774 }
5775 }
5776 callbacks.fail_if(gasm_->IsSmi(object), BranchHint::kFalse);
5777 Node* map = gasm_->LoadMap(object);
5778 Node* instance_type = gasm_->LoadInstanceType(map);
5779 Node* check = gasm_->Uint32LessThan(
5780 instance_type, gasm_->Uint32Constant(FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE));
5781 callbacks.fail_if_not(check, BranchHint::kTrue);
5782}
5783
5784WasmGraphBuilder::ResultNodesOfBr WasmGraphBuilder::BrOnCastAbs(
5785 std::function<void(Callbacks)> type_checker) {
5786 SmallNodeVector no_match_controls, no_match_effects, match_controls,
5787 match_effects;
5788 Node *match_control, *match_effect, *no_match_control, *no_match_effect;
5789
5790 type_checker(BranchCallbacks(no_match_controls, no_match_effects,
5791 match_controls, match_effects));
5792
5793 match_controls.emplace_back(control());
5794 match_effects.emplace_back(effect());
5795
5796 // Wire up the control/effect nodes.
5797 DCHECK_EQ(match_controls.size(), match_effects.size());
5798 unsigned match_count = static_cast<unsigned>(match_controls.size());
5799 if (match_count == 1) {
5800 match_control = match_controls[0];
5801 match_effect = match_effects[0];
5802 } else {
5803 match_control = Merge(match_count, match_controls.data());
5804 // EffectPhis need their control dependency as an additional input.
5805 match_effects.emplace_back(match_control);
5806 match_effect = EffectPhi(match_count, match_effects.data());
5807 }
5808
5809 DCHECK_EQ(no_match_controls.size(), no_match_effects.size());
5810 unsigned no_match_count = static_cast<unsigned>(no_match_controls.size());
5811 if (no_match_count == 1) {
5812 no_match_control = no_match_controls[0];
5813 no_match_effect = no_match_effects[0];
5814 } else {
5815 // Range is 2..4, so casting to unsigned is safe.
5816 no_match_control = Merge(no_match_count, no_match_controls.data());
5817 // EffectPhis need their control dependency as an additional input.
5818 no_match_effects.emplace_back(no_match_control);
5819 no_match_effect = EffectPhi(no_match_count, no_match_effects.data());
5820 }
5821
5822 return {match_control, match_effect, no_match_control, no_match_effect};
5823}

5852
5853WasmGraphBuilder::ResultNodesOfBr WasmGraphBuilder::BrOnCast(
5854 Node* object, Node* rtt, WasmTypeCheckConfig config) {
5855 auto [true_node, false_node] =
5856 BranchNoHint(gasm_->WasmTypeCheck(object, rtt, config));
5857
5858 return {true_node, // control on match
5859 effect(), // effect on match
5860 false_node, // control on no match
5861 effect()}; // effect on no match
5862}
5863
5864WasmGraphBuilder::ResultNodesOfBr WasmGraphBuilder::BrOnEq(
5865 Node* object, Node* /*rtt*/, WasmTypeCheckConfig config) {
5866 return BrOnCastAbs([this, config, object](Callbacks callbacks) -> void {
5867 if (config.from.is_nullable()) {
5868 if (config.to.is_nullable()) {
5869 callbacks.succeed_if(gasm_->IsNull(object, config.from),
5870 BranchHint::kFalse);
5871 } else {
5872 // The {IsDataRefMap} check below will fail for {null}.
5873 }
5874 }
5875 callbacks.succeed_if(gasm_->IsSmi(object), BranchHint::kFalse);
5876 Node* map = gasm_->LoadMap(object);
5877 callbacks.fail_if_not(gasm_->IsDataRefMap(map), BranchHint::kTrue);
5878 });
5879}

5881WasmGraphBuilder::ResultNodesOfBr WasmGraphBuilder::BrOnStruct(
5882 Node* object, Node* /*rtt*/, WasmTypeCheckConfig config) {
5883 bool null_succeeds = config.to.is_nullable();
5884 return BrOnCastAbs(
5885 [this, object, config, null_succeeds](Callbacks callbacks) -> void {
5886 return ManagedObjectInstanceCheck(object, config.from.is_nullable(),
5887 WASM_STRUCT_TYPE, callbacks,
5888 null_succeeds);
5889 });
5890}

5892WasmGraphBuilder::ResultNodesOfBr WasmGraphBuilder::BrOnArray(

5894 bool null_succeeds = config.to.is_nullable();
5895 return BrOnCastAbs(
5896 [this, config, object, null_succeeds](Callbacks callbacks) -> void {
5897 return ManagedObjectInstanceCheck(object, config.from.is_nullable(),
5898 WASM_ARRAY_TYPE, callbacks,
5899 null_succeeds);
5900 });
5901}
5902
5903WasmGraphBuilder::ResultNodesOfBr WasmGraphBuilder::BrOnI31(
5904 Node* object, Node* /* rtt */, WasmTypeCheckConfig config) {
5905 return BrOnCastAbs([this, object, config](Callbacks callbacks) -> void {
5906 if (config.from.is_nullable()) {
5907 if (config.to.is_nullable()) {
5908 callbacks.succeed_if(gasm_->IsNull(object, config.from),
5909 BranchHint::kFalse);
5910 } else {
5911 // Covered by the {IsSmi} check below.
5912 }
5913 }
5914 callbacks.fail_if_not(gasm_->IsSmi(object), BranchHint::kTrue);
5915 });
5916}

5918WasmGraphBuilder::ResultNodesOfBr WasmGraphBuilder::BrOnString(

5920 bool null_succeeds = config.to.is_nullable();
5921 return BrOnCastAbs(
5922 [this, config, object, null_succeeds](Callbacks callbacks) -> void {
5923 return StringCheck(object, config.from.is_nullable(), callbacks,
5924 null_succeeds);
5925 });
5926}

5955
5956void WasmGraphBuilder::BoundsCheckArray(Node* array, Node* index,
5957 CheckForNull null_check,
5958 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5959 if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.experimental_wasm_skip_bounds_checks)) {
5960 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
5961 AssertNotNull(array, wasm::kWasmArrayRef, position);
5962 }
5963 } else {
5964 Node* length = gasm_->ArrayLength(array, null_check);
5965 SetSourcePosition(length, position);
5966 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds,
5967 gasm_->Uint32LessThan(index, length), position);
5968 }
5969}
5970
5971void WasmGraphBuilder::BoundsCheckArrayWithLength(
5972 Node* array, Node* index, Node* length, CheckForNull null_check,
5973 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5974 if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.experimental_wasm_skip_bounds_checks)) return;
5975 Node* array_length = gasm_->ArrayLength(array, null_check);
5976 SetSourcePosition(array_length, position);
5977 Node* range_end = gasm_->Int32Add(index, length);
5978 Node* range_valid = gasm_->Word32And(
5979 // OOB if (index + length > array.len).
5980 gasm_->Uint32LessThanOrEqual(range_end, array_length),
5981 // OOB if (index + length) overflows.
5982 gasm_->Uint32LessThanOrEqual(index, range_end));
5983 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds, range_valid, position);
5984}
5985
5986Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayGet(Node* array_object,
5987 const wasm::ArrayType* type, Node* index,
5988 CheckForNull null_check, bool is_signed,
5989 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5990 BoundsCheckArray(array_object, index, null_check, position);
5991 return gasm_->ArrayGet(array_object, index, type, is_signed);
5992}
5993
5994void WasmGraphBuilder::ArraySet(Node* array_object, const wasm::ArrayType* type,
5995 Node* index, Node* value,
5996 CheckForNull null_check,
5997 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5998 BoundsCheckArray(array_object, index, null_check, position);
5999 gasm_->ArraySet(array_object, index, value, type);
6000}
6001
6002Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayLen(Node* array_object, CheckForNull null_check,
6003 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
6004 Node* result = gasm_->ArrayLength(array_object, null_check);
6005 SetSourcePosition(result, position);
6006 return result;
6007}
6008
6009void WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayCopy(Node* dst_array, Node* dst_index,
6010 CheckForNull dst_null_check, Node* src_array,
6011 Node* src_index, CheckForNull src_null_check,
6012 Node* length,
6013 const wasm::ArrayType* array_type,
6014 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
6015 BoundsCheckArrayWithLength(dst_array, dst_index, length, dst_null_check,
6016 position);
6017 BoundsCheckArrayWithLength(src_array, src_index, length, src_null_check,
6018 position);
6019
6020 auto end = gasm_->MakeLabel();
6021
6022 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->Word32Equal(length, Int32Constant(0)), &end);
6023
6024 auto builtin = gasm_->MakeLabel();
6025
6026 // Values determined by test/mjsunit/wasm/array-copy-benchmark.js on x64.
6027 int array_copy_max_loop_length;
6028 switch (array_type->element_type().kind()) {
6029 case wasm::kI32:
6030 case wasm::kI64:
6031 case wasm::kI8:
6032 case wasm::kI16:
6033 array_copy_max_loop_length = 20;
6034 break;
6035 case wasm::kF16:
6036 case wasm::kF32:
6037 case wasm::kF64:
6038 array_copy_max_loop_length = 35;
6039 break;
6040 case wasm::kS128:
6041 array_copy_max_loop_length = 100;
6042 break;
6043 case wasm::kRtt:
6044 case wasm::kRef:
6045 case wasm::kRefNull:
6046 array_copy_max_loop_length = 15;
6047 break;
6048 case wasm::kVoid:
6049 case wasm::kTop:
6050 case wasm::kBottom:
6051 UNREACHABLE();
6052 }
6053
6054 gasm_->GotoIf(
6055 gasm_->Uint32LessThan(Int32Constant(array_copy_max_loop_length), length),
6056 &builtin);
6057
6058 auto reverse = gasm_->MakeLabel();
6059
6060 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->Uint32LessThan(src_index, dst_index), &reverse);
6061
6062 Node* src_end_index = gasm_->Int32Sub(gasm_->Int32Add(src_index, length),
6063 gasm_->Int32Constant(1));
6064 Node* dst_end_index = gasm_->Int32Sub(gasm_->Int32Add(dst_index, length),
6065 gasm_->Int32Constant(1));
6066
6067 {
6068 auto loop = gasm_->MakeLoopLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
6069 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
6070
6071 gasm_->Goto(&loop, src_index, dst_index);
6072 gasm_->Bind(&loop);
6073
6074 Node* value = gasm_->ArrayGet(src_array, loop.PhiAt(0), array_type, false);
6075 gasm_->ArraySet(dst_array, loop.PhiAt(1), value, array_type);
6076
6077 Node* condition = gasm_->Uint32LessThan(loop.PhiAt(0), src_end_index);
6078 gasm_->GotoIfNot(condition, &end);
6079 gasm_->Goto(&loop, gasm_->Int32Add(loop.PhiAt(0), Int32Constant(1)),
6080 gasm_->Int32Add(loop.PhiAt(1), Int32Constant(1)));
6081 }
6082
6083 {
6084 gasm_->Bind(&reverse);
6085 auto loop = gasm_->MakeLoopLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
6086 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
6087
6088 gasm_->Goto(&loop, src_end_index, dst_end_index);
6089 gasm_->Bind(&loop);
6090
6091 Node* value = gasm_->ArrayGet(src_array, loop.PhiAt(0), array_type, false);
6092 gasm_->ArraySet(dst_array, loop.PhiAt(1), value, array_type);
6093
6094 Node* condition = gasm_->Uint32LessThan(src_index, loop.PhiAt(0));
6095 gasm_->GotoIfNot(condition, &end);
6096 gasm_->Goto(&loop, gasm_->Int32Sub(loop.PhiAt(0), Int32Constant(1)),
6097 gasm_->Int32Sub(loop.PhiAt(1), Int32Constant(1)));
6098 }
6099
6100 {
6101 gasm_->Bind(&builtin);
6102 Node* function =
6103 gasm_->ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::wasm_array_copy());
6104 MachineType arg_types[]{MachineType::TaggedPointer(), MachineType::Uint32(),
6105 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), MachineType::Uint32(),
6106 MachineType::Uint32()};
6107 MachineSignature sig(0, 5, arg_types);
6108 BuildCCall(&sig, function, dst_array, dst_index, src_array, src_index,
6109 length);
6110 gasm_->Goto(&end);
6111 }
6112
6113 gasm_->Bind(&end);
6114}
6115
6116Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StoreInInt64StackSlot(Node* value,
6117 wasm::ValueType type) {
6118 Node* value_int64;
6119 switch (type.kind()) {
6120 case wasm::kI32:
6121 case wasm::kI8:
6122 case wasm::kI16:
6123 value_int64 =
6124 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->ChangeInt32ToInt64(), value);
6125 break;
6126 case wasm::kI64:
6127 value_int64 = value;
6128 break;
6129 case wasm::kS128:
6130 // We can only get here if {value} is the constant 0.
6131 DCHECK_EQ(value->opcode(), IrOpcode::kS128Zero);
6132 value_int64 = Int64Constant(0);
6133 break;
6134 case wasm::kF32:
6135 value_int64 = graph()->NewNode(
6136 mcgraph()->machine()->ChangeInt32ToInt64(),
6137 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->BitcastFloat32ToInt32(),
6138 value));
6139 break;
6140 case wasm::kF64:
6141 value_int64 = graph()->NewNode(
6142 mcgraph()->machine()->BitcastFloat64ToInt64(), value);
6143 break;
6144 case wasm::kRefNull:
6145 case wasm::kRef:
6146 value_int64 = kSystemPointerSize == 4
6147 ? graph()->NewNode(
6148 mcgraph()->machine()->ChangeInt32ToInt64(), value)
6149 : value;
6150 break;
6151 case wasm::kF16:
6152 UNIMPLEMENTED();
6153 case wasm::kRtt:
6154 case wasm::kVoid:
6155 case wasm::kTop:
6156 case wasm::kBottom:
6157 UNREACHABLE();
6158 }
6159
6160 return StoreArgsInStackSlot({{MachineRepresentation::kWord64, value_int64}});
6161}
6162
6163void WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayFill(Node* array, Node* index, Node* value,
6164 Node* length, const wasm::ArrayType* type,
6165 CheckForNull null_check,
6166 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
6167 BoundsCheckArrayWithLength(array, index, length, null_check, position);
6168 ArrayFillImpl(array, index, value, length, type,
6169 type->element_type().is_reference());
6170}
6171
6172void WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayFillImpl(Node* array, Node* index, Node* value,
6173 Node* length, const wasm::ArrayType* type,
6174 bool emit_write_barrier) {
6175 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(value);
6176 wasm::ValueType element_type = type->element_type();
6177
6178 // Initialize the array. Use an external function for large arrays with
6179 // null/number initializer. Use a loop for small arrays and reference arrays
6180 // with a non-null initial value.
6181 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel();
6182 // TODO(manoskouk): If the loop is ever removed here, we have to update
6183 // ArrayNew(), ArrayNewDefault(), and ArrayFill() in
6184 // graph-builder-interface.cc to not mark the current loop as non-innermost.
6185 auto loop = gasm_->MakeLoopLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
6186
6187 // The builtin cannot handle s128 values other than 0.
6188 if (!(element_type == wasm::kWasmS128 &&
6189 value->opcode() != IrOpcode::kS128Zero)) {
6190 constexpr uint32_t kArrayNewMinimumSizeForMemSet = 16;
6191 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->Uint32LessThan(
6192 length, Int32Constant(kArrayNewMinimumSizeForMemSet)),
6193 &loop, BranchHint::kNone, index);
6194 Node* function =
6195 gasm_->ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::wasm_array_fill());
6196
6197 Node* stack_slot = StoreInInt64StackSlot(value, element_type);
6198
6199 MachineType arg_types[]{
6200 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), MachineType::Uint32(),
6201 MachineType::Uint32(), MachineType::Uint32(),
6202 MachineType::Uint32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
6203 MachineSignature sig(0, 6, arg_types);
6204 BuildCCall(&sig, function, array, index, length,
6205 Int32Constant(emit_write_barrier ? 1 : 0),
6206 Int32Constant(element_type.raw_bit_field()), stack_slot);
6207 gasm_->Goto(&done);
6208 } else {
6209 gasm_->Goto(&loop, index);
6210 }
6211 gasm_->Bind(&loop);
6212 {
6213 Node* current_index = loop.PhiAt(0);
6214 Node* check =
6215 gasm_->UintLessThan(current_index, gasm_->Int32Add(index, length));
6216 gasm_->GotoIfNot(check, &done);
6217 gasm_->ArraySet(array, current_index, value, type);
6218 current_index = gasm_->Int32Add(current_index, Int32Constant(1));
6219 gasm_->Goto(&loop, current_index);
6220 }
6221 gasm_->Bind(&done);
6222}
6223
6224// General rules for operator properties for builtin calls:
6225// - Use kEliminatable if it can neither throw a catchable exception nor trap.
6226// - Use kNoDeopt | kNoThrow if it can trap (because in that case, eliminating
6227// it would avoid the trap and thereby observably change the code's behavior
6228// compared to its unoptimized version).
6229// - If you don't use kNoThrow (nor kEliminatable which implies it), then you
6230// must also set up control nodes for the throwing case, e.g. by using
6231// WasmGraphBuildingInterface::CheckForException().
6232
6233Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StringNewWtf8(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory,
6234 unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
6235 Node* offset, Node* size,
6236 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
6237 MemTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(memory->address_type, {&offset}, position);
6238 return gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmStringNewWtf8,
6239 Operator::kNoDeopt | Operator::kNoThrow, offset,
6240 size, gasm_->Int32Constant(memory->index),
6241 gasm_->SmiConstant(static_cast<int32_t>(variant)));
6242}
6243
6244Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StringNewWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
6245 Node* array, CheckForNull null_check,
6246 Node* start, Node* end,
6247 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
6248 // Special case: shortcut a sequence "array from data segment" + "string from
6249 // wtf8 array" to directly create a string from the segment.
6250 if (IsArrayNewSegment(array)) {
6251 // We can only pass 3 untagged parameters to the builtin (on 32-bit
6252 // platforms). The segment index is easy to tag: if it validated, it must
6253 // be in Smi range.
6254 Node* segment_index = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(array, 1);
6255 Uint32Matcher index_matcher(segment_index);
6256 DCHECK(index_matcher.HasResolvedValue());
6257 Node* segment_index_smi = gasm_->SmiConstant(index_matcher.ResolvedValue());
6258 // Arbitrary choice for the second tagged parameter: the segment offset.
6259 Node* segment_offset = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(array, 2);
6260 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapDataSegmentOutOfBounds,
6261 gasm_->Uint32LessThan(segment_offset,
6262 gasm_->Uint32Constant(Smi::kMaxValue)),
6263 position);
6264 Node* segment_offset_smi = gasm_->BuildChangeInt32ToSmi(segment_offset);
6265 Node* segment_length = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(array, 3);
6266 Node* variant_smi = gasm_->SmiConstant(static_cast<int32_t>(variant));
6267 return gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmStringFromDataSegment,
6268 Operator::Operator::kNoDeopt | Operator::kNoThrow,
6269 segment_length, start, end, segment_index_smi,
6270 segment_offset_smi, variant_smi);
6271 }
6272
6273 // Regular path if the shortcut wasn't taken.
6274 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
6275 array = AssertNotNull(array, wasm::kWasmArrayRef, position);
6276 }
6277 return gasm_->CallBuiltin(
6278 Builtin::kWasmStringNewWtf8Array, Operator::kNoDeopt | Operator::kNoThrow,
6279 start, end, array, gasm_->SmiConstant(static_cast<int32_t>(variant)));
6280}

6426
6427Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StringEqual(Node* a, wasm::ValueType a_type, Node* b,
6428 wasm::ValueType b_type,
6429 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
6430 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
6431 // Covers "identical string pointer" and "both are null" cases.
6432 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->TaggedEqual(a, b), &done, Int32Constant(1));
6433 if (a_type.is_nullable()) {
6434 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->IsNull(a, a_type), &done, Int32Constant(0));
6435 }
6436 if (b_type.is_nullable()) {
6437 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->IsNull(b, b_type), &done, Int32Constant(0));
6438 }
6439 // TODO(jkummerow): Call Builtin::kStringEqual directly.
6440 gasm_->Goto(&done, gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmStringEqual,
6441 Operator::kEliminatable, a, b));
6442 gasm_->Bind(&done);
6443 return done.PhiAt(0);
6444}

6478void WasmGraphBuilder::StringViewWtf8Encode(
6479 const wasm::WasmMemory* memory, unibrow::Utf8Variant variant, Node* view,

6504
6505Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StringViewWtf16GetCodeUnit(
6506 Node* string, CheckForNull null_check, Node* offset,
6507 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
6508 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
6509 string = AssertNotNull(string, wasm::kWasmStringRef, position);
6510 }
6511 Node* prepare = gasm_->StringPrepareForGetCodeunit(string);
6512 Node* base = gasm_->Projection(0, prepare);
6513 Node* base_offset = gasm_->Projection(1, prepare);
6514 Node* charwidth_shift = gasm_->Projection(2, prepare);
6515
6516 // Bounds check.
6517 Node* length = gasm_->LoadStringLength(string);
6518 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapStringOffsetOutOfBounds,
6519 gasm_->Uint32LessThan(offset, length), position);
6520
6521 auto onebyte = gasm_->MakeLabel();
6522 auto bailout = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
6523 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
6524 gasm_->GotoIf(
6525 gasm_->Word32Equal(charwidth_shift,
6526 gasm_->Int32Constant(kCharWidthBailoutSentinel)),
6527 &bailout);
6528 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->Word32Equal(charwidth_shift, gasm_->Int32Constant(0)),
6529 &onebyte);
6530
6531 // Two-byte.
6532 Node* object_offset =
6533 gasm_->IntAdd(gasm_->IntMul(gasm_->BuildChangeInt32ToIntPtr(offset),
6534 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(2)),
6535 base_offset);
6536 Node* result = gasm_->LoadImmutableFromObject(MachineType::Uint16(), base,
6537 object_offset);
6538 gasm_->Goto(&done, result);
6539
6540 // One-byte.
6541 gasm_->Bind(&onebyte);
6542 object_offset =
6543 gasm_->IntAdd(gasm_->BuildChangeInt32ToIntPtr(offset), base_offset);
6544 result =
6545 gasm_->LoadImmutableFromObject(MachineType::Uint8(), base, object_offset);
6546 gasm_->Goto(&done, result);
6547
6548 gasm_->Bind(&bailout);
6549 gasm_->Goto(&done, gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
6550 Builtin::kWasmStringViewWtf16GetCodeUnit,
6551 Operator::kEliminatable, string, offset));
6552
6553 gasm_->Bind(&done);
6554 // Make sure the original string is kept alive as long as we're operating
6555 // on pointers extracted from it (otherwise e.g. external strings' resources
6556 // might get freed prematurely).
6557 gasm_->Retain(string);
6558 return done.PhiAt(0);
6559}
6560
6561Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StringCodePointAt(Node* string, CheckForNull null_check,
6562 Node* offset,
6563 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
6564 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
6565 string = AssertNotNull(string, wasm::kWasmStringRef, position);
6566 }
6567 Node* prepare = gasm_->StringPrepareForGetCodeunit(string);
6568 Node* base = gasm_->Projection(0, prepare);
6569 Node* base_offset = gasm_->Projection(1, prepare);
6570 Node* charwidth_shift = gasm_->Projection(2, prepare);
6571
6572 // Bounds check.
6573 Node* length = gasm_->LoadStringLength(string);
6574 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapStringOffsetOutOfBounds,
6575 gasm_->Uint32LessThan(offset, length), position);
6576
6577 auto onebyte = gasm_->MakeLabel();
6578 auto bailout = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
6579 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
6580 gasm_->GotoIf(
6581 gasm_->Word32Equal(charwidth_shift,
6582 gasm_->Int32Constant(kCharWidthBailoutSentinel)),
6583 &bailout);
6584 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->Word32Equal(charwidth_shift, gasm_->Int32Constant(0)),
6585 &onebyte);
6586
6587 // Two-byte.
6588 Node* object_offset =
6589 gasm_->IntAdd(gasm_->IntMul(gasm_->BuildChangeInt32ToIntPtr(offset),
6590 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(2)),
6591 base_offset);
6592 Node* lead = gasm_->LoadImmutableFromObject(MachineType::Uint16(), base,
6593 object_offset);
6594 Node* is_lead_surrogate =
6595 gasm_->Word32Equal(gasm_->Word32And(lead, gasm_->Int32Constant(0xFC00)),
6596 gasm_->Int32Constant(0xD800));
6597 gasm_->GotoIfNot(is_lead_surrogate, &done, lead);
6598 Node* trail_offset = gasm_->Int32Add(offset, gasm_->Int32Constant(1));
6599 gasm_->GotoIfNot(gasm_->Uint32LessThan(trail_offset, length), &done, lead);
6600 Node* trail = gasm_->LoadImmutableFromObject(
6601 MachineType::Uint16(), base,
6602 gasm_->IntAdd(object_offset, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(2)));
6603 Node* is_trail_surrogate =
6604 gasm_->WordEqual(gasm_->Word32And(trail, gasm_->Int32Constant(0xFC00)),
6605 gasm_->Int32Constant(0xDC00));
6606 gasm_->GotoIfNot(is_trail_surrogate, &done, lead);
6607 Node* surrogate_bias =
6608 gasm_->Int32Constant(0x10000 - (0xD800 << 10) - 0xDC00);
6609 Node* result =
6610 gasm_->Int32Add(gasm_->Word32Shl(lead, gasm_->Int32Constant(10)),
6611 gasm_->Int32Add(trail, surrogate_bias));
6612 gasm_->Goto(&done, result);
6613
6614 // One-byte.
6615 gasm_->Bind(&onebyte);
6616 object_offset =
6617 gasm_->IntAdd(gasm_->BuildChangeInt32ToIntPtr(offset), base_offset);
6618 result =
6619 gasm_->LoadImmutableFromObject(MachineType::Uint8(), base, object_offset);
6620 gasm_->Goto(&done, result);
6621
6622 gasm_->Bind(&bailout);
6623 gasm_->Goto(&done, gasm_->CallBuiltinThroughJumptable(
6624 Builtin::kWasmStringCodePointAt,
6625 Operator::kEliminatable, string, offset));
6626
6627 gasm_->Bind(&done);
6628 // Make sure the original string is kept alive as long as we're operating
6629 // on pointers extracted from it (otherwise e.g. external strings' resources
6630 // might get freed prematurely).
6631 gasm_->Retain(string);
6632 return done.PhiAt(0);
6633}
6634
6635Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StringViewWtf16Encode(const wasm::WasmMemory* memory,
6636 Node* string,
6637 CheckForNull null_check,
6638 Node* offset, Node* start,
6639 Node* codeunits,
6640 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
6641 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
6642 string = AssertNotNull(string, wasm::kWasmStringRef, position);
6643 }
6644 MemTypeToUintPtrOrOOBTrap(memory->address_type, {&offset}, position);
6645 return gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmStringViewWtf16Encode,
6646 Operator::kNoDeopt | Operator::kNoThrow, offset,
6647 start, codeunits, string,
6648 gasm_->SmiConstant(memory->index));
6649}

6740 // This call traps when the {code_point} is invalid.

6745
6746Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StringHash(Node* string, CheckForNull null_check,
6747 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
6748 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
6749 string = AssertNotNull(string, wasm::kWasmStringRef, position);
6750 }
6751
6752 auto runtime_label = gasm_->MakeLabel();
6753 auto end_label = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
6754
6755 Node* raw_hash = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
6756 MachineType::Int32(), string,
6757 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(offsetof(Name, raw_hash_field_)));
6758 Node* hash_not_computed_mask =
6759 gasm_->Int32Constant(static_cast<int32_t>(Name::kHashNotComputedMask));
6760 static_assert(Name::HashFieldTypeBits::kShift == 0);
6761 Node* hash_not_computed = gasm_->Word32And(raw_hash, hash_not_computed_mask);
6762 gasm_->GotoIf(hash_not_computed, &runtime_label);
6763
6764 // Fast path if hash is already computed: Decode raw hash value.
6765 static_assert(Name::HashBits::kLastUsedBit == kBitsPerInt - 1);
6766 Node* hash = gasm_->Word32Shr(
6767 raw_hash,
6768 gasm_->Int32Constant(static_cast<int32_t>(Name::HashBits::kShift)));
6769 gasm_->Goto(&end_label, hash);
6770
6771 gasm_->Bind(&runtime_label);
6772 Node* hash_runtime = gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmStringHash,
6773 Operator::kEliminatable, string);
6774 gasm_->Goto(&end_label, hash_runtime);
6775
6776 gasm_->Bind(&end_label);
6777 return end_label.PhiAt(0);
6778}
6779
6780void WasmGraphBuilder::BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlagHelper(
6781 Node* thread_in_wasm_flag_address, bool new_value) {
6782 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6783 Node* flag_value =
6784 gasm_->Load(MachineType::Int32(), thread_in_wasm_flag_address, 0);
6785 Node* check =
6786 gasm_->Word32Equal(flag_value, Int32Constant(new_value ? 0 : 1));
6787 Assert(check, new_value ? AbortReason::kUnexpectedThreadInWasmSet
6788 : AbortReason::kUnexpectedThreadInWasmUnset);
6789 }
6790
6791 gasm_->Store({MachineRepresentation::kWord32, kNoWriteBarrier},
6792 thread_in_wasm_flag_address, 0,
6793 Int32Constant(new_value ? 1 : 0));
6794}
6795
6796void WasmGraphBuilder::BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(bool new_value) {
6797 if (!trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled()) return;
6798 Node* isolate_root = BuildLoadIsolateRoot();
6799
6800 Node* thread_in_wasm_flag_address =
6801 gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), isolate_root,
6802 Isolate::thread_in_wasm_flag_address_offset());
6803
6804 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlagHelper(thread_in_wasm_flag_address, new_value);
6805}
6806
6807void WasmGraphBuilder::Assert(Node* condition, AbortReason abort_reason) {
6808 if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
6809
6810 Diamond check(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), condition, BranchHint::kTrue);
6811 check.Chain(control());
6812 SetControl(check.if_false);
6813 Node* message_id = gasm_->NumberConstant(static_cast<int32_t>(abort_reason));
6814 Node* old_effect = effect();
6815 Node* call = BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(
6816 Runtime::kAbort, NoContextConstant(), &message_id, 1);
6817 check.merge->ReplaceInput(1, call);
6818 SetEffectControl(check.EffectPhi(old_effect, effect()), check.merge);
6819}
6820
6821Node* WasmGraphBuilder::WellKnown_StringIndexOf(
6822 Node* string, Node* search, Node* start, CheckForNull string_null_check,
6823 CheckForNull search_null_check) {
6824 if (string_null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
6825 // If string is null, throw.
6826 auto if_not_null = gasm_->MakeLabel();
6827 auto if_null = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
6828 gasm_->GotoIf(IsNull(string, wasm::kWasmStringRef), &if_null);
6829 gasm_->Goto(&if_not_null);
6830 gasm_->Bind(&if_null);
6831 gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kThrowIndexOfCalledOnNull, Operator::kNoWrite);
6832 gasm_->Unreachable();
6833 gasm_->Bind(&if_not_null);
6834 }
6835 if (search_null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
6836 // If search is null, replace it with "null".
6837 auto search_not_null =
6838 gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
6839 gasm_->GotoIfNot(IsNull(search, wasm::kWasmStringRef), &search_not_null,
6840 search);
6841 Node* null_string = LOAD_ROOT(null_string, null_string);
6842 gasm_->Goto(&search_not_null, null_string);
6843 gasm_->Bind(&search_not_null);
6844 search = search_not_null.PhiAt(0);
6845 }
6846 {
6847 // Clamp the start index.
6848 auto clamped_start = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
6849 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->Int32LessThan(start, Int32Constant(0)), &clamped_start,
6850 Int32Constant(0));
6851 Node* length = gasm_->LoadStringLength(string);
6852 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->Int32LessThan(start, length), &clamped_start, start);
6853 gasm_->Goto(&clamped_start, length);
6854 gasm_->Bind(&clamped_start);
6855 start = clamped_start.PhiAt(0);
6856 }
6857
6858 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(false);
6859 // This can't overflow because we've clamped {start} above.
6860 Node* start_smi = gasm_->BuildChangeInt32ToSmi(start);
6861 Node* result =
6862 gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kStringIndexOf, Operator::kEliminatable,
6863 string, search, start_smi);
6864 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
6865 return gasm_->BuildChangeSmiToInt32(result);
6866}
6867
6868Node* WasmGraphBuilder::WellKnown_StringToLocaleLowerCaseStringref(
6869 int func_index, Node* string, Node* locale,
6870 CheckForNull string_null_check) {
6871#if V8_INTL_SUPPORT
6872 if (string_null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
6873 // We can let the builtin throw the exception, but it only checks for
6874 // JS null, so we must externalize any Wasm null here.
6875 // Externalizing the {locale} is not required, because
6876 // {Object::ConvertToString} has been taught how to deal with WasmNull.
6877 string = gasm_->WasmExternConvertAny(string);
6878 }
6879 int param_count = 2; // String, locale.
6880 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = Linkage::GetJSCallDescriptor(
6881 zone_, false, param_count, CallDescriptor::kCanUseRoots,
6882 Operator::kNoDeopt | Operator::kNoWrite);
6883 Node* callees_array =
6884 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(WellKnownImports, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
6885 Node* callee = gasm_->LoadFixedArrayElementPtr(callees_array, func_index);
6886 Node* context = gasm_->LoadContextFromJSFunction(callee);
6887 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(false);
6888 Node* result = gasm_->Call(call_descriptor, callee, string, locale,
6889 UndefinedValue(), // new.target
6890 gasm_->Int32Constant(param_count), // argc
6891 context); // context
6892 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
6893 return result;
6894#else
6895 UNREACHABLE();
6896#endif
6897}
6898
6899Node* WasmGraphBuilder::WellKnown_StringToLowerCaseStringref(
6900 Node* string, CheckForNull null_check) {
6901#if V8_INTL_SUPPORT
6902 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(false);
6903 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
6904 auto if_not_null = gasm_->MakeLabel();
6905 auto if_null = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
6906 gasm_->GotoIf(IsNull(string, wasm::kWasmStringRef), &if_null);
6907 gasm_->Goto(&if_not_null);
6908 gasm_->Bind(&if_null);
6909 gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kThrowToLowerCaseCalledOnNull,
6910 Operator::kNoWrite);
6911 gasm_->Unreachable();
6912 gasm_->Bind(&if_not_null);
6913 }
6914 Node* result =
6915 gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kStringToLowerCaseIntl,
6916 Operator::kEliminatable, string, NoContextConstant());
6917 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
6918 return result;
6919#else
6920 UNREACHABLE();
6921#endif
6922}

6924Node* WasmGraphBuilder::WellKnown_ParseFloat(Node* string,
6925 CheckForNull null_check) {
6926 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
6927 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
6928 auto if_null = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
6929 gasm_->GotoIf(IsNull(string, wasm::kWasmStringRef), &if_null);
6930 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(false);
6931 Node* result = gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmStringToDouble,
6932 Operator::kEliminatable, string);
6933 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
6934 gasm_->Goto(&done, result);
6935 gasm_->Bind(&if_null);
6936 gasm_->Goto(&done,
6937 Float64Constant(std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN()));
6938 gasm_->Bind(&done);
6939 return done.PhiAt(0);
6940 } else {
6941 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(false);
6942 Node* result = gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmStringToDouble,
6943 Operator::kEliminatable, string);
6944 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
6945 return result;
6946 }
6947}

6964
6965Node* WasmGraphBuilder::RefI31(Node* input) {
6966 if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
6967 return gasm_->Word32Shl(input, gasm_->BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant32());
6968 } else {
6969 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits());
6970 // Set the topmost bit to sign-extend the second bit. This way,
6971 // interpretation in JS (if this value escapes there) will be the same as
6972 // i31.get_s.
6973 input = gasm_->BuildChangeInt32ToIntPtr(input);
6974 return gasm_->WordSar(
6975 gasm_->WordShl(input,
6976 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize + 1)),
6977 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(1));
6978 }
6979}
6980
6981Node* WasmGraphBuilder::I31GetS(Node* input, CheckForNull null_check,
6982 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
6983 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
6984 input = AssertNotNull(input, wasm::kWasmI31Ref, position);
6985 }
6986 if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
6987 input = gasm_->BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(input);
6988 return gasm_->Word32SarShiftOutZeros(input,
6989 gasm_->BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant32());
6990 } else {
6991 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits());
6992 // Topmost bit is already sign-extended.
6993 return gasm_->BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(gasm_->WordSar(
6994 input, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize)));
6995 }
6996}
6997
6998Node* WasmGraphBuilder::I31GetU(Node* input, CheckForNull null_check,
6999 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
7000 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
7001 input = AssertNotNull(input, wasm::kWasmI31Ref, position);
7002 }
7003 if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
7004 input = gasm_->BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(input);
7005 return gasm_->Word32Shr(input, gasm_->BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant32());
7006 } else {
7007 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits());
7008 // We need to remove the topmost bit of the 32-bit Smi.
7009 return gasm_->BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(
7010 gasm_->WordShr(gasm_->WordShl(input, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(1)),
7011 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize + 1)));
7012 }
7013}
7014
7015Node* WasmGraphBuilder::SetType(Node* node, wasm::ValueType type) {
7016 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(env_);
7017 if (!compiler::NodeProperties::IsTyped(node)) {
7018 compiler::NodeProperties::SetType(
7019 node, compiler::Type::Wasm(type, env_->module, graph_zone()));
7020 } else {
7021 // We might try to set the type twice since some nodes are cached in the
7022 // graph assembler, but we should never change the type.
7023 // The exception is imported strings support, which may special-case
7024 // values that are officially externref-typed as being known to be strings.
7025#if DEBUG
7026 static constexpr wasm::ValueType kRefExtern =
7027 wasm::ValueType::Ref(wasm::HeapType::kExtern);
7028 DCHECK((compiler::NodeProperties::GetType(node).AsWasm().type == type) ||
7029 (enabled_features_.has_imported_strings() &&
7030 compiler::NodeProperties::GetType(node).AsWasm().type ==
7031 wasm::kWasmRefExternString &&
7032 (type == wasm::kWasmExternRef || type == kRefExtern)));
7033#endif
7034 }
7035 return node;
7036}
7037
7038class WasmDecorator final : public GraphDecorator {
7039 public:
7040 explicit WasmDecorator(NodeOriginTable* origins, wasm::Decoder* decoder)
7041 : origins_(origins), decoder_(decoder) {}
7042
7043 void Decorate(Node* node) final {
7044 origins_->SetNodeOrigin(
7045 node, NodeOrigin("wasm graph creation", "n/a",
7046 NodeOrigin::kWasmBytecode, decoder_->position()));
7047 }
7048
7049 private:
7050 compiler::NodeOriginTable* origins_;
7051 wasm::Decoder* decoder_;
7052};
7053
7054void WasmGraphBuilder::AddBytecodePositionDecorator(
7055 NodeOriginTable* node_origins, wasm::Decoder* decoder) {
7056 DCHECK_NULL(decorator_);
7057 decorator_ = graph()->zone()->New<WasmDecorator>(node_origins, decoder);
7058 graph()->AddDecorator(decorator_);
7059}
7060
7061void WasmGraphBuilder::RemoveBytecodePositionDecorator() {
7062 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(decorator_);
7063 graph()->RemoveDecorator(decorator_);
7064 decorator_ = nullptr;
7065}

7067namespace {
