7069// A non-null {isolate} signifies that the generated code is treated as being in
7070// a JS frame for functions like BuildLoadIsolateRoot().
7071class WasmWrapperGraphBuilder : public WasmGraphBuilder {
7072 public:
7073 WasmWrapperGraphBuilder(Zone* zone, MachineGraph* mcgraph,
7074 const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig,
7075 ParameterMode parameter_mode, Isolate* isolate,
7076 compiler::SourcePositionTable* spt)
7077 : WasmGraphBuilder(nullptr, zone, mcgraph, nullptr, spt, parameter_mode,
7078 isolate, wasm::WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), sig) {}
7079
7080 CallDescriptor* GetBigIntToI64CallDescriptor(bool needs_frame_state) {
7081 return wasm::GetWasmEngine()->call_descriptors()->GetBigIntToI64Descriptor(
7082 needs_frame_state);
7083 }
7084
7085 Node* GetTargetForBuiltinCall(Builtin builtin) {
7086 // Per-process shared wrappers don't have access to a jump table, so they
7087 // can't use kCallWasmRuntimeStub mode.
7088 return gasm_->GetBuiltinPointerTarget(builtin);
7089 }
7090
7091 Node* IsNull(Node* object, wasm::CanonicalValueType type) {
7092 // We immediately lower null in wrappers, as they do not go through a
7093 // lowering phase.
7094 Node* null = type.use_wasm_null() ? LOAD_ROOT(WasmNull, wasm_null)
7095 : LOAD_ROOT(NullValue, null_value);
7096 return gasm_->TaggedEqual(object, null);
7097 }
7098
7099 Node* BuildChangeInt32ToNumber(Node* value) {
7100 // We expect most integers at runtime to be Smis, so it is important for
7101 // wrapper performance that Smi conversion be inlined.
7102 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
7103 return gasm_->BuildChangeInt32ToSmi(value);
7104 }
7105 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
7106
7107 auto builtin = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
7108 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
7109
7110 // Double value to test if value can be a Smi, and if so, to convert it.
7111 Node* add = gasm_->Int32AddWithOverflow(value, value);
7112 Node* ovf = gasm_->Projection(1, add);
7113 gasm_->GotoIf(ovf, &builtin);
7114
7115 // If it didn't overflow, the result is {2 * value} as pointer-sized value.
7116 Node* smi_tagged =
7117 gasm_->BuildChangeInt32ToIntPtr(gasm_->Projection(0, add));
7118 gasm_->Goto(&done, smi_tagged);
7119
7120 // Otherwise, call builtin, to convert to a HeapNumber.
7121 gasm_->Bind(&builtin);
7122 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = mcgraph()->common();
7123 Node* target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(Builtin::kWasmInt32ToHeapNumber);
7124 if (!int32_to_heapnumber_operator_.is_set()) {
7125 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
7126 mcgraph()->zone(), WasmInt32ToHeapNumberDescriptor(), 0,
7127 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties,
7128 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
7129 int32_to_heapnumber_operator_.set(common->Call(call_descriptor));
7130 }
7131 Node* call =
7132 gasm_->Call(int32_to_heapnumber_operator_.get(), target, value);
7133 gasm_->Goto(&done, call);
7134 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7135 return done.PhiAt(0);
7136 }
7137
7138 Node* BuildChangeTaggedToInt32(Node* value, Node* context,
7139 Node* frame_state) {
7140 // We expect most integers at runtime to be Smis, so it is important for
7141 // wrapper performance that Smi conversion be inlined.
7142 auto builtin = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
7143 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
7144
7145 gasm_->GotoIfNot(IsSmi(value), &builtin);
7146
7147 // If Smi, convert to int32.
7148 Node* smi = gasm_->BuildChangeSmiToInt32(value);
7149 gasm_->Goto(&done, smi);
7150
7151 // Otherwise, call builtin which changes non-Smi to Int32.
7152 gasm_->Bind(&builtin);
7153 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = mcgraph()->common();
7154 Node* target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(Builtin::kWasmTaggedNonSmiToInt32);
7155 if (!tagged_non_smi_to_int32_operator_.is_set()) {
7156 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
7157 mcgraph()->zone(), WasmTaggedNonSmiToInt32Descriptor(), 0,
7158 frame_state ? CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState
7159 : CallDescriptor::kNoFlags,
7160 Operator::kNoProperties, StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
7161 tagged_non_smi_to_int32_operator_.set(common->Call(call_descriptor));
7162 }
7163 Node* call = frame_state
7164 ? gasm_->Call(tagged_non_smi_to_int32_operator_.get(),
7165 target, value, context, frame_state)
7166 : gasm_->Call(tagged_non_smi_to_int32_operator_.get(),
7167 target, value, context);
7168 // The source position here is needed for asm.js, see the comment on the
7169 // source position of the call to JavaScript in the wasm-to-js wrapper.
7170 SetSourcePosition(call, 1);
7171 gasm_->Goto(&done, call);
7172 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7173 return done.PhiAt(0);
7174 }
7175
7176 Node* BuildChangeFloat32ToNumber(Node* value) {
7177 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = mcgraph()->common();
7178 Node* target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(Builtin::kWasmFloat32ToNumber);
7179 if (!float32_to_number_operator_.is_set()) {
7180 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
7181 mcgraph()->zone(), WasmFloat32ToNumberDescriptor(), 0,
7182 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties,
7183 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
7184 float32_to_number_operator_.set(common->Call(call_descriptor));
7185 }
7186 return gasm_->Call(float32_to_number_operator_.get(), target, value);
7187 }
7188
7189 Node* BuildChangeFloat64ToNumber(Node* value) {
7190 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = mcgraph()->common();
7191 Node* target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(Builtin::kWasmFloat64ToNumber);
7192 if (!float64_to_number_operator_.is_set()) {
7193 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
7194 mcgraph()->zone(), WasmFloat64ToTaggedDescriptor(), 0,
7195 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties,
7196 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
7197 float64_to_number_operator_.set(common->Call(call_descriptor));
7198 }
7199 return gasm_->Call(float64_to_number_operator_.get(), target, value);
7200 }
7201
7202 Node* BuildChangeTaggedToFloat64(Node* value, Node* context,
7203 Node* frame_state) {
7204 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = mcgraph()->common();
7205 Node* target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(Builtin::kWasmTaggedToFloat64);
7206 bool needs_frame_state = frame_state != nullptr;
7207 if (!tagged_to_float64_operator_.is_set()) {
7208 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
7209 mcgraph()->zone(), WasmTaggedToFloat64Descriptor(), 0,
7210 frame_state ? CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState
7211 : CallDescriptor::kNoFlags,
7212 Operator::kNoProperties, StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
7213 tagged_to_float64_operator_.set(common->Call(call_descriptor));
7214 }
7215 Node* call = needs_frame_state
7216 ? gasm_->Call(tagged_to_float64_operator_.get(), target,
7217 value, context, frame_state)
7218 : gasm_->Call(tagged_to_float64_operator_.get(), target,
7219 value, context);
7220 // The source position here is needed for asm.js, see the comment on the
7221 // source position of the call to JavaScript in the wasm-to-js wrapper.
7222 SetSourcePosition(call, 1);
7223 return call;
7224 }
7225
7226 int AddArgumentNodes(base::Vector<Node*> args, int pos, int param_count,
7227 const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig, Node* context) {
7228 // Convert wasm numbers to JS values and drop the instance node.
7229 for (int i = 0; i < param_count; ++i) {
7230 Node* param = Param(i + 1);
7231 args[pos++] = ToJS(param, sig->GetParam(i), context);
7232 }
7233 return pos;
7234 }
7235
7236 Node* ToJS(Node* node, wasm::CanonicalValueType type, Node* context) {
7237 switch (type.kind()) {
7238 case wasm::kI32:
7239 return BuildChangeInt32ToNumber(node);
7240 case wasm::kI64:
7241 return BuildChangeInt64ToBigInt(node,
7242 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
7243 case wasm::kF32:
7244 return BuildChangeFloat32ToNumber(node);
7245 case wasm::kF64:
7246 return BuildChangeFloat64ToNumber(node);
7247 case wasm::kRef:
7248 switch (type.heap_representation_non_shared()) {
7249 case wasm::HeapType::kEq:
7250 case wasm::HeapType::kI31:
7251 case wasm::HeapType::kStruct:
7252 case wasm::HeapType::kArray:
7253 case wasm::HeapType::kAny:
7254 case wasm::HeapType::kExtern:
7255 case wasm::HeapType::kString:
7256 case wasm::HeapType::kNone:
7257 case wasm::HeapType::kNoFunc:
7258 case wasm::HeapType::kNoExtern:
7259 case wasm::HeapType::kExn:
7260 case wasm::HeapType::kNoExn:
7261 return node;
7262 case wasm::HeapType::kBottom:
7263 case wasm::HeapType::kTop:
7264 case wasm::HeapType::kStringViewWtf8:
7265 case wasm::HeapType::kStringViewWtf16:
7266 case wasm::HeapType::kStringViewIter:
7267 UNREACHABLE();
7268 case wasm::HeapType::kFunc:
7269 default:
7270 if (type.heap_representation_non_shared() ==
7271 wasm::HeapType::kFunc ||
7272 wasm::GetTypeCanonicalizer()->IsFunctionSignature(
7273 type.ref_index())) {
7274 // Function reference. Extract the external function.
7275 auto done =
7276 gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
7277 Node* internal = gasm_->LoadTrustedPointerFromObject(
7278 node,
7279 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
7280 WasmFuncRef::kTrustedInternalOffset),
7281 kWasmInternalFunctionIndirectPointerTag);
7282 Node* maybe_external = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
7283 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), internal,
7284 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
7285 WasmInternalFunction::kExternalOffset));
7286 gasm_->GotoIfNot(
7287 gasm_->TaggedEqual(maybe_external, UndefinedValue()), &done,
7288 maybe_external);
7289 Node* from_builtin = gasm_->CallBuiltin(
7290 Builtin::kWasmInternalFunctionCreateExternal,
7291 Operator::kNoProperties, internal, context);
7292 gasm_->Goto(&done, from_builtin);
7293 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7294 return done.PhiAt(0);
7295 } else {
7296 return node;
7297 }
7298 }
7299 case wasm::kRefNull:
7300 switch (type.heap_representation_non_shared()) {
7301 case wasm::HeapType::kExtern:
7302 case wasm::HeapType::kNoExtern:
7303 case wasm::HeapType::kExn:
7304 case wasm::HeapType::kNoExn:
7305 return node;
7306 case wasm::HeapType::kNone:
7307 case wasm::HeapType::kNoFunc:
7308 return LOAD_ROOT(NullValue, null_value);
7309 case wasm::HeapType::kEq:
7310 case wasm::HeapType::kStruct:
7311 case wasm::HeapType::kArray:
7312 case wasm::HeapType::kString:
7313 case wasm::HeapType::kI31:
7314 case wasm::HeapType::kAny: {
7315 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
7316 gasm_->GotoIfNot(IsNull(node, type), &done, node);
7317 gasm_->Goto(&done, LOAD_ROOT(NullValue, null_value));
7318 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7319 return done.PhiAt(0);
7320 }
7321 case wasm::HeapType::kFunc:
7322 default: {
7323 if (type.heap_representation_non_shared() ==
7324 wasm::HeapType::kFunc ||
7325 wasm::GetTypeCanonicalizer()->IsFunctionSignature(
7326 type.ref_index())) {
7327 // Function reference. Extract the external function.
7328 auto done =
7329 gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
7330 auto null_label = gasm_->MakeLabel();
7331 gasm_->GotoIf(IsNull(node, type), &null_label);
7332 Node* internal = gasm_->LoadTrustedPointerFromObject(
7333 node,
7334 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
7335 WasmFuncRef::kTrustedInternalOffset),
7336 kWasmInternalFunctionIndirectPointerTag);
7337 Node* maybe_external = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
7338 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), internal,
7339 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
7340 WasmInternalFunction::kExternalOffset));
7341 gasm_->GotoIfNot(
7342 gasm_->TaggedEqual(maybe_external, UndefinedValue()), &done,
7343 maybe_external);
7344 Node* from_builtin = gasm_->CallBuiltin(
7345 Builtin::kWasmInternalFunctionCreateExternal,
7346 Operator::kNoProperties, internal, context);
7347 gasm_->Goto(&done, from_builtin);
7348 gasm_->Bind(&null_label);
7349 gasm_->Goto(&done, LOAD_ROOT(NullValue, null_value));
7350 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7351 return done.PhiAt(0);
7352 } else {
7353 auto done =
7354 gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
7355 gasm_->GotoIfNot(IsNull(node, type), &done, node);
7356 gasm_->Goto(&done, LOAD_ROOT(NullValue, null_value));
7357 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7358 return done.PhiAt(0);
7359 }
7360 }
7361 }
7362 case wasm::kRtt:
7363 case wasm::kI8:
7364 case wasm::kI16:
7365 case wasm::kF16:
7366 case wasm::kS128:
7367 case wasm::kVoid:
7368 case wasm::kTop:
7369 case wasm::kBottom:
7370 // If this is reached, then IsJSCompatibleSignature() is too permissive.
7371 UNREACHABLE();
7372 }
7373 }
7374
7375 Node* BuildChangeBigIntToInt64(Node* input, Node* context,
7376 Node* frame_state) {
7377 Node* target;
7378 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is64()) {
7379 target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(Builtin::kBigIntToI64);
7380 } else {
7381 DCHECK(mcgraph()->machine()->Is32());
7382 // On 32-bit platforms we already set the target to the
7383 // BigIntToI32Pair builtin here, so that we don't have to replace the
7384 // target in the int64-lowering.
7385 target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(Builtin::kBigIntToI32Pair);
7386 }
7387
7388 return frame_state ? gasm_->Call(GetBigIntToI64CallDescriptor(true), target,
7389 input, context, frame_state)
7390 : gasm_->Call(GetBigIntToI64CallDescriptor(false),
7391 target, input, context);
7392 }
7393
7394 Node* BuildCheckString(Node* input, Node* js_context,
7395 wasm::CanonicalValueType type) {
7396 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
7397 auto type_error = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
7398 gasm_->GotoIf(IsSmi(input), &type_error, BranchHint::kFalse);
7399 if (type.is_nullable()) {
7400 auto not_null = gasm_->MakeLabel();
7401 gasm_->GotoIfNot(IsNull(input, wasm::kCanonicalExternRef), &not_null);
7402 gasm_->Goto(&done, LOAD_ROOT(WasmNull, wasm_null));
7403 gasm_->Bind(&not_null);
7404 }
7405 Node* map = gasm_->LoadMap(input);
7406 Node* instance_type = gasm_->LoadInstanceType(map);
7407 Node* check = gasm_->Uint32LessThan(
7408 instance_type, gasm_->Uint32Constant(FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE));
7409 gasm_->GotoIf(check, &done, BranchHint::kTrue, input);
7410 gasm_->Goto(&type_error);
7411 gasm_->Bind(&type_error);
7412 BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kWasmThrowJSTypeError, js_context,
7413 nullptr, 0);
7414 TerminateThrow(effect(), control());
7415 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7416 return done.PhiAt(0);
7417 }
7418
7419 Node* FromJS(Node* input, Node* js_context, wasm::CanonicalValueType type,
7420 Node* frame_state = nullptr) {
7421 switch (type.kind()) {
7422 case wasm::kRef:
7423 case wasm::kRefNull: {
7424 switch (type.heap_representation_non_shared()) {
7425 // TODO(14034): Add more fast paths?
7426 case wasm::HeapType::kExtern:
7427 case wasm::HeapType::kExn:
7428 if (type.kind() == wasm::kRef) {
7429 Node* null_value = gasm_->LoadImmutable(
7430 MachineType::Pointer(), gasm_->LoadRootRegister(),
7431 IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kNullValue));
7432 auto throw_label = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
7433 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel();
7434 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->TaggedEqual(input, null_value),
7435 &throw_label);
7436 gasm_->Goto(&done);
7437
7438 gasm_->Bind(&throw_label);
7439 BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kWasmThrowJSTypeError,
7440 js_context, {}, 0);
7441 gasm_->Unreachable();
7442
7443 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7444 }
7445 return input;
7446 case wasm::HeapType::kString:
7447 return BuildCheckString(input, js_context, type);
7448 case wasm::HeapType::kNoExtern:
7449 case wasm::HeapType::kNoExn:
7450 case wasm::HeapType::kNone:
7451 case wasm::HeapType::kNoFunc:
7452 case wasm::HeapType::kI31:
7453 case wasm::HeapType::kAny:
7454 case wasm::HeapType::kFunc:
7455 case wasm::HeapType::kStruct:
7456 case wasm::HeapType::kArray:
7457 case wasm::HeapType::kEq:
7458 default: {
7459 // Make sure CanonicalValueType fits in a Smi.
7460 static_assert(wasm::CanonicalValueType::kLastUsedBit + 1 <=
7461 kSmiValueSize);
7462
7463 Node* inputs[] = {
7464 input, mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(
7465 IntToSmi(static_cast<int>(type.raw_bit_field())))};
7466
7467 return BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kWasmJSToWasmObject,
7468 js_context, inputs, 2);
7469 }
7470 }
7471 }
7472 case wasm::kF32:
7473 return gasm_->TruncateFloat64ToFloat32(
7474 BuildChangeTaggedToFloat64(input, js_context, frame_state));
7475
7476 case wasm::kF64:
7477 return BuildChangeTaggedToFloat64(input, js_context, frame_state);
7478
7479 case wasm::kI32:
7480 return BuildChangeTaggedToInt32(input, js_context, frame_state);
7481
7482 case wasm::kI64:
7483 // i64 values can only come from BigInt.
7484 return BuildChangeBigIntToInt64(input, js_context, frame_state);
7485
7486 case wasm::kRtt:
7487 case wasm::kS128:
7488 case wasm::kI8:
7489 case wasm::kI16:
7490 case wasm::kF16:
7491 case wasm::kTop:
7492 case wasm::kBottom:
7493 case wasm::kVoid:
7494 // If this is reached, then IsJSCompatibleSignature() is too permissive.
7495 UNREACHABLE();
7496 }
7497 }
7498
7499 Node* SmiToFloat32(Node* input) {
7500 return gasm_->RoundInt32ToFloat32(gasm_->BuildChangeSmiToInt32(input));
7501 }
7502
7503 Node* SmiToFloat64(Node* input) {
7504 return gasm_->ChangeInt32ToFloat64(gasm_->BuildChangeSmiToInt32(input));
7505 }
7506
7507 Node* HeapNumberToFloat64(Node* input) {
7508 return gasm_->LoadFromObject(
7509 MachineType::Float64(), input,
7510 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
7511 AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue().offset));
7512 }
7513
7514 Node* FromJSFast(Node* input, wasm::CanonicalValueType type) {
7515 switch (type.kind()) {
7516 case wasm::kI32:
7517 return gasm_->BuildChangeSmiToInt32(input);
7518 case wasm::kF32: {
7519 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kFloat32);
7520 auto heap_number = gasm_->MakeLabel();
7521 gasm_->GotoIfNot(IsSmi(input), &heap_number);
7522 gasm_->Goto(&done, SmiToFloat32(input));
7523 gasm_->Bind(&heap_number);
7524 Node* value =
7525 gasm_->TruncateFloat64ToFloat32(HeapNumberToFloat64(input));
7526 gasm_->Goto(&done, value);
7527 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7528 return done.PhiAt(0);
7529 }
7530 case wasm::kF64: {
7531 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
7532 auto heap_number = gasm_->MakeLabel();
7533 gasm_->GotoIfNot(IsSmi(input), &heap_number);
7534 gasm_->Goto(&done, SmiToFloat64(input));
7535 gasm_->Bind(&heap_number);
7536 gasm_->Goto(&done, HeapNumberToFloat64(input));
7537 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7538 return done.PhiAt(0);
7539 }
7540 case wasm::kRef:
7541 case wasm::kRefNull:
7542 case wasm::kI64:
7543 case wasm::kRtt:
7544 case wasm::kS128:
7545 case wasm::kI8:
7546 case wasm::kI16:
7547 case wasm::kF16:
7548 case wasm::kTop:
7549 case wasm::kBottom:
7550 case wasm::kVoid:
7551 UNREACHABLE();
7552 }
7553 }
7554
7555 class ModifyThreadInWasmFlagScope {
7556 public:
7557 ModifyThreadInWasmFlagScope(
7558 WasmWrapperGraphBuilder* wasm_wrapper_graph_builder,
7559 WasmGraphAssembler* gasm)
7560 : wasm_wrapper_graph_builder_(wasm_wrapper_graph_builder) {
7561 if (!trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled()) return;
7562 Node* isolate_root = wasm_wrapper_graph_builder_->BuildLoadIsolateRoot();
7563
7564 thread_in_wasm_flag_address_ =
7565 gasm->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), isolate_root,
7566 Isolate::thread_in_wasm_flag_address_offset());
7567
7568 wasm_wrapper_graph_builder_->BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlagHelper(
7569 thread_in_wasm_flag_address_, true);
7570 }
7571
7572 ModifyThreadInWasmFlagScope(const ModifyThreadInWasmFlagScope&) = delete;
7573
7574 ~ModifyThreadInWasmFlagScope() {
7575 if (!trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled()) return;
7576
7577 wasm_wrapper_graph_builder_->BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlagHelper(
7578 thread_in_wasm_flag_address_, false);
7579 }
7580
7581 private:
7582 WasmWrapperGraphBuilder* wasm_wrapper_graph_builder_;
7583 Node* thread_in_wasm_flag_address_;
7584 };
7585
7586 Node* BuildMultiReturnFixedArrayFromIterable(const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig,
7587 Node* iterable, Node* context) {
7588 Node* length = gasm_->BuildChangeUint31ToSmi(
7589 mcgraph()->Uint32Constant(static_cast<uint32_t>(sig->return_count())));
7590 return gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kIterableToFixedArrayForWasm,
7591 Operator::kEliminatable, iterable, length,
7592 context);
7593 }
7594
7595 // Generate a call to the AllocateJSArray builtin.
7596 Node* BuildCallAllocateJSArray(Node* array_length, Node* context) {
7597 // Since we don't check that args will fit in an array,
7598 // we make sure this is true based on statically known limits.
7599 static_assert(wasm::kV8MaxWasmFunctionReturns <=
7600 JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray);
7601 return gasm_->CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmAllocateJSArray,
7602 Operator::kEliminatable, array_length, context);
7603 }
7604
7605 Node* BuildCallAndReturn(Node* js_context, Node* function_data,
7606 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args,
7607 bool do_conversion, Node* frame_state,
7608 bool set_in_wasm_flag) {
7609 const int rets_count = static_cast<int>(wrapper_sig_->return_count());
7610 base::SmallVector<Node*, 1> rets(rets_count);
7611
7612 // Set the ThreadInWasm flag before we do the actual call.
7613 {
7614 std::optional<ModifyThreadInWasmFlagScope>
7615 modify_thread_in_wasm_flag_builder;
7616 if (set_in_wasm_flag) {
7617 modify_thread_in_wasm_flag_builder.emplace(this, gasm_.get());
7618 }
7619
7620 // Call to an import or a wasm function defined in this module.
7621 // The (cached) call target is the jump table slot for that function.
7622 // We do not use the imports dispatch table here so that the wrapper is
7623 // target independent, in particular for tier-up.
7624 Node* internal = gasm_->LoadImmutableProtectedPointerFromObject(
7625 function_data, wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
7626 WasmFunctionData::kProtectedInternalOffset));
7627 args[0] = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
7628 MachineType::Uint32(), internal,
7629 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
7630 WasmInternalFunction::kRawCallTargetOffset));
7631 Node* implicit_arg = gasm_->LoadImmutableProtectedPointerFromObject(
7632 internal, wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
7633 WasmInternalFunction::kProtectedImplicitArgOffset));
7634 BuildWasmCall(wrapper_sig_, base::VectorOf(args), base::VectorOf(rets),
7635 wasm::kNoCodePosition, implicit_arg, true, frame_state);
7636 }
7637
7638 Node* jsval;
7639 if (wrapper_sig_->return_count() == 0) {
7640 jsval = UndefinedValue();
7641 } else if (wrapper_sig_->return_count() == 1) {
7642 jsval = !do_conversion
7643 ? rets[0]
7644 : ToJS(rets[0], wrapper_sig_->GetReturn(), js_context);
7645 } else {
7646 int32_t return_count = static_cast<int32_t>(wrapper_sig_->return_count());
7647 Node* size = gasm_->NumberConstant(return_count);
7648
7649 jsval = BuildCallAllocateJSArray(size, js_context);
7650
7651 Node* fixed_array = gasm_->LoadJSArrayElements(jsval);
7652
7653 for (int i = 0; i < return_count; ++i) {
7654 Node* value = ToJS(rets[i], wrapper_sig_->GetReturn(i), js_context);
7655 gasm_->StoreFixedArrayElementAny(fixed_array, i, value);
7656 }
7657 }
7658 return jsval;
7659 }
7660
7661 bool QualifiesForFastTransform(const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig) {
7662 const int wasm_count = static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count());
7663 for (int i = 0; i < wasm_count; ++i) {
7664 wasm::CanonicalValueType type = sig->GetParam(i);
7665 switch (type.kind()) {
7666 case wasm::kRef:
7667 case wasm::kRefNull:
7668 case wasm::kI64:
7669 case wasm::kRtt:
7670 case wasm::kS128:
7671 case wasm::kI8:
7672 case wasm::kI16:
7673 case wasm::kF16:
7674 case wasm::kTop:
7675 case wasm::kBottom:
7676 case wasm::kVoid:
7677 return false;
7678 case wasm::kI32:
7679 case wasm::kF32:
7680 case wasm::kF64:
7681 break;
7682 }
7683 }
7684 return true;
7685 }
7686
7687 Node* IsSmi(Node* input) {
7688 return gasm_->Word32Equal(
7689 gasm_->Word32And(gasm_->BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(input),
7690 Int32Constant(kSmiTagMask)),
7691 Int32Constant(kSmiTag));
7692 }
7693
7694 void CanTransformFast(
7695 Node* input, wasm::CanonicalValueType type,
7696 v8::internal::compiler::GraphAssemblerLabel<0>* slow_path) {
7697 switch (type.kind()) {
7698 case wasm::kI32: {
7699 gasm_->GotoIfNot(IsSmi(input), slow_path);
7700 return;
7701 }
7702 case wasm::kF32:
7703 case wasm::kF64: {
7704 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel();
7705 gasm_->GotoIf(IsSmi(input), &done);
7706 Node* map = gasm_->LoadMap(input);
7707 Node* heap_number_map = LOAD_ROOT(HeapNumberMap, heap_number_map);
7708#if V8_MAP_PACKING
7709 Node* is_heap_number = gasm_->WordEqual(heap_number_map, map);
7710#else
7711 Node* is_heap_number = gasm_->TaggedEqual(heap_number_map, map);
7712#endif
7713 gasm_->GotoIf(is_heap_number, &done);
7714 gasm_->Goto(slow_path);
7715 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7716 return;
7717 }
7718 case wasm::kRef:
7719 case wasm::kRefNull:
7720 case wasm::kI64:
7721 case wasm::kRtt:
7722 case wasm::kS128:
7723 case wasm::kI8:
7724 case wasm::kI16:
7725 case wasm::kF16:
7726 case wasm::kTop:
7727 case wasm::kBottom:
7728 case wasm::kVoid:
7729 UNREACHABLE();
7730 }
7731 }
7732
7733 void BuildJSToWasmWrapper(bool do_conversion = true,
7734 Node* frame_state = nullptr,
7735 bool set_in_wasm_flag = true) {
7736 const int wasm_param_count =
7737 static_cast<int>(wrapper_sig_->parameter_count());
7738
7739 // Build the start and the JS parameter nodes.
7740 // TODO(saelo): this should probably be a constant with a descriptive name.
7741 // As far as I understand, it's the number of additional parameters in the
7742 // JS calling convention. Also there should be a static_assert here that it
7743 // matches the number of parameters in the JSTrampolineDescriptor?
7744 // static_assert
7745 Start(wasm_param_count + 6);
7746
7747 // Create the js_closure and js_context parameters.
7748 Node* js_closure = Param(Linkage::kJSCallClosureParamIndex, "%closure");
7749 Node* js_context = Param(
7750 Linkage::GetJSCallContextParamIndex(wasm_param_count + 1), "%context");
7751 Node* function_data = gasm_->LoadFunctionDataFromJSFunction(js_closure);
7752
7753 if (!wasm::IsJSCompatibleSignature(wrapper_sig_)) {
7754 // Throw a TypeError. Use the js_context of the calling javascript
7755 // function (passed as a parameter), such that the generated code is
7756 // js_context independent.
7757 BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kWasmThrowJSTypeError, js_context,
7758 nullptr, 0);
7759 TerminateThrow(effect(), control());
7760 return;
7761 }
7762
7763#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
7764 if (v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms && v8_flags.slow_histograms &&
7765 !v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
7766 Node* runtime_call = BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(
7767 Runtime::kWasmTraceBeginExecution, js_context, nullptr, 0);
7768 SetControl(runtime_call);
7769 }
7770#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
7771
7772 const int args_count = wasm_param_count + 1; // +1 for wasm_code.
7773
7774 // Check whether the signature of the function allows for a fast
7775 // transformation (if any params exist that need transformation).
7776 // Create a fast transformation path, only if it does.
7777 bool include_fast_path = do_conversion && wasm_param_count > 0 &&
7778 QualifiesForFastTransform(wrapper_sig_);
7779
7780 // Prepare Param() nodes. Param() nodes can only be created once,
7781 // so we need to use the same nodes along all possible transformation paths.
7782 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> params(args_count);
7783 for (int i = 0; i < wasm_param_count; ++i) params[i + 1] = Param(i + 1);
7784
7785 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
7786 if (include_fast_path) {
7787 auto slow_path = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
7788 // Check if the params received on runtime can be actually transformed
7789 // using the fast transformation. When a param that cannot be transformed
7790 // fast is encountered, skip checking the rest and fall back to the slow
7791 // path.
7792 for (int i = 0; i < wasm_param_count; ++i) {
7793 CanTransformFast(params[i + 1], wrapper_sig_->GetParam(i), &slow_path);
7794 }
7795 // Convert JS parameters to wasm numbers using the fast transformation
7796 // and build the call.
7797 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(args_count);
7798 for (int i = 0; i < wasm_param_count; ++i) {
7799 Node* wasm_param = FromJSFast(params[i + 1], wrapper_sig_->GetParam(i));
7800 args[i + 1] = wasm_param;
7801 }
7802 Node* jsval =
7803 BuildCallAndReturn(js_context, function_data, args, do_conversion,
7804 frame_state, set_in_wasm_flag);
7805
7806#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
7807 if (v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms &&
7808 v8_flags.slow_histograms && !v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
7809 Node* runtime_call = BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(
7810 Runtime::kWasmTraceEndExecution, js_context, nullptr, 0);
7811 SetControl(runtime_call);
7812 }
7813#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
7814
7815 gasm_->Goto(&done, jsval);
7816 gasm_->Bind(&slow_path);
7817 }
7818 // Convert JS parameters to wasm numbers using the default transformation
7819 // and build the call.
7820 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(args_count);
7821 for (int i = 0; i < wasm_param_count; ++i) {
7822 if (do_conversion) {
7823 args[i + 1] = FromJS(params[i + 1], js_context,
7824 wrapper_sig_->GetParam(i), frame_state);
7825 } else {
7826 Node* wasm_param = params[i + 1];
7827
7828 // For Float32 parameters
7829 // we set UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64 in
7830 // simplified-lowering and we need to add here a conversion from Float64
7831 // to Float32.
7832 if (wrapper_sig_->GetParam(i).kind() == wasm::kF32) {
7833 wasm_param = gasm_->TruncateFloat64ToFloat32(wasm_param);
7834 }
7835
7836 args[i + 1] = wasm_param;
7837 }
7838 }
7839
7840 Node* jsval =
7841 BuildCallAndReturn(js_context, function_data, args, do_conversion,
7842 frame_state, set_in_wasm_flag);
7843
7844#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
7845 if (v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms && v8_flags.slow_histograms &&
7846 !v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
7847 Node* runtime_call = BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(
7848 Runtime::kWasmTraceEndExecution, js_context, nullptr, 0);
7849 SetControl(runtime_call);
7850 }
7851#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
7852
7853 // If both the default and a fast transformation paths are present,
7854 // get the return value based on the path used.
7855 if (include_fast_path) {
7856 gasm_->Goto(&done, jsval);
7857 gasm_->Bind(&done);
7858 Return(done.PhiAt(0));
7859 } else {
7860 Return(jsval);
7861 }
7862 if (ContainsInt64(wrapper_sig_)) LowerInt64(wasm::kCalledFromJS);
7863 }
7864
7865 Node* BuildReceiverNode(Node* callable_node, Node* native_context,
7866 Node* undefined_node) {
7867 // Check function strict bit.
7868 Node* shared_function_info = gasm_->LoadSharedFunctionInfo(callable_node);
7869 Node* flags = gasm_->LoadFromObject(
7870 MachineType::Int32(), shared_function_info,
7871 wasm::ObjectAccess::FlagsOffsetInSharedFunctionInfo());
7872 Node* strict_check =
7873 Binop(wasm::kExprI32And, flags,
7874 Int32Constant(SharedFunctionInfo::IsNativeBit::kMask |
7875 SharedFunctionInfo::IsStrictBit::kMask));
7876
7877 // Load global receiver if sloppy else use undefined.
7878 Diamond strict_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), strict_check,
7879 BranchHint::kNone);
7880 Node* old_effect = effect();
7881 SetControl(strict_d.if_false);
7882 Node* global_proxy = gasm_->LoadFixedArrayElementPtr(
7883 native_context, Context::GLOBAL_PROXY_INDEX);
7884 SetEffectControl(strict_d.EffectPhi(old_effect, global_proxy),
7885 strict_d.merge);
7886 return strict_d.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, undefined_node,
7887 global_proxy);
7888 }
7889
7890 Node* BuildSuspend(Node* value, Node* import_data, Node** old_sp) {
7891 Node* native_context = gasm_->Load(
7892 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), import_data,
7893 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmImportData::kNativeContextOffset));
7894 // If value is a promise, suspend to the js-to-wasm prompt, and resume later
7895 // with the promise's resolved value.
7896 auto resume = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged,
7897 MachineType::UintPtr().representation());
7898 gasm_->GotoIf(IsSmi(value), &resume, value, *old_sp);
7899 gasm_->GotoIfNot(gasm_->HasInstanceType(value, JS_PROMISE_TYPE), &resume,
7900 BranchHint::kTrue, value, *old_sp);
7901
7902 // Trap if the suspender is undefined, which occurs when the export was
7903 // not wrapped with WebAssembly.promising.
7904 Node* suspender = LOAD_MUTABLE_ROOT(ActiveSuspender, active_suspender);
7905 auto bad_suspender = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
7906 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->TaggedEqual(suspender, UndefinedValue()),
7907 &bad_suspender, BranchHint::kFalse);
7908
7909 if (v8_flags.stress_wasm_stack_switching) {
7910 Node* undefined = LOAD_ROOT(UndefinedValue, undefined_value);
7911 Node* for_stress_testing = gasm_->TaggedEqual(
7912 gasm_->Load(
7913 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), suspender,
7914 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmSuspenderObject::kResumeOffset)),
7915 undefined);
7916 gasm_->GotoIf(for_stress_testing, &bad_suspender);
7917 }
7918
7919 auto* call_descriptor = GetBuiltinCallDescriptor(
7920 Builtin::kWasmSuspend, zone_, StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
7921 Node* call_target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(Builtin::kWasmSuspend);
7922 // If {old_sp} is null, it must be that we were on the central stack before
7923 // entering the wasm-to-js wrapper, which means that there are JS frames in
7924 // the current suspender. JS frames cannot be suspended, so trap.
7925 Node* has_js_frames = gasm_->IntPtrEqual(gasm_->IntPtrConstant(0), *old_sp);
7926 auto suspend = gasm_->MakeLabel();
7927 gasm_->GotoIfNot(has_js_frames, &suspend);
7928 // {ThrowWasmError} expects to be called from wasm code, so set the
7929 // thread-in-wasm flag now.
7930 // Usually we set this flag later so that it stays off while we convert the
7931 // return values. This is a special case, it is safe to set it now because
7932 // the error will unwind this frame.
7933 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
7934 Node* frames_error = gasm_->SmiConstant(
7935 static_cast<int32_t>(MessageTemplate::kWasmSuspendJSFrames));
7936 BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kThrowWasmSuspendError,
7937 native_context, &frames_error, 1);
7938 TerminateThrow(effect(), control());
7939
7940 gasm_->Bind(&suspend);
7941 Node* on_fulfilled = gasm_->Load(
7942 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), suspender,
7943 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmSuspenderObject::kResumeOffset));
7944 Node* on_rejected = gasm_->Load(
7945 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), suspender,
7946 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmSuspenderObject::kRejectOffset));
7947
7948 auto* then_call_desc = GetBuiltinCallDescriptor(
7949 Builtin::kPerformPromiseThen, zone_, StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
7950 Node* then_target =
7951 gasm_->GetBuiltinPointerTarget(Builtin::kPerformPromiseThen);
7952 gasm_->Call(then_call_desc, then_target, value, on_fulfilled, on_rejected,
7953 UndefinedValue(), native_context);
7954
7955 BuildSwitchBackFromCentralStack(*old_sp);
7956 Node* resolved = gasm_->Call(call_descriptor, call_target, suspender);
7957 BuildSwitchToTheCentralStack();
7958 gasm_->Goto(&resume, resolved, *old_sp);
7959
7960 gasm_->Bind(&bad_suspender);
7961
7962 Node* suspendError = gasm_->SmiConstant(
7963 static_cast<int32_t>(MessageTemplate::kWasmSuspendError));
7964 BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kThrowWasmSuspendError,
7965 native_context, &suspendError, 1);
7966
7967 TerminateThrow(effect(), control());
7968 gasm_->Bind(&resume);
7969 *old_sp = resume.PhiAt(1);
7970 return resume.PhiAt(0);
7971 }
7972
7973 Node* BuildSwitchToTheCentralStack() {
7974 Node* do_switch = gasm_->ExternalConstant(
7975 ExternalReference::wasm_switch_to_the_central_stack_for_js());
7976 MachineType reps[] = {MachineType::Pointer(), MachineType::Pointer(),
7977 MachineType::Pointer()};
7978 MachineSignature sig(1, 2, reps);
7979
7980 Node* central_stack_sp = BuildCCall(
7981 &sig, do_switch,
7982 gasm_->ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::isolate_address()),
7983 gasm_->LoadFramePointer());
7984 Node* old_sp = gasm_->LoadStackPointer();
7985 // Temporarily disallow sp-relative offsets.
7986 gasm_->SetStackPointer(central_stack_sp);
7987 return old_sp;
7988 }
7989
7990 void BuildSwitchBackFromCentralStack(Node* old_sp) {
7991 auto skip = gasm_->MakeLabel();
7992 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->IntPtrEqual(old_sp, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(0)), &skip);
7993 Node* do_switch = gasm_->ExternalConstant(
7994 ExternalReference::wasm_switch_from_the_central_stack_for_js());
7995 MachineType reps[] = {MachineType::Pointer()};
7996 MachineSignature sig(0, 1, reps);
7997 BuildCCall(&sig, do_switch,
7998 gasm_->ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::isolate_address()));
7999 gasm_->SetStackPointer(old_sp);
8000 gasm_->Goto(&skip);
8001 gasm_->Bind(&skip);
8002 }
8003
8004 Node* BuildSwitchToTheCentralStackIfNeeded() {
8005 // If the current stack is a secondary stack, switch to the central stack.
8006 auto end = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
8007 Node* isolate_root = BuildLoadIsolateRoot();
8008 Node* is_on_central_stack_flag =
8009 gasm_->Load(MachineType::Uint8(), isolate_root,
8010 IsolateData::is_on_central_stack_flag_offset());
8011 gasm_->GotoIf(is_on_central_stack_flag, &end, BranchHint::kTrue,
8012 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(0));
8013
8014 Node* old_sp = BuildSwitchToTheCentralStack();
8015 gasm_->Goto(&end, old_sp);
8016
8017 gasm_->Bind(&end);
8018 return end.PhiAt(0);
8019 }
8020
8021 // For wasm-to-js wrappers, parameter 0 is a WasmImportData.
8022 void BuildWasmToJSWrapper(wasm::ImportCallKind kind, int expected_arity,
8023 wasm::Suspend suspend) {
8024 int wasm_count = static_cast<int>(wrapper_sig_->parameter_count());
8025
8026 // Build the start and the parameter nodes.
8027 Start(wasm_count + 3);
8028
8029 Node* native_context = gasm_->Load(
8030 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), Param(0),
8031 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmImportData::kNativeContextOffset));
8032
8033 if (kind == wasm::ImportCallKind::kRuntimeTypeError) {
8034 // =======================================================================
8035 // === Runtime TypeError =================================================
8036 // =======================================================================
8037 BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kWasmThrowJSTypeError,
8038 native_context, nullptr, 0);
8039 TerminateThrow(effect(), control());
8040 return;
8041 }
8042
8043#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
8044 if (v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms && v8_flags.slow_histograms &&
8045 !v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
8046 Node* runtime_call = BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(
8047 Runtime::kWasmTraceEndExecution, native_context, nullptr, 0);
8048 SetControl(runtime_call);
8049 }
8050#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
8051
8052 Node* callable_node = gasm_->Load(
8053 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), Param(0),
8054 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmImportData::kCallableOffset));
8055 Node* old_sp = BuildSwitchToTheCentralStackIfNeeded();
8056
8057 Node* undefined_node = UndefinedValue();
8058 Node* call = nullptr;
8059 // Clear the ThreadInWasm flag.
8060 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(false);
8061 switch (kind) {
8062 // =======================================================================
8063 // === JS Functions with matching arity ==================================
8064 // =======================================================================
8065 case wasm::ImportCallKind::kJSFunctionArityMatch:
8066 DCHECK_EQ(expected_arity, wasm_count);
8067 [[fallthrough]];
8068 case wasm::ImportCallKind::kJSFunctionArityMismatch: {
8069 int pushed_count = std::max(expected_arity, wasm_count);
8070 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(pushed_count + 8);
8071 int pos = 0;
8072
8073 args[pos++] = callable_node; // target callable.
8074 // Determine receiver at runtime.
8075 args[pos++] =
8076 BuildReceiverNode(callable_node, native_context, undefined_node);
8077
8078 // Convert wasm numbers to JS values.
8079 pos = AddArgumentNodes(base::VectorOf(args), pos, wasm_count,
8080 wrapper_sig_, native_context);
8081 for (int i = wasm_count; i < expected_arity; ++i) {
8082 args[pos++] = undefined_node;
8083 }
8084 args[pos++] = undefined_node; // new target
8085 args[pos++] =
8086 Int32Constant(JSParameterCount(wasm_count)); // argument count
8087#ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
8088 args[pos++] = Int32Constant(kPlaceholderDispatchHandle.value());
8089#endif
8090
8091 Node* function_context =
8092 gasm_->LoadContextFromJSFunction(callable_node);
8093 args[pos++] = function_context;
8094 args[pos++] = effect();
8095 args[pos++] = control();
8096
8097 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetJSCallDescriptor(
8098 graph()->zone(), false, pushed_count + 1, CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
8099 call = gasm_->Call(call_descriptor, pos, args.begin());
8100 break;
8101 }
8102 // =======================================================================
8103 // === General case of unknown callable ==================================
8104 // =======================================================================
8105 case wasm::ImportCallKind::kUseCallBuiltin: {
8106 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(wasm_count + 7);
8107 int pos = 0;
8108 args[pos++] =
8109 gasm_->GetBuiltinPointerTarget(Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsAny);
8110 args[pos++] = callable_node;
8111 args[pos++] =
8112 Int32Constant(JSParameterCount(wasm_count)); // argument count
8113 args[pos++] = undefined_node; // receiver
8114
8115 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
8116 graph()->zone(), CallTrampolineDescriptor{}, wasm_count + 1,
8117 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties,
8118 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
8119
8120 // Convert wasm numbers to JS values.
8121 pos = AddArgumentNodes(base::VectorOf(args), pos, wasm_count,
8122 wrapper_sig_, native_context);
8123
8124 // The native_context is sufficient here, because all kind of callables
8125 // which depend on the context provide their own context. The context
8126 // here is only needed if the target is a constructor to throw a
8127 // TypeError, if the target is a native function, or if the target is a
8128 // callable JSObject, which can only be constructed by the runtime.
8129 args[pos++] = native_context;
8130 args[pos++] = effect();
8131 args[pos++] = control();
8132 call = gasm_->Call(call_descriptor, pos, args.begin());
8133 break;
8134 }
8135 default:
8136 UNREACHABLE();
8137 }
8138 // For asm.js the error location can differ depending on whether an
8139 // exception was thrown in imported JS code or an exception was thrown in
8140 // the ToNumber builtin that converts the result of the JS code a
8141 // WebAssembly value. The source position allows asm.js to determine the
8142 // correct error location. Source position 1 encodes the call to ToNumber,
8143 // source position 0 encodes the call to the imported JS code.
8144 SetSourcePosition(call, 0);
8145 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(call);
8146
8147#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
8148 if (v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms && v8_flags.slow_histograms &&
8149 !v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
8150 Node* runtime_call = BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(
8151 Runtime::kWasmTraceBeginExecution, native_context, nullptr, 0);
8152 SetControl(runtime_call);
8153 }
8154#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
8155
8156 if (suspend == wasm::kSuspend) {
8157 call = BuildSuspend(call, Param(0), &old_sp);
8158 }
8159
8160 // Convert the return value(s) back.
8161 Node* val;
8162 base::SmallVector<Node*, 8> wasm_values;
8163 if (wrapper_sig_->return_count() <= 1) {
8164 val = wrapper_sig_->return_count() == 0
8165 ? Int32Constant(0)
8166 : FromJS(call, native_context, wrapper_sig_->GetReturn());
8167 } else {
8168 Node* fixed_array = BuildMultiReturnFixedArrayFromIterable(
8169 wrapper_sig_, call, native_context);
8170 wasm_values.resize_no_init(wrapper_sig_->return_count());
8171 for (unsigned i = 0; i < wrapper_sig_->return_count(); ++i) {
8172 wasm_values[i] = FromJS(gasm_->LoadFixedArrayElementAny(fixed_array, i),
8173 native_context, wrapper_sig_->GetReturn(i));
8174 }
8175 }
8176 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
8177
8178 BuildSwitchBackFromCentralStack(old_sp);
8179 if (wrapper_sig_->return_count() <= 1) {
8180 Return(val);
8181 } else {
8182 Return(base::VectorOf(wasm_values));
8183 }
8184
8185 if (ContainsInt64(wrapper_sig_)) LowerInt64(wasm::kCalledFromWasm);
8186 }
8187
8188 void BuildJSFastApiCallWrapper(DirectHandle<JSReceiver> callable) {
8189 // Here 'callable_node' must be equal to 'callable' but we cannot pass a
8190 // HeapConstant(callable) because WasmCode::Validate() fails with
8191 // Unexpected mode: FULL_EMBEDDED_OBJECT.
8192 Node* callable_node = gasm_->Load(
8193 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), Param(0),
8194 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmImportData::kCallableOffset));
8195 Node* native_context = gasm_->Load(
8196 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), Param(0),
8197 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmImportData::kNativeContextOffset));
8198
8199 gasm_->Store(StoreRepresentation(mcgraph_->machine()->Is64()
8200 ? MachineRepresentation::kWord64
8201 : MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
8202 WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier),
8203 gasm_->LoadRootRegister(), Isolate::context_offset(),
8204 gasm_->BitcastMaybeObjectToWord(native_context));
8205
8206 Node* undefined_node = UndefinedValue();
8207
8208 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(false);
8209
8210 DirectHandle<JSFunction> target;
8211 Node* target_node;
8212 Node* receiver_node;
8213 Isolate* isolate = callable->GetIsolate();
8214 if (IsJSBoundFunction(*callable)) {
8215 target = direct_handle(
8216 Cast<JSFunction>(
8217 Cast<JSBoundFunction>(callable)->bound_target_function()),
8218 isolate);
8219 target_node =
8220 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), callable_node,
8221 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
8222 JSBoundFunction::kBoundTargetFunctionOffset));
8223 receiver_node = gasm_->Load(
8224 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), callable_node,
8225 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(JSBoundFunction::kBoundThisOffset));
8226 } else {
8227 DCHECK(IsJSFunction(*callable));
8228 target = Cast<JSFunction>(callable);
8229 target_node = callable_node;
8230 receiver_node =
8231 BuildReceiverNode(callable_node, native_context, undefined_node);
8232 }
8233
8234 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = target->shared();
8235 Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> api_func_data = shared->api_func_data();
8236 const Address c_address = api_func_data->GetCFunction(isolate, 0);
8237 const v8::CFunctionInfo* c_signature =
8238 api_func_data->GetCSignature(target->GetIsolate(), 0);
8239
8240#ifdef V8_USE_SIMULATOR_WITH_GENERIC_C_CALLS
8241 Address c_functions[] = {c_address};
8242 const v8::CFunctionInfo* const c_signatures[] = {c_signature};
8243 target->GetIsolate()->simulator_data()->RegisterFunctionsAndSignatures(
8244 c_functions, c_signatures, 1);
8245#endif // V8_USE_SIMULATOR_WITH_GENERIC_C_CALLS
8246
8247 Node* shared_function_info = gasm_->LoadSharedFunctionInfo(target_node);
8248 Node* function_template_info =
8249 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), shared_function_info,
8250 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
8251 SharedFunctionInfo::kUntrustedFunctionDataOffset));
8252 Node* api_data_argument =
8253 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), function_template_info,
8254 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
8255 FunctionTemplateInfo::kCallbackDataOffset));
8256
8257 FastApiCallFunction c_function{c_address, c_signature};
8258 Node* call = fast_api_call::BuildFastApiCall(
8259 target->GetIsolate(), graph(), gasm_.get(), c_function,
8260 api_data_argument,
8261 // Load and convert parameters passed to C function
8262 [this, c_signature, receiver_node](int param_index,
8263 GraphAssemblerLabel<0>*) {
8264 if (param_index == 0) {
8265 return gasm_->AdaptLocalArgument(receiver_node);
8266 }
8267 switch (c_signature->ArgumentInfo(param_index).GetType()) {
8268 case CTypeInfo::Type::kV8Value:
8269 return gasm_->AdaptLocalArgument(Param(param_index));
8270 default:
8271 return Param(param_index);
8272 }
8273 },
8274 // Convert return value (no conversion needed for wasm)
8275 [](const CFunctionInfo* signature, Node* c_return_value) {
8276 return c_return_value;
8277 },
8278 [](Node* options_stack_slot) {},
8279 // Generate fallback slow call if fast call fails
8280 [this, callable_node, native_context, receiver_node]() -> Node* {
8281 int wasm_count = static_cast<int>(wrapper_sig_->parameter_count());
8282 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(wasm_count + 7);
8283 int pos = 0;
8284 args[pos++] =
8285 gasm_->GetBuiltinPointerTarget(Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsAny);
8286 args[pos++] = callable_node;
8287 args[pos++] =
8288 Int32Constant(JSParameterCount(wasm_count)); // argument count
8289 args[pos++] = receiver_node; // receiver
8290
8291 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
8292 graph()->zone(), CallTrampolineDescriptor{}, wasm_count + 1,
8293 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties,
8294 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
8295
8296 // Convert wasm numbers to JS values.
8297 pos = AddArgumentNodes(base::VectorOf(args), pos, wasm_count,
8298 wrapper_sig_, native_context);
8299
8300 // The native_context is sufficient here, because all kind of
8301 // callables which depend on the context provide their own context.
8302 // The context here is only needed if the target is a constructor to
8303 // throw a TypeError, if the target is a native function, or if the
8304 // target is a callable JSObject, which can only be constructed by the
8305 // runtime.
8306 args[pos++] = native_context;
8307 args[pos++] = effect();
8308 args[pos++] = control();
8309
8310 DCHECK_EQ(pos, args.size());
8311 Node* call = gasm_->Call(call_descriptor, pos, args.begin());
8312 return wrapper_sig_->return_count() == 0
8313 ? Int32Constant(0)
8314 : FromJS(call, native_context, wrapper_sig_->GetReturn(),
8315 nullptr);
8316 });
8317
8318 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
8319
8320 Return(call);
8321 }
8322
8323 void BuildCWasmEntry() {
8324 // +1 offset for first parameter index being -1.
8325 Start(CWasmEntryParameters::kNumParameters + 1);
8326
8327 Node* code_entry = Param(CWasmEntryParameters::kCodeEntry);
8328 Node* object_ref = Param(CWasmEntryParameters::kObjectRef);
8329 Node* arg_buffer = Param(CWasmEntryParameters::kArgumentsBuffer);
8330 Node* c_entry_fp = Param(CWasmEntryParameters::kCEntryFp);
8331
8332 Node* fp_value = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->LoadFramePointer());
8333 gasm_->Store(StoreRepresentation(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
8334 kNoWriteBarrier),
8335 fp_value, TypedFrameConstants::kFirstPushedFrameValueOffset,
8336 c_entry_fp);
8337
8338 int wasm_arg_count = static_cast<int>(wrapper_sig_->parameter_count());
8339 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(wasm_arg_count + 4);
8340
8341 int pos = 0;
8342 args[pos++] = code_entry;
8343 args[pos++] = gasm_->LoadTrustedDataFromInstanceObject(object_ref);
8344
8345 int offset = 0;
8346 for (wasm::CanonicalValueType type : wrapper_sig_->parameters()) {
8347 Node* arg_load = SetEffect(
8348 graph()->NewNode(GetSafeLoadOperator(offset, type), arg_buffer,
8349 Int32Constant(offset), effect(), control()));
8350 args[pos++] = arg_load;
8351 offset += type.value_kind_size();
8352 }
8353
8354 args[pos++] = effect();
8355 args[pos++] = control();
8356
8357 // Call the wasm code.
8358 auto call_descriptor = GetWasmCallDescriptor(
8359 mcgraph()->zone(), wrapper_sig_, WasmCallKind::kWasmIndirectFunction);
8360
8361 DCHECK_EQ(pos, args.size());
8362 Node* call = gasm_->Call(call_descriptor, pos, args.begin());
8363
8364 Node* if_success = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfSuccess(), call);
8365 Node* if_exception =
8366 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfException(), call, call);
8367
8368 // Handle exception: return it.
8369 SetEffectControl(if_exception);
8370 Return(if_exception);
8371
8372 // Handle success: store the return value(s).
8373 SetEffectControl(call, if_success);
8374 pos = 0;
8375 offset = 0;
8376 for (wasm::CanonicalValueType type : wrapper_sig_->returns()) {
8377 Node* value = wrapper_sig_->return_count() == 1
8378 ? call
8379 : graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Projection(pos),
8380 call, control());
8381 SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(GetSafeStoreOperator(offset, type), arg_buffer,
8382 Int32Constant(offset), value, effect(),
8383 control()));
8384 offset += type.value_kind_size();
8385 pos++;
8386 }
8387
8388 Return(mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(0));
8389
8390 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32() && ContainsInt64(wrapper_sig_)) {
8391 // These correspond to {sig_types[]} in {CompileCWasmEntry}.
8392 MachineRepresentation sig_reps[] = {
8393 MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), // return value
8394 MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), // target
8395 MachineRepresentation::kTagged, // object_ref
8396 MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), // argv
8397 MachineType::PointerRepresentation() // c_entry_fp
8398 };
8399 Signature<MachineRepresentation> c_entry_sig(1, 4, sig_reps);
8400 Int64Lowering r(mcgraph()->graph(), mcgraph()->machine(),
8401 mcgraph()->common(), gasm_->simplified(),
8402 mcgraph()->zone(), &c_entry_sig);
8403 r.LowerGraph();
8404 }
8405 }
8406
8407 private:
8408 SetOncePointer<const Operator> int32_to_heapnumber_operator_;
8409 SetOncePointer<const Operator> tagged_non_smi_to_int32_operator_;
8410 SetOncePointer<const Operator> float32_to_number_operator_;
8411 SetOncePointer<const Operator> float64_to_number_operator_;
8412 SetOncePointer<const Operator> tagged_to_float64_operator_;
8413};
8414
8415} // namespace

8447
8448wasm::WasmCompilationResult CompileWasmImportCallWrapper(
8449 wasm::ImportCallKind kind, const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig,
8450 bool source_positions, int expected_arity, wasm::Suspend suspend) {
8451 DCHECK_NE(wasm::ImportCallKind::kLinkError, kind);
8452 DCHECK_NE(wasm::ImportCallKind::kWasmToWasm, kind);
8453 DCHECK_NE(wasm::ImportCallKind::kWasmToJSFastApi, kind);
8454
8455 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.wasm.detailed"),
8456 "wasm.CompileWasmImportCallWrapper");
8457 base::TimeTicks start_time;
8458 if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_compilation_times)) {
8459 start_time = base::TimeTicks::Now();
8460 }
8461
8462 // Build a name in the form "wasm-to-js-<kind>-<signature>".
8463 constexpr size_t kMaxNameLen = 128;
8464 char func_name[kMaxNameLen];
8465 int name_prefix_len = SNPrintF(base::VectorOf(func_name, kMaxNameLen),
8466 "wasm-to-js-%d-", static_cast<int>(kind));
8467 PrintSignature(base::VectorOf(func_name, kMaxNameLen) + name_prefix_len, sig,
8468 '-');
8469
8470 auto result = Pipeline::GenerateCodeForWasmNativeStubFromTurboshaft(
8471 sig,
8472 wasm::WrapperCompilationInfo{CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION, kind,
8473 expected_arity, suspend},
8474 func_name, WasmStubAssemblerOptions(), nullptr);
8475
8476 if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.trace_wasm_compilation_times)) {
8477 base::TimeDelta time = base::TimeTicks::Now() - start_time;
8478 int codesize = result.code_desc.body_size();
8479 StdoutStream{} << "Compiled WasmToJS wrapper " << func_name << ", took "
8480 << time.InMilliseconds() << " ms; codesize " << codesize
8481 << std::endl;
8482 }
8483
8484 return result;
8485}
8486
8487wasm::WasmCompilationResult CompileWasmCapiCallWrapper(
8488 const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig) {
8489 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.wasm.detailed"),
8490 "wasm.CompileWasmCapiFunction");
8491
8492 return Pipeline::GenerateCodeForWasmNativeStubFromTurboshaft(
8493 sig, wasm::WrapperCompilationInfo{CodeKind::WASM_TO_CAPI_FUNCTION},
8494 "WasmCapiCall", WasmStubAssemblerOptions(), nullptr);
8495}

8500
8501wasm::WasmCompilationResult CompileWasmJSFastCallWrapper(
8502 const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> callable) {
8503 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.wasm.detailed"),
8504 "wasm.CompileWasmJSFastCallWrapper");
8505
8506 Zone zone(wasm::GetWasmEngine()->allocator(), ZONE_NAME, kCompressGraphZone);
8507 SourcePositionTable* source_positions = nullptr;
8508 MachineGraph* mcgraph = CreateCommonMachineGraph(&zone);
8509
8510 WasmWrapperGraphBuilder builder(&zone, mcgraph, sig,
8511 WasmGraphBuilder::kWasmImportDataMode,
8512 nullptr, source_positions);
8513
8514 // Set up the graph start.
8515 int param_count = static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count()) +
8516 1 /* offset for first parameter index being -1 */ +
8517 1 /* Wasm instance */ + 1 /* kExtraCallableParam */;
8518 builder.Start(param_count);
8519 builder.BuildJSFastApiCallWrapper(callable);
8520
8521 // Run the compiler pipeline to generate machine code.
8522 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
8523 GetWasmCallDescriptor(&zone, sig, WasmCallKind::kWasmImportWrapper);
8524 if (mcgraph->machine()->Is32()) {
8525 call_descriptor = GetI32WasmCallDescriptor(&zone, call_descriptor);
8526 }
8527
8528 const char* debug_name = "WasmJSFastApiCall";
8529 wasm::WasmCompilationResult result = Pipeline::GenerateCodeForWasmNativeStub(
8530 call_descriptor, mcgraph, CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION, debug_name,
8531 WasmStubAssemblerOptions(), source_positions);
8532 return result;
8533}
8534
8535Handle<Code> CompileCWasmEntry(Isolate* isolate,
8536 const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig) {
8537 DCHECK(!v8_flags.wasm_jitless);
8538
8539 std::unique_ptr<Zone> zone = std::make_unique<Zone>(
8540 isolate->allocator(), ZONE_NAME, kCompressGraphZone);
8541 Graph* graph = zone->New<Graph>(zone.get());
8542 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = zone->New<CommonOperatorBuilder>(zone.get());
8543 MachineOperatorBuilder* machine = zone->New<MachineOperatorBuilder>(
8544 zone.get(), MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
8545 InstructionSelector::SupportedMachineOperatorFlags(),
8546 InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements());
8547 MachineGraph* mcgraph = zone->New<MachineGraph>(graph, common, machine);
8548
8549 WasmWrapperGraphBuilder builder(zone.get(), mcgraph, sig,
8550 WasmGraphBuilder::kNoSpecialParameterMode,
8551 nullptr, nullptr);
8552 builder.BuildCWasmEntry();
8553
8554 // Schedule and compile to machine code.
8555 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Pointer(), // return
8556 MachineType::Pointer(), // target
8557 MachineType::AnyTagged(), // object_ref
8558 MachineType::Pointer(), // argv
8559 MachineType::Pointer()}; // c_entry_fp
8560 MachineSignature incoming_sig(1, 4, sig_types);
8561 // Traps need the root register, for TailCallRuntime to call
8562 // Runtime::kThrowWasmError.
8563 CallDescriptor::Flags flags = CallDescriptor::kInitializeRootRegister;
8564 CallDescriptor* incoming =
8565 Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(zone.get(), &incoming_sig, flags);
8566
8567 // Build a name in the form "c-wasm-entry:<params>:<returns>".
8568 constexpr size_t kMaxNameLen = 128;
8569 constexpr size_t kNamePrefixLen = 13;
8570 auto name_buffer = std::unique_ptr<char[]>(new char[kMaxNameLen]);
8571 memcpy(name_buffer.get(), "c-wasm-entry:", kNamePrefixLen);
8572 PrintSignature(
8573 base::VectorOf(name_buffer.get(), kMaxNameLen) + kNamePrefixLen, sig);
8574
8575 // Run the compilation job synchronously.
8576 std::unique_ptr<TurbofanCompilationJob> job(
8577 Pipeline::NewWasmHeapStubCompilationJob(
8578 isolate, incoming, std::move(zone), graph, CodeKind::C_WASM_ENTRY,
8579 std::move(name_buffer), AssemblerOptions::Default(isolate)));
8580
8581 CHECK_NE(job->ExecuteJob(isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats(), nullptr),
8582 CompilationJob::FAILED);
8583 CHECK_NE(job->FinalizeJob(isolate), CompilationJob::FAILED);
8584
8585 return job->compilation_info()->code();
8586}

8596
8597AssemblerOptions WasmAssemblerOptions() {
8598 return AssemblerOptions{
8599 // Relocation info required to serialize {WasmCode} for proper functions.
8600 .record_reloc_info_for_serialization = true,
8601 .enable_root_relative_access = false,
8602 .is_wasm = true,
8603 };
8604}
8605
8606AssemblerOptions WasmStubAssemblerOptions() {
8607 return AssemblerOptions{
8608 // Relocation info not necessary because stubs are not serialized.
8609 .record_reloc_info_for_serialization = false,
8610 .enable_root_relative_access = false,
8611 // TODO(jkummerow): Would it be better to have a far jump table in
8612 // the wrapper cache's code space, and call builtins through that?
8613 .builtin_call_jump_mode = BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect,
8614 .is_wasm = true,
8615 };
8616}
